第一步

First Steps

我使用 Emacs，它可能被认为是一个热核文字处理器。

– Neal Stephenson，一开始……是命令行。

I use Emacs, which might be thought of as a thermonuclear word processor.

– Neal Stephenson, In the Beginning… was the Command Line.

安装并启动 Emacs

Installing and Starting Emacs

在我详细介绍安装 Emacs 之前，您应该检查一下它是否已经安装。但是，如果是的话，你必须格外警惕：它可能是一个古老的版本。

Before I get into the nitty-gritty of installing Emacs, you should check and see if it’s installed already. However, you have to be extra vigilant if it is: it might be an ancient version.

检查 Emacs 的版本

您可以通过键入 来检查 Emacs 的版本emacs --version。

Checking Emacs’s version

You can check Emacs’s version by typing emacs --version.

截至 2020 年，最新的主要版本是 GNU Emacs 27。如果您的 Emacs 版本是23.x或更早版本，请升级。如果是24.x或更新版本，那么对于大多数情况来说通常就可以了。理想情况下，您应该尝试保持最新状态：Emacs 中的主要版本并不频繁，因此保持最新状态不会给您带来太多麻烦。如果您确实升级，则很少是为了修复错误（因为 Emacs 实际上非常稳定），而是为了功能以及大多数软件包作者假设您使用的是最新版本这一事实。 （话虽如此，如果您使用的是一个非常不起眼的平台，则可能根本无法升级。）

As of 2020 the newest major version is GNU Emacs 27. If your version of Emacs is version 23.x or older — upgrade. If it’s 24.x or newer, then that’s generally fine for most things. Ideally you should try to stay current: major releases in Emacs are infrequent enough that keeping abreast shouldn’t trouble you much. If you do upgrade, it’s rarely for the bug fixes (because Emacs is actually extremely stable) but for the features and the fact that most package authors assume you’re using the latest version. (Having said that, if you’re on a very obscure platform it may not be possible for you to upgrade at all.)

如果您正在使用 XEmacs 或其他非 GNU Emacs，您确实应该切换。十五年前，XEmacs 处于领先地位，但 GNU Emacs 很久以前就赶上了并超越了 XEmacs 的功能。

If you’re using XEmacs or another non-GNU Emacs, you really should switch. Fifteen years ago, XEmacs was leading the pack but GNU Emacs caught up and exceeded the capabilities of XEmacs a long time ago.

令人惊讶的是，Emacs 可以在一些非常古老的平台上运行1，直到 Emacs 23.1（2009 年 7 月发布）为止，其中包括： Tandem Integrity S2；阿波罗 SR10.x；橡子；哈里斯夜鹰 1200 系列和 3000 系列；还有大约两三打其他不知名的平台。现在已经很少了，但是 Emacs 维护者非常重视向后兼容性和遗留支持。 Emacs 的一个标志是它长期以来坚信，破坏兼容性应该导致多个主要版本从弃用到删除。罕见的是，Emacs 邮件列表中涌入了抱怨，称他们在 20 世纪 80 年代末编写的一段代码突然崩溃了，因为 Emacs 维护者最终删除了一个长期废弃的变量或函数。

Surprisingly, Emacs ran on some incredibly old platforms1 until Emacs 23.1 (released in July 2009), including the following: Tandem Integrity S2; Apollo SR10.x; the Acorn; the Harris Night Hawk Series 1200 and Series 3000; and about another two or three dozen more obscure platforms. There are fewer today, but the Emacs maintainers are serious about backwards compatibility and legacy support. A hallmark of Emacs is its long held belief that breaking compatibility should take multiple major releases from deprecation to removal. Uncommonly, complaints stream into the Emacs mailing lists that a piece of code they wrote in the late 1980s suddenly broke because the Emacs maintainers finally removed a long-obsoleted variable or function.

Emacs 支持您可能使用的大多数主要平台：BSD 和 Linux、Mac OSX、MS-DOS 和 Microsoft Windows。我不会详细介绍如何在 Linux 以外的操作系统上编译或构建 Emacs。 Emacs 被设计为一个跨平台编辑器，但如果你不在 Linux 上运行它们，总会有一些权衡。尤其是 Mac OSX，关于如何最好地运行 Emacs 似乎引起了大量相互矛盾的建议。我能提供的最好建议是尝试几种不同的方法并找到适合您的方法。

Emacs supports most major platforms you are likely to use yourself: BSD and Linux, Mac OSX, MS-DOS, and Microsoft Windows. I will not go into too great a detail on how to compile or build Emacs on operating systems other than Linux. Emacs was made to be a cross platform editor but there are always some trade-offs if you don’t run them on Linux. Mac OSX, in particular, seems to attract a great deal of conflicting advice on how to best run Emacs; the best advice I can offer is to try out a few different approaches and find one that fits you.

微软Windows
Microsoft Windows

Emacs 在其官方网站上发布了 Microsoft Windows 的官方版本。2只需提取并运行可执行文件即可。

大多数外部工具支持在 Windows 上不起作用。诸如内置grep支持之类的功能需要 GNU coreutils 的存在。不过，您可以从 Cygwin 3运行 Emacs ，并以这种方式在 Windows 上获得类似 Linux 的环境。或者，交叉编译的 GnuWin32 4项目几乎包含了在 Windows 上本机运行的所有 Linux 命令行程序。

另一个新的机会是使用适用于 Linux 的 Windows 子系统，这是一个在 Windows 10 子系统之上本机运行 Linux 的兼容层。

Emacs releases official builds for Microsoft Windows on their official site.2 Extracting and running the executable is all it takes.

Most external tool support will not work on Windows. Functionality like built-in grep support requires the GNU coreutils to be present. You can, however, run Emacs from Cygwin3 and get a Linux-like environment on Windows that way. Alternatively, the cross-compiled GnuWin324 project has almost every Linux command line program that runs natively on Windows.

Another new opportunity that has sprung up is to use the Windows Subsystem for Linux, a compatibility layer that runs Linux natively on top of the subsystem in Windows 10.

苹果电脑
Mac OSX

一种方法（尽管有多种）是使用 Emacs 的非官方版本。5还有Aquamacs，但它与 GNU Emacs 有很大不同。这个话题本身相当复杂。有些人喜欢使用像 homebrew 这样的包管理器，而另一些人则不喜欢。一般来说，使用 homebrew 的人也经常使用 Emacs 的 homebrew 版本。如果您想自己编译 Emacs ，EmacsWiki 的关于在 Mac OSX 上安装 Emacs 的文章6是一个很好的起点。

One approach (though there are several) is to use an unofficial build of Emacs.5 There is also Aquamacs but it differs from GNU Emacs quite a bit. The topic itself is rather complex. Some prefer using a package manager like homebrew and others do not. Generally, people who use homebrew often use the homebrew version of Emacs also. EmacsWiki’s article6 on installing Emacs on Mac OSX is a good place to start if you want to compile Emacs yourself.

Linux
Linux

Emacs 几乎总是出现在您的发行版的包管理器中。一些发行版更新到新的次要版本的速度很慢（很少是次要版本，添加了很多新功能和错误修复），因此可能值得您花时间从源代码构建。

在 Ubuntu 上，这就像Emacs 的主要版本apt-get install emacsNN在哪里一样简单： 、等等。NN2425

如果您想从源代码构建自己的 Emacs 版本，我建议您使用apt-get build-dep emacsNN构建和安装 Emacs 的依赖项。从那时起，就可以轻松地遵循构建说明中概述的常规配置、制作、安装过程。

Emacs is almost always present in your distribution’s package manager. Some distros are slow to update to new minor releases (which are rarely minor at all, adding a lot of new functionality and bug fixes) so it may be worth your while to build from source.

On Ubuntu, it’s as easy as apt-get install emacsNN where NN is the major version of Emacs: 24, 25, and so on.

If you want to build your own version of Emacs from source, I recommend you use apt-get build-dep emacsNN to build and install Emacs’s dependencies. From that point on it’s easy to follow the usual configure, make, make install procedure outlined in the build instructions.

启动 Emacs

Starting Emacs

启动 Emacs 就像emacs从命令行运行一样简单。如果您从窗口管理器运行该命令，则 Emacs 将作为 GUI Emacs 启动 — 与终端 Emacs 不同，终端 Emacs 在终端内运行。

Starting Emacs is as simple as running emacs from the command line. If you run the command from a window manager, then Emacs will launch as GUI Emacs — as opposed to Terminal Emacs where Emacs is running inside a terminal.

您可以通过给定参数 来强制 Emacs 在终端中运行，甚至在窗口管理器中运行，-nw如下所示：emacs -nw。

You can force Emacs to run in a terminal, even in a window manager, by giving it the argument -nw, like so: emacs -nw.

您可以将许多命令行开关传递给 Emacs，但您只需要四个即可开始：

There’s a host of command line switches you can pass to Emacs, but you only need four to get started:

转变 目的
--help 显示帮助
-nw 强制 Emacs 在终端模式下运行
-q 不加载初始化文件（例如init.el）
-Q 不加载站点范围的启动文件7，您的
初始化文件，也不是 X 资源

如果 Emacs 在启动时给出错误消息，您可以使用-q来阻止加载init 文件。如果这修复了错误，那么您的初始化文件已损坏，应该采取措施进行补救：恢复到旧版本，注释掉代码直到它起作用，或者寻求帮助。

If Emacs is giving you error messages when you start it, you can use -q to prevent your init file from loading. If that fixes the errors — then you have a broken init file and should take steps to remedy that: revert to an older version, comment out code until it works, or ask for help.

Emacs 二进制文件遵循通常的命令行约定：emacs [switches] [file1, file2, ...].

The Emacs binary follows the usual command line conventions: emacs [switches] [file1, file2, ...].

Emacs 的方式是保持其运行并在专用的 Emacs 实例中进行所有编辑。 Emacs 通常会比其他编辑器启动得慢（因为它有更多的软件包和功能），因为它是为长时间运行的会话而不是快速编辑而设计的。

The Emacs way is to keep it running and do all your editing in a dedicated Emacs instance. Emacs will typically start slower than other editors (as it has a lot more packages and features) as it’s designed for long-running sessions and not quick edits.

Emacs 客户端-服务器

Emacs Client-Server

那么，您如何处理在命令行中消磨时间但又必须编辑文件的情况呢？也许您正在从命令行编写电子邮件或编写提交消息 - 您希望使用 Emacs，并且最好是您已经运行的 Emacs 的同一实例。忽略 Emacs 对电子邮件和源代码控制系统都具有一流支持的事实，答案是 Emacs 的客户端-服务器模式。

So, how do you deal with situations where you’re whiling away at the command line but have to edit a file? Maybe you’re writing an email from the command line or writing a commit message — you’d want to use Emacs, and ideally the same instance of Emacs you already have running. The answer, ignoring the fact that Emacs has first-class support for both email and source control systems, is Emacs’s client-server mode.

笔记

客户端-服务器功能非常棒，但在您熟悉 Emacs 基础知识之前，我不会花太多时间使用它。

Note

The client-server functionality is fantastic, but I wouldn’t spend too much time playing around with it until you’re comfortable with Emacs basics.

Emacs 服务器模式的众多优点是：

The myriad advantages of Emacs’s server mode are:

持久会话
A persistent session

意味着 Emacs 将重复使用相同的会话，而不是每次都生成一个新的、不同的 Emacs 副本。

means Emacs will re-use the same session instead of spawning a new, distinct copy of Emacs every time.

它适用于$EDITOR
It works well with $EDITOR

通过在共享 Emacs 会话中打开文件并在会话结束时自动向调用程序发出信号。

by opening the files in your shared Emacs session and automatically signalling the calling program when the session finishes.

快速打开文件
Fast file opening

使用二进制文件从命令行emacsclient。 Emacs 客户端将连接到本地 Emacs 服务器实例并指示它打开文件。

from the command line using the emacsclient binary. The Emacs client will connect to the local Emacs server instance and instruct it to open the file.

有多种方法可以激活 Emacs 的客户端-服务器模式：

There are several ways of activating Emacs’s client-server mode:

M-x server-start在已运行的 Emacs 实例内启动服务器。当您键入此命令时，实例将变成服务器；本身没有视觉反馈表明它正在运行。当你退出这个 Emacs 实例时，它也会关闭服务器——所以如果你想要一个服务器守护进程，你需要下面的选项。

M-x server-start launches a server inside an already-running Emacs instance. The instance turns into a server when you type this; there’s no visual feedback, per se, that it’s running. When you exit this Emacs instance, it will shut down the server also — so if you want a server daemon you need the option below.

emacs --daemon将作为守护进程运行 Emacs。如上所述，它将调用server-start，但会立即将控制权返回到您的终端并在后台运行，等待客户端请求。

emacs --daemon will run Emacs as a daemon. It will call server-start, as above, but will return control to your terminal immediately and run in the background, waiting for client requests.

如果您的操作系统支持，Emacs 还附带对systemd 的本机支持。 Emacs 26 及更高版本可以通过运行命令自动配置systemdsystemctl --user enable emacs单元文件。 Emacs 的守护进程由systemd管理。

Emacs also ships with native support for systemd, if your operating system supports it. Emacs 26 and up can configure a systemd unit file automatically by running the command systemctl --user enable emacs. Emacs’s daemon is then managed by systemd.

如果您走服务器路线，则无法emacs再使用默认二进制文件。该二进制文件将仅生成独立实例。您必须使用类似名称的名称emacsclient来代替。将您的$EDITOR环境变量设置为emacsclient，从那时起一切就应该正常工作了。

If you go the server route, you cannot use the default emacs binary any more. That binary will spawn standalone instances only. You must use the similarly-named emacsclient instead. Set your $EDITOR environment variable to emacsclient and things should just work from then on.

该emacsclient二进制文件有自己的一组开关，您应该了解：

The emacsclient binary has its own set of switches you should know about:

转变 目的
--help 显示帮助。
-c 创建图形框架（如果 X 可用）
或终端帧（如果 X 不可用）。
-nw 创建一个终端框架。
-n 客户将立即返回，而不是
等待您保存更改。
如果您只想打开一堆文件，这很有用。

当您启动emacsclient实例时，客户端将等待文件完成编辑。按C-x #将切换到您正在通过客户端编辑的下一个缓冲区 — 当您对打开的文件执行此操作后，Emacs 将向客户端发出信号以退出并将控制权返回到终端。如果您使用的工具git允许您$EDITOR在使用其他编辑器时编辑提交消息，那么 git 将等待，直到收到编辑器的确认，表明它已将提交消息保存到临时文件中，然后再使用提交操作。

When you launch an emacsclient instance, the client will wait for the file(s) to finish editing. Pressing C-x # will switch to the next buffer you’re editing through a client — when you’ve done this for the file(s) you opened, Emacs will signal to the client to exit and return control to the terminal. If you’re using a tool like git that lets you use your $EDITOR to edit commit messages when using other editors, git will wait until it receives the go-ahead from your editor that it has saved the commit messages to a temporary file before resuming with the commit operation.

-n如果您希望客户端只打开文件而不等待，您可以添加开关。如果我正在进行探索性工作或者希望文件在 Emacs 中“永久”打开，我发现这很有用。

You can add the -n switch if you want the client to just open the files and not wait. I find this useful if I’m doing exploratory work or if I want the files “permanently” open in Emacs.

Emacs 界面

The Emacs Interface

当您第一次启动 Emacs 时，您会看到启动画面。它可能是大多数 Emacs 黑客首先禁用的东西之一，其他还有滚动条、菜单和工具栏。在您熟悉 Emacs 之前，我建议您启用 UI 元素，因为它们将为您提供一种快速访问常用功能的方法，尽管它们占用了您宝贵的空间，但您可能不记得如何立即执行这些功能。屏幕。

When you first launch Emacs, you’re greeted with the splash screen. It’s probably one of the first things most Emacs hackers disable, along with the scroll bars, the menu and tool bar. Until you’re comfortable with Emacs I would recommend you leave the UI elements enabled since they will provide you with a quick way to access common functionality that you may not remember how to do off-hand, although they take up valuable real estate on your screen.

如果您在终端中使用 Emacs，您仍然可以通过按 访问菜单栏F10。

If you’re using Emacs in the Terminal, you can still access the menu bar by pressing F10.

如果您没有看到与上图类似的用户界面，很可能是由于对初始化文件进行了自定义。测试这一点的最快方法是关闭 Emacs 并使用 重新启动它emacs -q。如果这能解决问题，那么肯定是对您的 Emacs 进行了自定义。大多数入门工具包假设您相当熟悉 Emacs，并且它们经常禁用菜单栏和工具栏等功能。

If you don’t see a user interface similar to the figure above, it’s most likely due to customizations made to your init file. The quickest way to test this is to close Emacs and restart it with emacs -q. If that fixes things, then it’s definitely customizations made to your Emacs. Most starter kits assume you’re reasonably familiar with Emacs and they often disable things like the menu bar and tool bar.

现在您实际上可以自由地使用 Emacs：箭头键可以正常工作，并且与菜单栏结合使用，您可以打开和保存文件。 Emacs 将自动检测大多数文件类型并对其应用正确的主要模式- 如果没有，您可能需要安装第三方软件包，我将在稍后讨论。

You are actually free to play around with Emacs now: the arrows keys will work fine and, combined with the menu bar, you can open and save files. Emacs will auto-detect most file types and apply the correct major mode to it — if it doesn’t, you may have to install third-party packages, which I will talk about later.

按键

Keys

Emacs 中最重要的主题。 Emacs 因两件事而闻名：它晦涩难懂的键盘咒语，以及它是无所不能的厨房水槽编辑器。漫画 xkcd 8幽默地引用了 Emacs 传说的这一部分。一个更古老的笑话是 Emacs 代表“Escape Meta Alt Control Shift”。

The most important subject in Emacs. Emacs is famous for two things: its obscure keyboard incantations and that it’s the kitchen sink editor that can do everything. The comic strip xkcd8 humorously referenced that part of Emacs lore. A much older joke is that Emacs stands for “Escape Meta Alt Control Shift.”

然而，键修饰符是 Emacs 日常使用的重要组成部分，因此能够“解码”一串键非常重要。

Nevertheless, key modifiers are a big part of day-to-day Emacs use so being able to “decode” a string of keys is important.

在 Emacs 中，您可以使用多个修饰键，每个修饰键都有自己的字符：

In Emacs, there are several modifier keys you can use, each with its own character:

修饰符 全名
C- 控制
M- 元（大多数键盘上的“Alt”）
S- 转移

由于历史原因还存在另外两个（Super 和 Hyper），但在当今的键盘上没有专用键，但为了与 Space Cadet 键盘保持一致，内部仍存在9 个键盘；另一个键 (Alt)确实存在于现代键盘上，但在 Emacs 中被绑定（并被称为 Meta）：

Two more exist for historical reasons (Super and Hyper) but don’t have dedicated keys on today’s keyboards, but for consistency with Space Cadet keyboards9 still exist internally; another key (Alt) does exist on modern keyboards but is bound (and known by) as Meta in Emacs:

修饰符 全名
s- 超级（不是移位！）
H- 超
A- Alt（多余且未使用）

Super 和 Hyper 仍然可以使用，如果您拥有带有“开始”和“应用程序上下文”按钮的 Microsoft Windows 兼容 PC 键盘，您可以将它们重新绑定为 Super 和 Hyper，这非常有用。 Emacs 本身支持修饰符，但您需要告诉操作系统或窗口管理器来绑定它们。

Super and Hyper can still be used, and if you’re the owner of a Microsoft Windows-compatible PC keyboard with the Start and Application Context buttons, you can rebind them to serve as Super and Hyper which is very useful. Emacs supports the modifiers natively but you need to tell your operating system or window manager to bind them.

重要的

由于终端的限制，如果您在终端中运行 Emacs，则有些键绑定您根本无法键入。我的建议是，如果可能的话，在 GUI 中运行 Emacs。

Important

Owing to the limitations of terminals, there are some key bindings you simply cannot type if you’re running Emacs in a terminal. My advice is to run Emacs in a GUI, if at all possible.

不过，了解修饰符只是等式的一半。

Knowing the modifiers is only one half of the equation though.

在 Emacs 中，我们正式定义一个键序列（或只是键）来表示一系列键盘（或鼠标）操作序列，以及一个完整的键来表示调用命令的一个或多个键盘序列；如果键序列不是完整的键，则您有一个前缀 key。如果 Emacs 根本无法识别该键序列，则该键序列无效，并且会在回显区域中显示错误。

In Emacs, we formally define a key sequence (or just key) to mean a sequence of keyboard (or mouse) actions and a complete key to mean one or more keyboard sequences that invoke a command; if the sequence of keys is not a complete key, then you have a prefix key. And if the key sequence is not recognized by Emacs at all it is invalid, and an error is displayed in the echo area.

这是一个相当枯燥的定义，所以让我们看几个例子。

That’s a rather dry definition, so let’s look at a few examples.

C-d
C-d

调用名为 的命令delete-char。要调用它，请按住control并按d。由于该键是一个完整的键，因此它会调用该命令delete-char并立即删除该点旁边的字符。

calls a command named delete-char. To invoke it, hold down control and press d. As the key is a complete key, it will call the command delete-char and immediately delete the character next to point.

C-M-d
C-M-d

与上面的示例类似，但这次您必须同时按住control和 ，meta然后再按d。

is similar to the example above, but this time you must hold down both control and meta before you press d.

让我们尝试一些前缀键。前缀键基本上是细分——一种对键进行分组并增加可能的键组合数量的方法。例如，前缀键C-x有几十个与其绑定的键。C-x是您将一直使用的前缀键。

Let’s try a few prefix keys. Prefix keys are basically subdivisions — a way of grouping keys and increasing the number of possible key combinations. For instance, the prefix key C-x has several dozen keys bound to it. C-x is a prefix key you will use all the time.

C-x C-f
C-x C-f

在 Emacs 中运行一个名为 的命令find-file。解释的方法是先按住control，然后按下再松开x。在您的回显区域中，Emacs 将在大约一秒的短暂空闲时间后显示C-x-（末尾带有破折号），这是 Emacs 告诉您它需要其他键的方式。最后，键入C-f您现在应该很容易执行的操作：按住control并按f。

要打字C-x C-f，您不必control在每个键之间释放按键 - 按住control可以帮助您保持我称之为节奏的东西，我将在稍后讨论。

in Emacs runs a command called find-file. The way to interpret it is to first hold down control and then press and release x. In your echo area, Emacs will display – after a small idle period of about a second – C-x- (with a dash at the end) which is Emacs’s way of telling you that it expects additional keys. Finally, type C-f which should be easy for you to do now: hold down control and press f.

To type C-x C-f, you don’t have to release the control key between each key — keeping control pressed helps you maintain something I call tempo, which I will talk about later.

C-x 8 P
C-x 8 P

有两个前缀键：firstC-x和then 8，它是 的子类别C-x。所以8它本身不会做任何事情（它只会打印数字8），也不会C-x甚至C-x 8- 两者仍然是前缀键。只有当您完成后，密钥才完整P。

我们将属于特定前缀键的键集称为键映射，这就是 Emacs 在内部跟踪键和命令之间映射的方式。在这种情况下，键映射C-x 8具有用于书写或数学的各种实用字符，但在大多数键盘上不受限制。例如，C-x 8 P将插入段落符号¶。

has two prefix keys: first C-x and then 8, which is a subcategory to C-x. So 8 on its own wouldn’t do anything (it would just print the number 8) nor would C-x or even C-x 8 — both are still prefix keys. The key is complete only when you finish with P.

We call sets of keys that belong to a particular prefix key key maps, which is how Emacs internally tracks the mapping between a key and a command. In this case, the key map C-x 8 has a variety of utility characters used in writing or mathematics but not bound on most keyboards. For instance, C-x 8 P will insert the paragraph symbol ¶.

C-M-%
C-M-%

对于初学者来说是一个棘手的问题。使用您在上面学到的知识，按住control和alt（正如您从上表中记住的那样，Meta 是 Alt）但也按住 shift。该%字符通常与键盘数字范围上的数字共享，这意味着您还必须键入 shift。

如果您不按 Shift 键，那么您实际上是在打字C-M-5（无论如何，在美国键盘上）。

值得一提的是，这个特定的键绑定到一个流行的命令 ( )，并且是由于终端的技术限制（而不是 Emacs）而无法在终端 Emacs 中键入的M-x query-replace-regexp键的示例。

is a tricky one for beginners. Using what you’ve learned above, hold down control and alt (and as you’ll remember from the table above, Meta is Alt) but also shift. The % character is typically shared with a number on the keyboard number range and the implication here is you must type shift also.

If you don’t press shift, you’re actually typing C-M-5 (on a US keyboard, anyway.)

It bears mentioning that this particular key is bound to a popular command (M-x query-replace-regexp) and is an example of a key that you cannot type in Terminal Emacs because of the terminal’s technical limitations (and not Emacs.)

TAB，F1-F12等等
TAB, F1–F12 and so on

偶尔会这样写，但也用尖括号括起来：<tab>, <f1>。重要的是不要TAB与角色混淆T A B。我将仅使用前一种表示法以避免歧义。

are occasionally written like this, but also in angle brackets: <tab>, <f1>. It’s important you don’t confuse TAB with the characters T A B. I will only use the former notation to avoid ambiguities.

暗示

如果您遇到困难，或者万一 Emacs 停止运行，或者您输入了想要取消的部分命令，请按C-g。这是 Emacs 中通用的“保释我”命令。

Hint

If you’re stuck, or in the unlikely event Emacs has seized up, or if you have typed in a partial command that you want to cancel — press C-g. That’s the universal “bail me out” command in Emacs.

大写锁定作为控制

Caps Lock as Control

您应该对环境进行的最重要的修改之一是将大写锁定键重新绑定到control。您将经常使用控制键，为了避免Emacs 小指，我建议您完全解除右侧控制键的绑定，而使用大写锁定。

One of the most important modifications you should make to your environment is rebinding your caps lock key to control. You’re going to use the control key a lot and to avoid the Emacs pinky I suggest you unbind your right control entirely and instead use caps lock.

是的，这将是一个烦人的过渡，但却是一个值得的过渡（顺便说一句，这将在 Emacs 之外为您提供良好的服务。）这一更改是必要的，因为在较旧的键盘10上，控制键占据了现在由大写锁定键使用的空间，因此可以在不拉紧左小指的情况下到达左控制键。

Yes, it’ll be an annoying transition but a worthwhile one (that will, incidentally, serve you well outside of Emacs.) This change is necessary because on older keyboards10 the control key occupied the space now used by the caps lock key so reaching the left control key could be done without straining your left pinky.

在 Windows 上，我建议您使用 SharpKeys。11在 Ubuntu 和 Mac OSX 上，它是内置的；转到键盘设置并更改它。如果您使用的是其他 Linux 发行版，您可能需要摆弄xmodmap.

On Windows, I recommend you use SharpKeys.11 On Ubuntu and Mac OSX, it’s built-in; go to the Keyboard settings and change it. If you’re using another Linux distribution you may have to fiddle with xmodmap.

M-x：执行扩展命令

M-x: Execute Extended Command

Emacs 中只有一小部分可用命令绑定到实际的键。大多数不是：它们很少被使用，并且不保证键绑定；或者您可能已显式覆盖了它所绑定的密钥，使其未绑定；或者您可能忘记了它的键绑定。

Only a small portion of available commands in Emacs are bound to actual keys. Most are not: they are rarely used, and do not warrant a key binding; or maybe you have explicitly overridden the key it was bound to, leaving it unbound; or perhaps you forgot its key binding.

本质上，您通常希望运行很少使用的命令。要执行此操作，请按M-x（发音为mex、M x或meta x）。在您的迷你缓冲区中，将出现一个提示，您可以自由输入要运行的命令的名称。

In essence, it’s common that you want to run seldom-used commands. To do this press M-x (pronounced mex, M x, or meta x.) In your minibuffer, a prompt will appear and you are free to input the name of a command you wish to run.

当 Emacs 用户说“跑去M-x lunar-phases看看月亮的月相”之类的话时，他们所说的是：按住meta并按下x，提示M-x将出现在您的迷你缓冲区中（这是 Emacs 最底部的一行。）

When Emacs users say something like “run M-x lunar-phases to see the lunar phases of the moon” what they’re saying is: hold down meta and press x and the M-x prompt will appear in your minibuffer (that’s the line at the very bottom of Emacs.)

此时您可以输入命令的名称。尝试一下，输入lunar-phases并按RET。该lunar-phases命令将在屏幕上打开一个新窗口，显示从今天开始的月相。您可以键入C-x 1来隐藏缓冲区。

At this point you can type in the name of the command. Try it, enter lunar-phases and press RET. The lunar-phases command will open a new window on your screen displaying the lunar phases from today onward. You can type C-x 1 to hide the buffer.

暗示

如果您输入M-x错误，请记住您可以C-g再次输入退出。

Hint

If you enter M-x by mistake, remember you can type C-g to exit out again.

Emacs 具有内置的自动完成支持，因此按下TAB将打开一个新窗口并列出所有潜在的候选者。当您键入并按 时TAB，Emacs 将自动缩小候选列表的范围。如果您按 时，部分输入的匹配项只剩下一名候选者TAB，Emacs 将为您补全整个名称。您也可以按RET— 它会像这样完成，TAB但如果它是唯一剩下的候选者，则还有运行命令的额外好处。

Emacs has built-in auto completion support so pressing TAB will open a new window and list all the potential candidates. As you type and press TAB, Emacs will automatically narrow the list of candidates. If your partially-typed match only has one candidate left when you press TAB, Emacs will complete the whole name for you. You can also just press RET — it completes like TAB but with the added benefit of running the command if it’s the only candidate left.

您可能认为M-x这是一个特殊的 Emacs 命令，但实际上并非如此。它也是用 elisp 编写的，并且像其他东西一样绑定到一个键。

You may think M-x is a special Emacs command but it’s actually not. It, too, is written in elisp and bound to a key just like everything else.

命令和功能

当我谈论命令时，我谈论的是用户可以访问的一种功能。

对于用户可以访问的函数（尽管能够计算 elisp 中的任何表达式），它必须是交互式的，这是一个 Emacs 术语，指的是具有与其关联的附加属性的函数，通过执行扩展命令使其可用（M-x）接口和按键绑定。

因此，如果您是包作者，则必须选择最终用户是否可以通过M-x界面访问特定功能。将其标记为交互式将使最终用户可以访问它。

换句话说，如果它不是交互式的，您就无法运行它，M-x也无法将它绑定到键。

Commands and functions

When I talk about commands, I’m talking about a type of function that is accessible to the user.

For a function to be accessible to a user (notwithstanding the ability to evaluate any expression in elisp) it must be interactive, which is an Emacs term for a function that has additional properties associated with it, rendering it usable through the execute extended command (M-x) interface and key bindings.

So if you’re a package author, you have to choose if a particular function is accessible to the end-user through the M-x interface. Marking it as interactive will make it accessible to end users.

In other words, if it’s not interactive, you cannot run it from M-x nor can you bind it to a key.

普遍论点

Universal Arguments

某些命令具有备用状态，要访问它们，您需要为它们提供通用参数（也称为前缀参数）。通用参数也可通过其键绑定来识别C-u。当您为另一个键绑定添加前缀时（M-x顺便说一下，这也包括在内），您就是在告诉 Emacs 修改该命令的功能。接下来发生的情况将取决于您调用的命令：有些命令具有零个、一个甚至多个通用参数状态。如果命令有N 个状态，您只需键入C-u最多N次。

Some commands have alternate states, and to access them you need to give them a universal argument (also called a prefix argument.) The universal argument is also known by its key binding C-u. When you prefix another key binding (this includes M-x by the way), you’re telling Emacs to modify the functionality of that command. What happens next will depend on the command you’re invoking: some have zero, one or even more universal argument states. If a command has N states, you simply type C-u up to N times.

通用参数是数字 4 的简写。如果您键入C-u a，Emacs 将aaaa在屏幕上打印。如果您输入C-u C-u a，Emacs 将显示 16 个字符（因为 4 乘以 4 等于 16）。请记住，普遍论证本身是完全无效的。当您键入它们时，Emacs 会像前缀键一样等待，直到您给它一个后续命令 — 然后 Emacs 才会应用通用参数。

The universal argument is shorthand for the number 4. If you type C-u a, Emacs will print aaaa on your screen. If you type C-u C-u a, Emacs will display 16 characters (because 4 times 4 equals 16). Keep in mind that universal arguments on their own are totally inactive. When you type them, Emacs will, much like a prefix key, wait until you give it a follow-up command — and only then will Emacs apply the universal arguments.

了解 Emacs 的命令状态仅仅是数字是一件很容易知道的事情，因为您还可以将任意数字传递给命令。许多 Emacs 黑客会编写C-u 10 a打印 10 个字符，但还有一种更简单的方法。

Understanding that Emacs’s command states are merely numbers is a handy thing to know because you can also pass arbitrary numbers to commands. A lot of Emacs hackers would write C-u 10 a to print 10 characters, but there’s a much easier way.

顺便一提

当您按下某个键（例如键盘上的a按钮）时，Emacs 如何将其写在屏幕上？事实上，有一个特殊的命令self-insert-command，调用该命令时，将插入最后键入的键。使用此命令可以增加按键和命令的对称性：它使常规键盘字符的行为方式与 Emacs 中的所有其他命令完全相同。

这也意味着键盘字符，因此self-insert-command，受到与所有其他命令完全相同的规则的约束。它们可以由您解除绑定、反弹或以其他方式修改。

By the way

When you press a key – say the a button on your keyboard – how does Emacs write it on your screen? The truth is there’s a special command called self-insert-command that, when invoked, will insert the last typed key. Having this command adds symmetry to keys and commands: it makes your regular keyboard characters behave in exactly the same way as all other commands in Emacs.

And that also means keyboard characters, and hence self-insert-command, are subject to the exact same rules as all other commands. They can be unbound, rebound, and otherwise modified by you.

绑定到键绑定C-0的C-9是数字参数。但它们不仅仅需要靠那排按键来维持我个人所说的打字节奏——而且更多的是关于下面的节奏。

Bound to key binding C-0 to C-9 are the digit arguments. But they’re bound to more than just that row of keys to maintain what I personally call the tempo of typing — but more on tempo below.

以下是将数字参数传递给命令的各种方法。

Here are the various ways you can pass digit arguments to a command.

按键绑定 笔记
C-u 数字参数4
C-u C-u 数字参数16
C-u C-u … 数字参数4^n
M-0 到 M-9 数字参数0到9
C-0 到 C-9 数字参数0到9
C-M-0 到 C-M-9 数字参数0到9
C-- 否定论点
M-- 否定论点
C-M-- 否定论点

笔记

负参数命令绑定到减号键 ( -)，尽管从上表中很难看出。

它们被写为C--而不是 ，C- -因为后者是无效的 Emacs 键：您不能按修饰键 ，C-释放它，然后按-。那只会打印-在您的屏幕上。减号本身与多个修饰符绑定。空白很重要。

Note

The negative argument commands are bound to the minus key (-) even though it’s hard to make out from the table above.

They’re written as C-- instead of C- - because the latter is an invalid Emacs key: you cannot press a modifier key, C-, release it, and then press -. That would just print - on your screen. It’s the minus itself that is bound to several modifiers. White space matters.

所以我提到了节奏的重要性。一旦您熟悉了 Emacs，您就会在屏幕上飞翔，并且无需将手指从修饰符上移开即可应用负数或数字参数，这将帮助您做到这一点。确保数字和负参数绑定到修饰符C-、M-、 和C-M-，这三个非常常见的修饰符组合，几乎可以保证您在执行预期命令之前无需将手指从修饰符上移开。

So I mentioned the importance of tempo. Once you’re comfortable with Emacs, you’ll be flying across the screen, and not having to take your fingers off the modifiers to apply a negative or digit argument will help you do that. Ensuring the digits and negative arguments are bound to the modifiers C-, M-, and C-M-, three very common modifier combinations, all but guarantees you won’t have to move your fingers from the modifiers before you follow them up with your intended command.

以下是我的意思的几个例子。

Here are a few examples of what I mean.

M-- M-d
M-- M-d

删除 point 之前的前一个单词。如果没有M--,M-d将会杀死紧接在点后面的单词。该命令与否定参数具有协同作用，因为您可以将手指放在元键上并按- d。

这种组合可以保持你的节奏。

kills the previous word before point. Without M--, M-d would kill the word immediately following point. The command has synergy with the negative argument because you can keep your finger on the meta key and press - d.

This combination maintains your tempo.

C-- M-d
C-- M-d

功能完全相同，但打字时间会增加大约三倍。您必须按下C--，松开控制键，然后M-按下d。

这种组合会打破你的节奏。

does exactly the same but it will take you about thrice as long to type. You have to press C--, release the control key, and then press M- followed by d.

This combination breaks your tempo.

很多人从不费心将数字和否定参数纳入他们的工作流程，但我发现它们非常有用。诸如更改我刚刚键入的单词的大小写之类的事情可以通过给命令一个否定参数来反转命令的方向来轻松完成。

A lot of people never bother working the digit and negative arguments into their workflow, but I find them immensely useful. Things like changing the casing on a word I just typed are easily done by reversing the direction of a command by giving it a negative argument.

保持你的节奏
Maintain your tempo

并避免将手指移离主行。12否定参数为命令添加方向性；数字增加重复或改变命令的工作方式。

and avoid moving your fingers away from the home row.12 Negative arguments add directionality to commands; digits add repetition or change how a command works.

发现并记住钥匙

Discovering and Remembering Keys

如果您不记得某件事的确切命令，那么 Emacs 可以提供帮助。假设您不记得如何打印段落字符¶，但您确实记得它位于C-x 8键映射中的某个位置，那么您所要做的就是附加C-h到任何前缀键以获取属于该键映射的所有绑定的列表。

If you can’t remember the exact command for something, then Emacs can help. Let’s say you can’t remember how to print the paragraph character ¶, but you do remember it’s somewhere in the C-x 8 key map, then all you have to do is append C-h to any prefix key to get a list of all bindings that belong to that key map.

键入C-x 8 C-h将显示计算机生成的按键及其命令的列表。该界面有超链接，并且是 Emacs 自文档帮助系统的一部分。

Typing C-x 8 C-h will display a computer-generated list of keys and their commands. This interface is hyperlinked and part of Emacs’s self-documenting help system.

钥匙 捆绑
C-x 8 " 前缀命令
C-x 8 < «
C-x 8 > »
C-x 8 ? ¿
C-x 8 C ©
C-x 8 L £
C-x 8 P ¶
C-x 8 R ®
C-x 8 S §
C-x 8 Y ¥

以上是您在请求 的帮助页面时看到的命令的子集C-x 8。如果您在“绑定”列中只看到一个字符，则意味着当您键入该键时它将打印该字符。

Above is a subset of the commands you see when you request the help page for C-x 8. If you see just a character in the Binding column, that means it’ll print the character when you type that key.

但是，Emacs 还会告诉您是否有更多带有更多子级别的前缀键；在这种情况下，C-x 8 "有附加的键绑定到它。

However, Emacs will also tell you if there are more prefix keys with further sub-levels; in this case, C-x 8 " has additional keys bound to it.

所有这些键都隐藏在 Emacs 的尘埃深处，所有这些键都随意地绑定到所有可以想象的键盘字符排列，这可能看起来很奇怪，特别是如果您来自像 Vim 这样的模态编辑器。

All these keys, hidden away in the dusty depths of Emacs, all haphazardly bound to all conceivable permutations of keyboard characters, may seem like a strange thing particularly if you come from modal editors like Vim.

Super、Hyper 和 Meta 等名称明显体现了 80 年代早期使用的特定键盘的传统。

The legacy of a particular keyboard used in the early ’80s is evident in the names Super, Hyper, and Meta.

当时，大多数 Emacs 键都绑定到更大范围的物理键盘修改器，但当键盘制造商（以及制造键盘插入的机器的企业）破产时，Emacs 必须与时俱进。开发人员并没有毁掉 Emacs 的基石，而是对按键进行了重新调整，让它们可以在普通、无聊的 PC 键盘上工作。

Back then, most Emacs keys were bound to a larger range of physical keyboard modifiers but when the keyboard maker (and the business that made the machines the keyboards were plugged into) went bust, Emacs had to change with the times. Instead of undoing the cornerstone of Emacs, the developers shuffled the keys around and made them work on normal, boring PC keyboards.

因此，您可能认为记住所有这些按键确实是一项艰巨的任务 - 但您不必这样做。我会记住我经常使用的内容（就像我们习惯用人类大脑做的那样），然后让 Emacs 帮我记住其余的内容。

So you’re probably thinking it’s a daunting task indeed to memorize all those keys — but you don’t have to. I memorize what I use frequently (as we are wont to do with our human brains) and leave the rest for Emacs to remember for me.

使用 Emacs 的帮助系统
Use Emacs’s help system

如果您忘记了特定的组合键。您始终可以附加C-h到前缀键。

if you forget a particular key combination. You can always append C-h to a prefix key.

配置 Emacs

Configuring Emacs

修补 Emacs 是每个 Emacs 黑客最喜欢的消遣。参加 Emacs 聚会或与经验丰富的 Emacs 黑客交谈，谈话将不可避免地转向他们为了让生活更轻松而做出的小改动和黑客攻击。

Tinkering with Emacs is every Emacs hacker’s favorite pastime. Go to Emacs meetups or talk to experienced Emacs hackers and the conversation will inevitably drift towards small changes and hacks they’ve made to make their lives easier.

知道如果您不喜欢编辑器行为的某个方面，您可以简单地更改它，这很有趣（而且很有价值）——事实上，关于更改 Emacs 的主题可以写一整本书。

It’s fun (and rewarding) knowing that, if there’s an aspect of your editor’s behavior that you don’t like that you can simply change it — indeed, a whole book could be written on the subject of changing Emacs.

在本书中，我将提出一些需要改变的建议。如果可能，我将使用自定义界面，而不是建议 elisp 片段的典型方法。

Throughout this book I will make suggestions of things to change. Where possible I will use the Customize interface instead of the typical approach of suggesting elisp snippets.

如果你想改变Emacs，你有两个选择：

If you want to change Emacs, you have two choices:

使用自定义界面
Use the Customize interface

因为它是内置的并且设计为用户友好的。我这么说，但很多人觉得它很麻烦，很难用。我认为这有点不公平：它很实用，并且必须支持许多任意方式来配置相当复杂的功能。

并非所有内容都受自定义支持。由于您需要编写 elisp 来更改变量，并且由于 LISP 使用数据即代码范式，因此您会发现 Customize 可以编写已显示如何编写的 elisp，然后仅针对特定选项。这使得在 Emacs 的所有设置中通用一个界面实际上是不可能的。但是大多数 Emacs 的内置软件包都支持自定义接口，并且许多第三方软件包也支持。

我强烈建议您尽可能使用自定义界面，直到您能够轻松编写 elisp。

as it’s built-in and designed to be user friendly. I say that, but a lot of people find it cumbersome and hard to use. I think that’s a bit unfair: it’s utilitarian and has to support a lot of arbitrary ways of configuring fairly complicated features.

Not everything is supported by Customize. Since you need to write elisp to change variables, and because of the data-as-code paradigm LISP uses, you will find that Customize can write elisp that it’s been shown how to write, and then only for specific options. That makes it a virtual impossibility to generalize an interface across all of Emacs’s many, many settings. But most of Emacs’s built-in packages support the Customize interface and a lot of third-party packages do too.

I would strongly recommend you use the Customize interface, where possible, until you’re comfortable writing elisp.

编写省略号
Write elisp

更改您想要自定义的内容。这是最强大的选项，但也是最复杂的。你必须学习 elisp（它并不太难，而且编写它通常很有趣）才能做到这一点，但我认为，从长远来看，这是值得做的。

当我更改字体时，我自己仍然使用自定义界面。 Emacs 中有数百种字体；从字体锁定面（语法突出显示）到模型行的颜色、信息手册使用的字体等等。

to alter what you want to customize. This is the most powerful option but also the most complicated. You’ll have to learn elisp (it’s not too hard, and writing it is usually a lot of fun) to do this, but I think, in the long run, it’s worth doing.

I still use the Customize interface myself when I change font faces. There are hundreds of font faces in Emacs; everything from font lock faces (syntax highlighting) to the color of the modeline, the fonts to use for the info manual, and more.

自定义界面

The Customize Interface

自定义界面分为组和子组。每个组通常代表一个包、模式或一项功能。顶级组称为Emacs，并且如您所料，包含所有其他组。

The Customize interface is divided into groups and sub groups. Each group typically represents one package, mode, or piece of functionality. The top-level group is called Emacs and contains, as you would expect, all other groups.

要访问自定义界面，请键入M-x customize。调用的缓冲区*Customize Group: Emacs*应该与组列表一起出现。这是 Emacs 中使用鼠标的一大优势；该界面有按钮、超链接和编辑框，就像浏览器一样。单击周围 - 探索界面，并惊叹于有多少东西需要配置！这只是向自定义界面公开的内容。

To access the customize interface, type M-x customize. A buffer called *Customize Group: Emacs* should appear with a list of groups. This is one part of Emacs where using a mouse can be beneficial; the interface has buttons, hyperlinks and edit boxes much like a browser would. Click around — explore the interface, and marvel at just how much stuff there is to configure! And that’s just the things exposed to the Customize interface.

在自定义中搜索

Searching in Customize

如果您使用的是 Emacs 24.1 或更高版本，则可以使用自定义界面顶部的搜索栏按名称搜索内容。

If you’re using Emacs 24.1 or later, you can use the Search bar at the top of the Customize interface to search for things by name.

自定义界面相当复杂，但是一旦您了解了它的工作原理，它就非常容易使用。上图显示了一张脸：font-lock-string-face。这是该面的实际 elisp 变量名称；打印漂亮的名称是Font Lock String Face，您将在上图中看到它。左边是一个箭头——它很小，但它会隐藏/显示每张脸。在终端上，它被替换为可以说更易读的文本Hide或Show。

The Customize interface is rather byzantine but once you understand how it works, it’s quite easy to use. The figure above shows one face: font-lock-string-face. That’s the actual elisp variable name for the face; the pretty-printed name is Font Lock String Face and what you’ll see in the figure above. To the immediate left is an arrow — it’s tiny but it’ll hide/show each face. On a Terminal, it’s replaced with the arguably more legible texts Hide or Show.

顺便说一句，自定义界面由两部分组成：面孔和选项。选项是一个包罗万象的术语，指的是您可以自定义的除面孔之外的事物。

As a quick aside, the Customize interface is made up of two things: faces and options. Options are a catch-all term for things you can Customize that aren’t faces.

控制font-lock-string-face字符串的外观——字符串是什么取决于它的使用模式。对于大多数编程主要模式，它将用于源代码中的实际文字字符串，但模式作者可以随意使用字体。话虽如此，大多数人都遵守每张脸的命名标准。

The font-lock-string-face governs the face for strings — and what a string is depends on the mode in which it is used. For most programming major modes, it’ll be for actual literal strings in the source code, but mode authors are free to use the font faces for whatever they please. Having said that, most adhere to the naming standard for each face.

我个人的前景脸部颜色是OrangeRed。但没有什么可以阻止我添加额外的属性，如上图所示。

My personal foreground face color is OrangeRed. But there’s nothing stopping me from adding additional attributes as the figure above shows.

支持的颜色

如果您在 GUI 中使用 Emacs，则仅受显示颜色深度的限制，并且可以自由地从 RGB 颜色空间中选择任何颜色。我使用命名颜色，要查看支持的名称列表，您可以键入M-x list-colors-display。如果您使用的是终端，您将看到终端支持的颜色。

从 Emacs 26 开始，除了通常的 16 或 256 之外，终端还支持 24 位颜色。如果您没有看到您期望看到的颜色，您应该阅读有关如何配置终端的信息手册常见问题解答:

键入M-x info-apropos然后输入Colors on a TTY。过了一会儿，您应该会看到一个常见问题解答的超链接，其中解释了如何配置您的终端设置。

Supported colors

If you’re using Emacs in a GUI, you are limited only by the color depth of the display and you are free to pick any color from the RGB color space. I use named colors, and to see a list of supported names you can type M-x list-colors-display. If you’re on a Terminal, you will be shown the colors supported by your Terminal.

As of Emacs 26, 24-bit colors are also supported in the Terminal in addition to the usual 16 or 256. If you’re not seeing the colors you expect to see, you should read the Info manual FAQ on how to configure your Terminal:

Type M-x info-apropos then enter Colors on a TTY. After a little while you should be presented with a hyperlink to the FAQ that explains how to configure your Terminal settings.

仅在自定义 UI 中进行更改是不够的。您必须应用更改并选择保存它们。如果您不保存它们，则更改将不会在 Emacs 会话之间保留。按恰当命名的“应用”和“应用并保存”即可完成此操作。 “恢复...”按钮类似，但有更多选项。仅当您对所应用的更改不满意时，才需要恢复此会话的自定义。请记住，它只会恢复当前缓冲区中的选项，而不是全局进行的所有自定义。

Making the changes in the Customize UI isn’t enough. You have to apply the changes and optionally save them also. If you don’t save them, the changes will not persist between Emacs sessions. Pressing the aptly named Apply and Apply and Save do just that. The Revert… button is similar but has a few more options. You only need Revert This Session’s Customizations if you’re unhappy with the changes you have applied. Keep in mind it will only revert the options you have in the current buffer — not all the customizations made globally.

请记住，在保存之前您可以恢复更改。之后，您必须手动执行并撤消或使用“恢复...”按钮的“擦除自定义”选项。

Always remember that you can revert your changes until you save. After that, you have to manually go through and undo or use the Revert… button’s Erase Customizations option.

默认情况下，所有自定义都存储在您的 init 文件中（或者可能是单独的自定义文件），并且与 Emacs 的其余部分一样，更改存储为 elisp 代码，使您可以返回并手动更改 elisp。

All Customizations are stored in your init file by default (or possibly a separate custom file) and like the rest of Emacs the changes are stored as elisp code, making it possible for you to go back and manually change the elisp.

您可以使用以下几个快捷命令之一，而不是在组树中导航：

Instead of navigating through the tree of groups, you can use one of several shortcut commands:

M-x customize
M-x customize

显示自定义界面和所有组。

displays the Customize interface and all the groups.

M-x customize-browse
M-x customize-browse

打开树组浏览器。与常规自定义界面非常相似，但没有组描述。

opens a tree group browser. Much like the regular Customize interface but without the group descriptions.

M-x customize-customized
M-x customize-customized

自定义您已更改但未保存的选项和面孔。如果你想调整一些东西的话很有用。

customizes options and faces that you have changed but not saved. Useful if you want to tweak things.

M-x customize-changed
M-x customize-changed

显示自特定 Emacs 版本以来更改的所有选项。发现新功能和选项的好方法。

displays all options changed since a particular Emacs version. Good way to discover new features and options.

M-x customize-face
M-x customize-face

提示输入要自定义的面孔名称。我建议你把你的观点写在你想改变的脸上。它会自动填写名称。

prompts for the name of a face to Customize. I recommend you put your point on the face you want to change. It’ll fill in the name automatically.

M-x customize-group
M-x customize-group

提示输入组名称（例如python）以进行自定义。

prompts for a group name (e.g., python) to Customize.

M-x customize-mode
M-x customize-mode

自定义当前缓冲区的主要模式。您应该为您使用的每个主要模式执行此操作。这是一种快速更改事物并概述主要模式功能的方法。

customizes the major mode of your current buffer. You should do this for every major mode you use. It’s a quick way to change things and gain an overview of what your major mode can do.

M-x customize-saved
M-x customize-saved

显示所有保存的选项和面孔。如果您想追踪并禁用错误的更改，则非常方便。

Displays all your saved options and faces. Extremely handy if you want to track down and disable errant changes.

M-x customize-themes
M-x customize-themes

显示您可以切换到的已安装主题的列表。

Shows a list of installed themes you can switch to.

我鼓励您使用自定义界面来配置 Emacs。它只有一部分您可以（或想要）更改的内容，但足以让您开始个性化 Emacs 之路。

I encourage you to use the Customize interface to configure Emacs. It only has a subset of things you can (or want) to change, but it’s enough to get you started on the road to personalizing Emacs.

当您继续使用和个性化 Emacs 时，您最终可能会达到初始化文件无法管理的地步。发生这种情况时，通常会将更改分成相关更改组。然而，在您熟悉 Emacs（并且您的初始化文件在接缝处分裂）之前，这是一个低优先级的任务。

As you continue to use and personalize Emacs you may eventually reach a point where your init file is unmanageable. When that happens it’s common to split up your changes into groups of related changes. However, this is a low priority task until you’re comfortable (and your init file splitting at the seams) with Emacs.

评估 Elisp 代码

Evaluating Elisp Code

通常，您会在 Internet 上找到或编写 elisp 代码片段，并且想要对其进行评估 — 每次关闭并重新启动 Emacs 是一件苦差事。

Frequently, you will find or write snippets of elisp code on the Internet and you’ll want to evaluate it — closing and restarting Emacs every time is a chore.

有多种不同的方法可以做到这一点，我只展示了一些可供您使用的不同方法。您可以阅读Evaluating Elisp in Emacs 13来深入研究该主题。

There are a number of different ways of doing this and I have only shown a few of the different methods available to you. You can read Evaluating Elisp in Emacs13 for a thorough study of the subject.

重新启动 Emacs
Restarting Emacs

是最简单的方法，如果您在 Emacs 中损坏了某些内容或者想确保其在新环境中正常运行，我建议您使用该方法。

is the simplest way, which I recommend if you have broken something in Emacs or if you want to be sure things work in a fresh environment.

M-x eval-buffer
M-x eval-buffer

将评估您所在的整个缓冲区。这就是我用来评估某些内容的方法。

will evaluate the entire buffer you’re in. This is what I use to evaluate something.

M-x eval-region
M-x eval-region

仅评估您标记的区域。

evaluates just the region that you have marked.

重要的

Important

您必须记住，即使您告诉 Emacs 也不会重新计算所有内容。这是一个令人烦恼的实现细节，让人们感到困惑。有些东西，比如defvar表单defcustom，只能设置一次。因此，如果您评估缓冲区，更改 adefvar的默认值，然后重新评估它，它不会应用对 所做的更改defvar。强制改变的唯一方法是在每个表格中坚持你C-M-x的观点。defvardefcustom

如果您不明白我所说的确切含义，请不要担心。如果您在代码片段中看到这两种形式中的任何一种，则只需重新启动 Emacs 即可。

You must remember that not all things will be re-evaluated even if you tell Emacs to. This is one annoying implementation detail that confuses people. Some things, like defvar and defcustom forms, are only set once. So, if you evaluate the buffer, change a defvar’s default value, then re-evaluate it, it won’t apply the changes made to defvar. The only way to force the change is to press C-M-x with your point in each defvar or defcustom form.

If you don’t know exactly what I mean by all of this then don’t worry. You can just restart Emacs if you see any of those two forms in your snippet.

当然，这只是使用 Emacs 评估 elisp 代码的皮毛。您不需要了解更多的知识来处理您看到并想要尝试的奇怪代码。不要害怕以这种方式探索 Emacs 的功能；阅读 Emacs 自己的 Elisp 简介手册。

Naturally, this is just scratching the surface in using Emacs to evaluate your elisp code. You shouldn’t need to know much more than this to deal with the odd bits of code you see and want to try out. Don’t be afraid to explore Emacs’s capabilities this way; read Emacs’s own Introduction to Elisp manual.

包管理器

The Package Manager

从版本 24 开始，Emacs 附带了一个包管理器，可以无缝地显示和安装集中存储库中的包。我相信这一变化以及 Github 等网站使 Emacs 的第 3 方生态系统以及 Emacs 本身焕发了活力。

Since version 24, Emacs has shipped with a package manager that seamlessly displays and installs packages from centralized repositories. I credit this change, alongside sites like Github, with rejuvenating Emacs’s 3rd-party ecosystem and, in turn, Emacs itself.

但也并非一帆风顺：没有一个存储库可以满足您的所有需求。有官方的 GNU Emacs 软件包存储库 ELPA  14，但其内容相当稀疏，因为您必须将版权实际签署给 FSF 才能提交给它，而大多数人不能或不会这样做。因此，几乎所有包都出现在 MELPA（志愿者运行的包存储库）上。值得庆幸的是，包管理器会将所有不同的列表合并为一个。

It’s not all roses though: there is no one repository you can use for all your needs. There’s the official GNU Emacs package repository, ELPA 14, but its content is rather sparse, as you have to physically sign over your copyrights to the FSF to submit to it, and most people can’t or won’t do that. Therefore, almost all packages appear on MELPA, a volunteer-run package repository. Thankfully, the package manager will merge all the different listings into one.

由于存储库由志愿者私有，它们可能会暂时或永久关闭，因此我会检查 Emacs Wiki 15以获取当前的存储库列表。

As the repositories are privately owned by volunteers, they may go down – temporarily or permanently – so I would check the Emacs Wiki15 for a current list of repositories.

不过现在，您可以将其添加到您的init 文件中。它包括 ELPA 和 MELPA。

For now though, you can add this to your init file. It includes both ELPA and MELPA.

(setq package-archives
 '(("gnu" . "http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/")
  ("melpa" . "http://melpa.org/packages/")))
(setq package-archives
 '(("gnu" . "http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/")
  ("melpa" . "http://melpa.org/packages/")))

现在是让 Emacs 评估它的好时机。M-x eval-buffer使用您的初始化文件作为当前缓冲区执行命令。

Now is a good time to make Emacs evaluate it. Execute the command M-x eval-buffer with your init file as the current buffer.

接下来，键入M-x package-list-packages，Emacs 应该从上面的所有两个存储库中检索包列表。完成后，将出现一个新的缓冲区，列出所有包。与 Emacs 中的许多辅助缓冲区一样，这个缓冲区也是超链接的。浏览一下 — 您可以从软件包的详细信息页面一键安装您关心的软件包。

Next, type M-x package-list-packages and Emacs should retrieve the package listings from all two repositories above. When it’s done, a new buffer will appear listing all the packages. Like a lot of ancillary buffers in Emacs, this one is also hyperlinked. Have a browse — you can one-click install the packages you care about from the detail page of a package.

暗示

如果您知道包的名称，则可以使用快捷方式M-x package-install并在迷你缓冲区中输入名称。与大多数迷你缓冲区提示一样，这个提示也有TAB完成功能。

包存档不断变化，尤其是如果您让 Emacs 长时间运行，您的本地副本就会变得陈旧；要解决此问题，您可以通过键入 来刷新目录M-x package-refresh-contents。

Hint

If you know the name of the package, you can use the shortcut M-x package-install and enter the name in the minibuffer. And like most minibuffer prompts, this one also has TAB completion.

The package archive(s) change constantly and – especially if you leave Emacs running for long periods of time – your local copy becomes stale; to remedy this, you can refresh the catalog by typing M-x package-refresh-contents.

颜色主题

Color Themes

如果您不喜欢 Emacs 中的默认配色方案 — 那么好消息是，您可以使用颜色主题。键入M-x customize-themes以查看已安装的颜色主题的列表。 Emacs 的包管理器或 Github 等网站免费提供更多内容。

If you dislike the default color scheme in Emacs — then good news, you can use a color theme. Type M-x customize-themes to see a list of your installed color themes. There are more available for free from Emacs’s package manager or sites like Github.

要使用包管理器安装主题，请打开包管理器 ( M-x package-list-packages) 并查找主题；大多数都会有后缀-theme，它们的行为和安装就像普通的软件包一样。安装所需的主题后，请使用界面M-x customize-themes来试用它们。您可以使用自定义界面中描述的常规自定义界面来覆盖您不喜欢的特定颜色。在自定义界面中所做的更改优先于主题。

To install a theme with the package manager, open the package manager (M-x package-list-packages) and go look for themes; most will have the suffix -theme, and they act and install like normal packages. Once you’ve installed the themes you need, use the M-x customize-themes interface to try them out. You can override specific colors you don’t like by using the regular Customize interface described in The Customize Interface. Changes made in the Customize interface take precedence over the themes.

我应该提到的是，您可以同时激活多个主题，因此请确保您意识到这一点。

I should mention that you can have multiple themes active at the same time, so make sure you are aware of this.

寻求帮助

Getting Help

正如我之前在谈论按键时提到的，Emacs 是一个复杂的自记录编辑器。 Emacs 的每个方面都是可搜索或可描述的。学习如何做到这一点对于掌握 Emacs 绝对必要。知道如何找到问题答案的效用是我无法夸大的。我一直使用 Emacs 的自记录功能；唤起我的记忆，或者寻找我不知道的问题的答案。

As I mentioned earlier when I talked about keys, Emacs is a sophisticated self-documenting editor. Every facet of Emacs is searchable or describable. Learning how to do this is absolutely essential to mastering Emacs. The utility of knowing how to find the answers to questions is something I cannot overstate enough. I use Emacs’s self-documenting functionality all the time; to jog my memory, or to seek answers to questions I don’t know.

我还没有谈论 Emacs 的实际核心（移动、编辑等），因为虽然这显然对于掌握 Emacs 至关重要，但它们是您可以耐心地通过使用 Emacs 的自我文档来获得的特定技能帮助系统。

I still haven’t talked about the actual core of Emacs yet (movement, editing, and so forth) because, although that’s obviously critical to mastering Emacs, they are specific skills that you could, with patience, acquire by using Emacs’s self-documenting help systems.

了解如何获得帮助至关重要，因为：

Knowing how to get help is critical because:

Emacs 最懂
Emacs knows best

您的 Emacs 配置会与其他人的 Emacs 配置有所不同，有时只是一点点，有时则很大。在互联网上提问只会给你一般性的答案。如果您重新绑定键，则只有您的Emacs 知道这些键是什么。

Your Emacs configuration will differ – sometimes just a little bit, other times a lot – from other people’s Emacs configurations. Asking a question on the Internet will only give you general answers. If you rebind keys, only your Emacs knows what the keys are.

你会发现更多 Emacs
You will discover more of Emacs

我偶然发现了比我简单地探索所能计数的更酷的功能 - 也许是隐藏在主要模式中的节省时间的命令，或者是改变我经常使用的命令的行为的变量。

许多第三方软件包可能没有足够的用户手册，迫使您阅读源代码或研究软件包公开的命令和变量。

I have stumbled upon more cool features than I can count simply by exploring — maybe a time saving command hidden away in a major mode, or a variable that changes the behavior of a command I use frequently.

A lot of third-party packages may not have an adequate user manual, forcing you to read the source or investigate the commands and variables exposed by the package.

它将帮助您解决问题
It will help you solve problems

我一直帮助人们解决 Emacs 问题，但我并不知道一切- 我所知道的是在哪里查找以及如何阅读文档。

I help people with Emacs questions all the time, but I don’t know everything — what I do know is where to look and how to read the documentation.

它给你信心
It gives you confidence

不知道如何在 Emacs 中执行某些操作很正常，但也会令人困惑。但如果能够说“哦，我不知道该怎么做，但我知道在哪里可以寻求帮助”——您对 Emacs 的信心将随着您的知识的增长而增强。

Not knowing how to do something in Emacs is normal but also confusing. But being able to say that “oh, I don’t know how to do this but I do know where I can look for help” — your confidence in Emacs will go up in step with your knowledge.

Emacs 的帮助系统大致分为三个部分，了解您需要哪一个以及何时需要将节省您的时间。

Emacs’s help system is roughly divided into three parts and knowing which one you need and when will save you time.

信息手册

The Info Manual

Emacs 自己的手册（事实上，GNU 生态系统中的所有手册）都是用 TeXinfo 编写的。如果您曾经使用过命令行工具info，您就会与 TeXinfo 超文本查看器进行交互。显然，Emacs 有自己的信息查看器。 Emacs 的信息手册不仅仅包含与 Emacs 相关的主题。默认情况下，信息浏览器将索引系统上安装的所有其他信息手册 - 像 GNU coreutils 手册之类的内容也会出现。

Emacs’s own manuals (and indeed, all manuals in the GNU ecosystem) are written in TeXinfo. If you have ever used the command line tool info, you will have interacted with the TeXinfo hypertext viewer. Emacs, obviously, has its own info viewer. Emacs’s info manual contains more than just topics relating to Emacs. By default, the info browser will index all the other info manuals installed on your system — things like the GNU coreutils manuals will also be present.

很多人不喜欢info，我也不知道为什么。它的工作方式与网络浏览器非常相似，尽管按键绑定有所不同。

A lot of people dislike info and I’m not sure why. It works in much the same way as a web browser, though the key bindings do differ.

要访问 Emacs 的信息阅读器，请键入M-x info或按C-h i。info将出现文档浏览器，您可以使用鼠标单击超链接，或使用此键盘快捷键表进行导航：

To access Emacs’s info reader type M-x info or press C-h i. info, the documentation browser, will appear and you are free to use your mouse to click on the hyperlinks, or use this table of keyboard shortcuts to navigate:

钥匙 目的
[和] 上一个/下一个节点
l和r 在历史中后退/前进
n和p 上一个/下一个兄弟节点
u 上一层到父节点
SPC 一次滚动一屏
TAB 循环引用和链接
RET 打开活动链接
m 提示输入菜单项名称并将其打开
q 关闭信息浏览器

因为信息手册有层次结构，就像这本书和大多数其他书籍一样，如果您从头到尾地阅读信息手册，您将需要使用[和导航。]这相当于从一章开始阅读一本书，按照排列顺序浏览所有子章、子子章等等。

Because info manuals have hierarchies, in much the same way this and most other books do, you’ll want to use [ and ] to navigate if you’re reading an info manual end-to-end. That’s equivalent to reading a book starting from a chapter, moving through all the sub-chapters, sub-sub-chapters, and so forth, in the order they were laid out.

日常阅读

对于日常阅读，您希望SPC浏览和阅读，因为它“做您想做的事”。它会翻阅一页，直到到达末尾。然后，它选择下一个子节点或下一章。用于浏览、使用[和]在节点之间来回循环。

Everyday reading

For everyday reading, you want SPC for browsing and reading as it “does what you want.” It thumbs through a page until it reaches the end. Then, it either picks the next sub node or the next chapter. For browsing, use [ and ] to cycle back and forth through nodes.

相反，如果您想跳转到下一个或上一个同级节点，则应使用n和p。要在历史记录中后退或前进（就像浏览器一样），请使用l和r。

If, instead, you want to jump to the next or previous sibling node you should use n and p. To go back or forward in history (much like a browser) use l and r.

密钥u上升一级到父级；TAB循环浏览超链接并RET打开它们。

The key u goes up one level to the parent; TAB cycles through the hyperlinks, and RET opens them.

大多数信息手册也以 HTML 版本在线发布，那么为什么要使用 Emacs 自己的阅读器呢？其一，您可以使用 Emacs 的通用书签系统（稍后会详细介绍）。您可以为 Emacs 中的几乎所有内容添加书签：信息页面、文件、目录等等。另一个优点是它在 Emacs 中，因此，如果您正在阅读 Emacs 优秀的《Emacs Lisp 编程简介》并在旁边编写代码，那么将信息手册放在旁边的拆分窗口中特别有用。

Most info manuals are also published in HTML versions online, so why use Emacs’s own reader? For one, you can use Emacs’s universal bookmark system (and more on that later.) You can bookmark almost everything in Emacs: info pages, files, directories, and more. The other advantage is that it’s in Emacs, so keeping the info manual in a split window next to you is particularly useful if you’re reading Emacs’s excellent An Introduction to Programming in Emacs Lisp and writing code alongside it.

如果您想了解特定的 Emacs 功能，您必须首先打开 Emacs 手册。为此，请键入C-h i后跟m。当提示输入菜单项时，输入EmacsEmacs 手册或Emacs Lisp Introelisp 简介。一如既往，有TAB完成。您还可以浏览手册主列表并找到您想要阅读的手册。

If you want to read up on a specific Emacs functionality, you have to open the Emacs manual first. To do this, type C-h i followed by m. When prompted for a menu item, type Emacs for the Emacs manual or Emacs Lisp Intro for the introduction to elisp. As always, there is TAB completion. You can also browse the master list of manuals and find the one you want to read.

C-h F您可以通过键入并在提示符下输入命令名称来查找命令的文档。 Emacs 将跳转到信息手册中描述该命令的正确位置。

You can look up the documentation for a command by typing C-h F and at the prompt enter the name of a command. Emacs will jump to the correct place in the info manual where the command is described.

恰如其分

Apropos

aproposEmacs 有一个广泛的 apropos 系统，其工作方式与命令行上的工作方式大致相同。如果您不完全确定自己在寻找什么，apropos 系统特别有用。有多种利基命令仅搜索 Emacs 自记录内部结构的特定方面。

Emacs has an extensive apropos system that works in much the same way as apropos does on the command line. The apropos system is especially useful if you’re not entirely sure what you’re looking for. There is a variety of niche commands that only search particular aspects of Emacs’s self-documenting internals.

Apropos 是您工具箱中的一个有用的工具。它之所以引人注目，是因为您可以将搜索范围缩小到特定区域。如果你正在寻找一个变量，你可以使用 apropos 系统来搜索变量；如果要查找命令，可以通过命令进行搜索。并且所有 apropos 都支持正则表达式。

Apropos is a useful tool to have in your toolbox. It shines because you can narrow what you’re looking for to a particular area. If you’re looking for a variable, you can use the apropos system that searches variables; if you are looking for commands, you can search by command. And all of apropos supports regular expressions.

最常见的一种必然C-h a是M-x apropos-command。apropos-command显示与给定模式匹配的所有命令（仅是命令，而不是函数）。

The most common one, bound to C-h a, is M-x apropos-command. apropos-command shows all commands (and just the commands, not functions) that match a given pattern.

例如，您可能正在寻找适用于单词的命令（但更多的是关于“单词”的实际含义，请参阅《什么构成单词？》），因此输入C-h a后跟 -word$是一个很好的起点。这将列出所有以.结尾-word的命令。

For instance, you might be on the hunt for commands that work on words (but more on what a “word” actually means in What Constitutes a Word?) so entering C-h a followed by -word$, is a good place to start. That will list all commands that end with -word.

如果运行该命令，您将看到以下输出的子集：

Here’s a subset of the output you would see if you ran that command:

命令 钥匙 目的
ispell-word M-$ 检查下面单词的拼写
或在光标之前。
kill-word M-d 向前杀死角色直到
遇到单词的结尾。
left-word C-<left> 将点向左移动 N 个单词
（如果 N 为负数则向右。）
mark-word M-@ 将标记 ARG 单词设置为远离
从点。

如您所见，您将获得命令的名称、与其绑定的键（如果有）以及用途。 Emacs 有一定的命名约定，一旦您熟悉了 Emacs，您就会发现某些模式的出现。例如，通常会在命令后添加其所操作的语法单元或上下文-word：对于单词、-window对于窗口等等。

As you can see, you get the name of the command, the keys bound to it (if any) and the purpose. Emacs has certain naming conventions and once you’re familiar with Emacs, you will see certain patterns emerge. For instance, it’s common to postfix a command with the syntactic unit or context it operates on: -word for words, -window for windows, and so on.

暗示

Apropos 可以按相关性对结果进行排序。要启用此功能，请添加：

(setq apropos-sort-by-scores t)

到你的初始化文件。

Hint

Apropos can sort results by relevancy. To enable this, add:

(setq apropos-sort-by-scores t)

to your init file.

您可以使用多种 apropos 命令来查询 Emacs。apropos-command对于初学者来说可能是最有用的。它可以让您按模式进行搜索，如果您只记住命令名称的一部分而不是全部，这非常有用。这也是意外发现 Emacs 新功能的绝佳方式。给出apropos-command模式.+（匹配所有内容）会产生大约 8,000 个 Emacs 知道的命令 — 然而，这个数量会根据您加载的软件包数量和您激活的 Emacs 功能而有很大差异。

There’s a wide range of apropos commands you can use to query Emacs. apropos-command is perhaps the most useful to a beginner. And it’ll let you search by pattern, which is great if you only remember part of a command’s name but not all of it. It’s also a fantastic way to accidentally discover new features in Emacs. Giving apropos-command the .+ pattern (to match everything) yields approximately 8,000 commands that Emacs knows about — this amount however will vary greatly depending on the number of packages you have loaded and the features in Emacs you have activated.

Emacs 有一系列专业的 apropos 命令，您可能会发现它们更合适。

Emacs has a range of specialist apropos commands that you might find more suitable.

M-x apropos
M-x apropos

热核选项。此命令将显示与给定模式匹配的所有符号。如果您试图追踪与模式相关的变量、命令和函数，这很有用。

The thermonuclear option. This command will display all symbols that match a given pattern. Useful if you’re trying to track down both variables, commands and functions relating to a pattern.

M-x apropos-command或者C-h a
M-x apropos-command or C-h a

正如我上面所解释的，此命令将仅列出命令。

As I explained above, this command will list only the commands.

M-x apropos-documentation或者C-h d
M-x apropos-documentation or C-h d

仅搜索文档。在 Emacs 中，这意味着可以用来提供符号的 doc 字符串（文档字符串）。偶尔有用。

Searches just the documentation. In Emacs parlance, that means the doc string (documentation string) with which you can supply symbols. Occasionally useful.

M-x apropos-library
M-x apropos-library

列出库中定义的所有变量和函数。如果您正在研究新模式或包，此命令可能会很有用，因为它列出了该库中定义的所有函数和变量。

Lists all variables and functions defined in a library. This command can be useful if you’re investigating a new mode or package as it lists all the functions and variables defined in that library.

M-x apropos-user-option
M-x apropos-user-option

显示通过自定义界面可用的用户选项。这是获取自定义选项的符号名称的一种方法，但如果您正在寻找搜索自定义界面的方法，最好使用自定义界面中的搜索框，因为它也可以让您自定义匹配项。我从来不使用它。

Shows user options available through the Customize interface. This is one way to get the symbol names of Customize options, but if you’re looking for ways to search the Customize interface, you are better off using the Search box in the Customize interface as it lets you customize the matches as well. I never use it.

M-x apropos-value
M-x apropos-value

搜索具有特定值的所有符号。如果您正在寻找保存特定值的变量，此命令可能对您有用。一个潜在的用途是如果我知道变量的值但不知道名称或它的定义位置。

Searches all symbols with a particular value. If you’re looking for a variable that holds a particular value, this command may be of use to you. A potential use is if I know the value of a variable but not the name or where it’s defined.

如果您不确定要查找的内容（也许您只知道名称的一部分，或者您只记得一些文档），那么 apropos 是一个可以帮助您的工具。我发现 apropos 不可或缺；这是列出与某些模式匹配的所有命令的好方法，也是发现新命令的更好方法。

If you’re unsure of what you are looking for – maybe you only have part of a name, or you just remember a bit of the documentation – then apropos is a tool that can help you. I find apropos indispensable; it’s a great way to list all the commands that match certain patterns and an even greater way to discover new commands.

描述系统

The Describe System

描述命令系统体现了 Emacs 自记录特性的美妙之处。如果您知道自己在寻找什么，那么描述将解释它是什么。 Emacs 的每个方面——无论是用 elisp 编写的代码还是用 C 编写的核心层——都可以通过描述系统进行访问和索引。从按键到命令、字符集、编码系统、字体、外观、模式、语法表等等——一切都在那里，分类整齐。

What captures the beauty of Emacs’s self-documenting nature is the describe system of commands. If you know what you’re looking for, then describe will explain what it is. Every facet of Emacs – be it code written in elisp or the core layer written is C – is accessible and indexed through the describe system. From keys, to commands, character sets, coding systems, fonts, faces, modes, syntax tables and more — it’s all there, neatly categorized.

描述系统不是静态的。每次您查询 Emacs 的特定部分时，它都会通过内部自省层获取所需的详细信息，该内部自省层本身会查询 Emacs 自己的内部数据结构。内省层和内部数据结构都可以通过 elisp 进行查询。 Emacs 中没有“秘密”——当然，记录的 API 层是访问 Emacs 自身内部状态的推荐方法，但与其他编辑器和 IDE 不同，您不必受制于包作者或 Emacs 维护者。我认为这种开放性的体现（由描述系统完美地捕捉到）是 Emacs 的最佳功能之一。

The describe system is not static. Every time you query a particular part of Emacs, it will fetch the required details through an internal introspection layer which itself queries Emacs’s own internal data structures. Both the introspection layer and internal data structures are queryable by you through elisp. There are no “secrets” in Emacs — sure, the documented API layer is the recommended way of accessing Emacs’s own internal state, but unlike other editors and IDEs you are not beholden to the package author or Emacs maintainers. I think this embodiment of openness, beautifully captured by the describe system, is one of the best features of Emacs.

C-h您可以找到与前缀键16绑定的最重要的描述键；实际上还有更多，但我认为其中大多数对于除了 elisp 编写者之外的所有人来说实用性有限。

You can find the most important describe keys bound to the C-h prefix key16; there’s more, a lot more actually, but I think most of them are of limited utility to all but elisp writers.

我经常使用描述系统。在撰写本书时，我广泛使用了信息手册和 apropos，但我使用描述系统来仔细检查我所写的所有内容是否正确。如果您发现自己想知道 Emacs 中的符号是做什么的（无论是函数、命令、变量还是模式），describe 会告诉您。

I use the describe system constantly. In writing this book, I have used both the info manual and apropos extensively, but the describe system is what I use to double check that everything I have written is correct. If you ever find yourself wondering what a symbol in Emacs does (be it a function, a command, a variable or a mode) then describe will tell you.

文档字符串唯一的小缺点是它假设了技术受众：信息手册通常不会。这并不全是坏事，您不必成为 elisp 专家才能理解描述，但需要一些时间来熟悉文档字符串中使用的术语。

The only slight downside to the doc string is that it assumes a technical audience: the info manual generally does not. It’s not all bad, you don’t have to be an elisp expert to make sense of the description but it will take a bit of time to familiarize yourself with the terminology used in the doc strings.

请记住，描述系统描述了一个活生生的系统——您的个性化 Emacs。

Remember, the describe system describes a living system — your personalized Emacs.

您需要记住四个描述键，因为它们是日常 Emacs 使用中最重要的键。

You need to memorize four describe keys as they are the most important ones for day-to-day Emacs use.

M-x describe-mode或者C-h m
M-x describe-mode or C-h m

显示主要模式（以及还启用的任何次要模式）的文档以及所述模式引入的任何键绑定。描述命令查看当前的缓冲区。

当您使用新的主要模式时，此命令应该是您的第一个调用端口。您将通过这种方式发现Emacs 的许多功能，并且使用此命令是绝对必要的。

它不做的是列出未绑定到任何键的特定于模式的命令：它们只是不显示。

Displays the documentation for the major mode (and any minor modes also enabled) along with any keybindings introduced by said modes. The describe command looks at your current buffer.

This command should be your first port of call when you’re using a new major mode. You will discover a lot of Emacs’s functionality this way and it is absolutely imperative that you use this command.

What it doesn’t do is list mode-specific commands that are not bound to any key: they are simply not shown.

M-x describe-function或者C-h f
M-x describe-function or C-h f

描述一个函数。掌握 Emacs 的关键路径上的另一个命令。了解 Emacs 中的某些内容（以及如何查找它）很有用，但能够跳转到声明它的代码部分也很有用。

描述一个函数将为您提供 elisp 函数签名、绑定到它的键（如果有）、声明它的超链接以及文档字符串。

如果该功能是一个命令，它会说它是交互式的。

Describes a function. Another command on the critical path to mastering Emacs. Knowing what something does in Emacs (and how to look it up) is useful but so is being able to jump to the part of the code where it’s declared.

Describing a function will give you the elisp function signature, the keys (if any) bound to it, a hyperlink to where it’s declared, and a doc string.

If the function is a command, it will say it is interactive.

M-x describe-variable或者C-h v
M-x describe-variable or C-h v

描述一个变量。与 一样describe-function，此命令也很重要，但可能不那么重要，因为更改变量对于初学者来说并不总是那么容易。尽管如此，能够了解变量的作用还是很重要的。

Describes a variable. Like describe-function, this command is also important, but perhaps less so as changing variables is not always easy to do for a beginner. Nevertheless, being able to read up on what a variable does is.

M-x describe-key或者C-h k
M-x describe-key or C-h k

描述键绑定的作用。在所有命令中，这是最需要记住的命令之一，并且就像M-x describe-function您会经常使用的命令一样。如果您不确定键绑定的作用，只需进入界面describe-key并重新键入该键 — Emacs 就会告诉您它的作用。

值得记住的是，一些键来自主要模式和次要模式，并且不是全局的。因此，根据您键入命令的缓冲区，您可能会得到不同的答案。

Describes what a key binding does. Of all the commands, this is one of the most useful ones to memorize, and like M-x describe-function it’s a command you will use frequently. If you’re unsure what a key binding does, simply enter the describe-key interface and re-type the key — and Emacs will tell you what it does.

It’s worth remembering that some keys come from major and minor modes and are not global. Therefore, you may get a different answer depending on the buffer in which you type the command.

Emacs 确实有更多的描述命令，但它们对于日常使用来说远不实用或有用。了解了您现在对描述命令的命名以及如何通过模式查找命令的了解，列出所有这些命令应该是一个简单的17 个练习。

Emacs does have a lot more describe commands but they’re nowhere near as practical or useful for day-to-day use. Knowing what you know now about the naming of describe commands and how to find commands by patterns, it should be a trivial17 exercise to list all of them.

运动理论

The Theory of Movement

Escape Meta Alt Control Shift

–信息.gnu.emacs

Escape Meta Alt Control Shift

– info.gnu.emacs

四处走动并高效地走动与了解如何快速有效地编辑文本同样重要。但 Emacs 中的移动不仅仅是缓冲区中的字符；还包括缓冲区中的字符。有许多补充技能可以构成导航，例如理解 Emacs 相当复杂的窗口系统。

Getting around, and getting around efficiently, is as important as knowing how to edit text quickly and efficiently. But movement in Emacs is more than characters in a buffer; there’s a host of supplementary skills that make up navigation, like understanding Emacs’s rather complicated windowing system.

我不希望您立即记住并应用您在这里学到的所有内容。我已经把事情列出来了，这样你就可以从头开始，逐步完成，在阅读时拾取一些零散的内容。正如我多次强调的那样，最重要的部分是给它时间和练习——在日常生活中花点时间问问自己是否有更好的方法来解决你面临的问题。

I wouldn’t expect you to remember and apply everything you learn here right away. I’ve laid things out so you can start at the beginning and work your way through, picking up bits and pieces as you read. The most important part, as I’ve stressed many times, is to give it time and practice — take a moment in your day-to-day life to ask yourself if there’s a better way of solving a problem with which you are faced.

Emacs 中的移动是本地的、区域的或全球的。局部移动是指在该点附近编辑和移动文本时所做的操作。句法单元（对一组字符进行操作的命令的半正式术语）是字符、单词、行、句子、段落、平衡表达式等。区域移动和局部移动类似，但区域移动涉及整个函数或类定义（如果您正在编写代码）；或者章节和类似的结构，如果你正在写散文。全局移动是指从一个缓冲区到另一个缓冲区，或者从一个窗口到下一个窗口的任何操作。

Movement in Emacs is local, regional or global. Local movement is what you do when you edit and move around text near to the point. A syntactic unit – a semi-formal term for commands that operate on a group of characters – is a character, word, line, sentence, paragraph, balanced expression, and so forth. Regional and local movement are similar but regional movement involves whole functions or class definitions, if you are writing code; or chapters and such constructs, if you are writing prose. Global movement is anything that takes you from one buffer to another, or from one window to the next.

初学者首先看到的是 Emacs 对创建窗口的偏好：当您查看帮助文件时，当您编译文件时，或者当您打开 shell 时。如果您从未使用过平铺窗口管理器（因为这正是 Emacs 的本质），那么拆分和删除窗口的想法可能看起来很奇怪 - 在其他编辑器中您可能会使用拆分窗格，但您几乎从不更改它以适应手头的任务。

The first thing a beginner sees is Emacs’s penchant for creating windows: when you view a help file, when you compile a file, or when you open a shell. If you have never used a tiling window manager (for that is exactly what Emacs is), the idea of splitting and deleting windows may seem strange — in other editors you may use split panes but you almost never change it to suit the task at hand.

在 Emacs 中，窗口是暂时的；他们根据您的需要来来去去。您可以保存窗口配置（有多种方法可以做到这一点），但它们从来都不是一成不变的，就像许多编辑器一样 - 设置一次，然后就不会再更改。你必须习惯这一点。现在，您可以使用许多变量来微调 Emacs 的窗口行为，但您无法真正调整自己的方式来停止使用 Emacs 的窗口。有些软件包尝试用框架替换窗口，并取得了一些成功，但它们本质上是 hack，我建议您至少在熟悉Emacs系统之前避免使用它们。

In Emacs, windows are transient; they come and go as you need them. You can save your window configuration (and there are several ways of doing this) but they were never meant to be immutable, like so many editors — set once and then never changed again. You have to get used to this. Now, there are many variables you can use to fine-tune Emacs’s windowing behavior, but you can’t really tweak your way out of using Emacs’s windows. Some packages try to replace windows with frames, with some success, but they are essentially hacks and I would recommend you avoid using them at least until you’re comfortable with Emacs’s system.

当不再需要缓冲区时，它们很少被杀死（即关闭）；大多数 Emacs 黑客只会简单地转向其他东西，只在需要时才返回。这可能看起来很浪费，但每个缓冲区（除了各种元数据和缓冲区的特定编码系统之外）仅比其中字符的字节大小稍大。典型的 Emacs 会话在重新启动之间会持续数周，并且大多数 Emacs 黑客都会毫无问题地运行数百个缓冲区。

Buffers are rarely killed (that is, closed) when they are no longer needed; most Emacs hackers will simply switch away to something else, only to return to it when needed. That may seem wasteful, but each buffer (aside from assorted metadata and the buffer’s particular coding system) is only slightly bigger than the byte size of the characters in it. A typical Emacs session lasts weeks between restarts and most Emacs hackers have many hundreds of buffers running without issue.

无论您在 Emacs 中执行什么任务，您都需要了解缓冲区和窗口的概念以及如何处理它们。值得庆幸的是，这可以很简单也可以很复杂，具体取决于您的期望或您希望如何设置。

No matter the task you’re doing in Emacs, you will need to contend with the notion of buffers and windows and how to handle them. Thankfully, that can be as easy or as complex, depending on your expectations or how you want things set up.

基础

The Basics

顺便一提

您是否已将 Caps Lock 重新映射为 Control？阅读Caps Lock as Control以了解为什么这如此重要。

By the way

Have you re-mapped Caps Lock to Control yet? Read Caps Lock as Control to understand why this is so important.

学习基本的按键绑定来查找和保存文件、更改缓冲区以及日常使用的基本要素是掌握 Emacs 的第一步。但是，您可以自由地使用菜单栏来执行此操作，直到您将这些键写入内存为止。关于菜单栏需要注意的一件重要事情是它在终端中不可单击（除非您使用 Emacs 24.4 或更高版本）。相反，您必须按F10来激活并使用键盘导航菜单栏。

Learning the basic key bindings to find and save files, change buffers, and the bare essentials of day-to-day use is the first step on the path to mastering Emacs. However, you’re free to use the menu bar to do this until you have committed the keys to memory. One important thing to note about the menu bar is that it won’t be clickable in a terminal (unless you’re using Emacs 24.4 or later). Instead, you must press F10 to activate and navigate the menu bar with the keyboard.

笔记

就像我在获取帮助中解释的那样，如果您没有看到菜单栏（它应该出现在 GUI 和终端 Emacs 中）并且您已对 Emacs 的配置进行了更改（例如，入门工具包或同事的初始化文件），您可以通过键入显示它M-x menu-bar-mode，但您仍然需要追踪配置中隐藏的部分。

Note

Like I explained in Getting Help, If you don’t see a menu bar (it should appear in both GUI and Terminal Emacs) and you have made changes to Emacs’s configuration – for instance, a starter kit or a colleague’s init file – you can show it by typing M-x menu-bar-mode but you still need to track down the part of your configuration where it’s hidden.

一旦您成为传奇的 Emacs 黑客，您自然会想要隐藏它，因为它占用了宝贵的屏幕空间。在此之前，请将其保持启用状态。我鼓励您保持启用状态，直到您对自己的 Emacs 技能有足够的信心而不再需要它为止。

Once you’re a legendary Emacs hacker, you will naturally want to hide it as it takes up valuable screen real estate. Until then, please leave it enabled. I encourage you to leave it enabled until you are confident enough in your Emacs skills that you no longer need it.

大多数主要模式也有自己的菜单栏条目，提高了主要模式的可发现性。我刚开始使用菜单栏很长一段时间，它确实对我很有帮助，因为我可以专注于记住导航和编辑等重要命令。

Most major modes have their own menu bar entry as well, improving the discoverability of the major mode. I used the menu bar for a long time when I was starting out, and it really helped me as I could focus on remembering important commands like navigation and editing.

如果您更喜欢仅使用键盘的方法，则必须了解一些键绑定才能在 Emacs 中执行基本任务。

If you prefer a keyboard-only approach, the are a handful of key bindings you must know to carry out basic tasks in Emacs.

按键绑定 目的
C-x C-f 查找（打开）文件
C-x C-s 保存缓冲区
C-x b 开关缓冲器
C-x k 杀死（关闭）缓冲区
C-x C-b 显示所有打开的缓冲区
C-x C-c 退出 Emacs
ESC ESC ESC 退出提示，
区域、前缀参数和
返回到只有一个窗口
C-/ 取消更改
F10 激活菜单栏1

当您根据扩展名打开文件时（如果失败，则根据文件的内容），Emacs 会猜测正确的主要模式，并且或多或少可以开箱即用。除了上面的键绑定之外，您还可以像其他编辑器一样仅使用箭头键开始编辑和移动。

Emacs will guess the right major mode when you open files based on its extension (and if that fails, by the content of the file) and more or less work out of the box. Aside from the key bindings above, you can start editing and moving around with just the arrow keys like other editors.

让我们依次讨论每个命令，因为它们的简单操作掩盖了它们的复杂性。

Let’s talk about each command in turn as their simple actions belie their complexity.

C-x C-f：查找文件

C-x C-f: Find file

在 Emacs 中打开文件称为查找文件甚至访问文件。话虽如此，说开放也完全没问题。原因是 Emacs 确实不区分打开现有文件和创建新文件。我交替使用这些术语。

Opening a file in Emacs is called finding a file or even visiting a file. Having said that, it’s perfectly fine to say open also. The reason is that Emacs really doesn’t distinguish between opening an existing file and creating a new file. I use the terms interchangeably.

因此，如果您键入C-x C-f并输入/tmp/hello-world.txt，Emacs 就会访问它，无论它是否存在；如果不是，则显示一个空缓冲区。

So, if you type C-x C-f and enter /tmp/hello-world.txt, Emacs will visit it, whether it’s there or not; if it isn’t, an empty buffer is shown instead.

主模式加载顺序

Major mode load order

当您访问文件时，Emacs 会选择一个主要模式。大多数编辑器都会对文件扩展名做出很多假设，而您无法轻易更改这些假设。 Emacs 支持一系列检测机制，这些机制都可以根据您的需要进行更改。它们按照应用顺序在此处列出。

When you visit a file, Emacs will pick a major mode. Most editors make a lot of assumptions about file extensions that you cannot easily change. Emacs supports an array of detection mechanisms that can all be changed to suit your needs. They are listed here in the order they are applied.

文件局部变量
File-local variables

是 Emacs 可以为每个文件启用的变量（如果它们存在于文件中）。它们可以显示为标题：

-*- mode: mode-name-here; my-variable: value -*-

或页脚：

Local Variables:
mode: mode-name-here
my-variable: value
End:

Emacs 还将使用该主要模式的注释语法来查看注释行。

值得注意的是，读入 Emacs 的文件变量是该文件缓冲区的本地变量（意味着其他缓冲区不受它的影响。）这意味着如果您有仅适用于该文件的特定设置，您可以将它们添加到页眉或页脚，然后Emacs 会自动加载它们。实际上，这意味着从缩进设置到更复杂的变量的所有内容都可以通过文件变量进行控制。

因为 Emacs 实际上是直接从文件运行代码，所以所有 Emacs 变量都分为安全和不安全文件变量：通常由 Emacs 维护人员声明为安全的变量会自动评估。对于不安全的变量，你必须首先告诉 Emacs 做什么：你可以忽略该变量；或仅对该文件临时评估一次；或声明其安全。

are variables that Emacs can enable per-file if they present in the file. They can appear as headers:

-*- mode: mode-name-here; my-variable: value -*-

or footers:

Local Variables:
mode: mode-name-here
my-variable: value
End:

Emacs will also look at commented lines using that major mode’s comment syntax.

It is worth knowing that file variables read into Emacs are local to that file’s buffer (meaning other buffers are unaffected by it.) That means if you have particular settings that apply only to that file, you can add them to the header or footer and Emacs will load them automatically. In practical terms, that means everything from indentation settings to more complex variables are controllable from file variables.

Because Emacs is in effect running code straight from a file, all Emacs variables are divided into safe and unsafe file variables: variables that are declared as safe – typically by Emacs maintainers – are evaluated automatically. For unsafe variables, you must first tell Emacs what to do: you can ignore the variable; or evaluate it once, temporarily, for that file only; or declare it as safe.

程序加载指令
Program loader directives

或shebangs也受支持。如果您的文件以#!- 例如#!/usr/bin/env python或#!/bin/bash- 开头，那么 Emacs 将找出主要模式并运行它（如果 Emacs 中可用）。该变量interpreter-mode-alist列出了 Emacs 可以检测到的程序加载器。

or shebangs are also supported. If your file begins with #! – for instance #!/usr/bin/env python or #!/bin/bash – then Emacs will figure out the major mode and run it, if it is available in Emacs. The variable interpreter-mode-alist lists the program loaders Emacs can detect.

魔法模式检测
Magic mode detection

使用该magic-mode-alist变量来查看文件的开头是否与魔术模式变量中存储的模式匹配。如果您无法提前注释文件或预测文件名或扩展名，则此检测模式特别有用。

uses the magic-mode-alist variable to see if the beginning of the file matches a pattern stored in the magic mode variable. This detection mode is particularly useful if you have no way of annotating the file or predicting the filename or extension ahead of time.

自动模式检测
Automatic mode detection

这是大多数主要模式的应用方式。 Emacs 有一个非常大的模式注册表，这些模式与文件扩展名、文件名或文件路径的全部或部分相匹配，存储在变量 中auto-mode-alist。

例如，如果您打开/etc/passwd，Emacs 将检测到这一点并以etc-passwd-generic-mode主要模式打开该文件。如果文件名以 结尾.zip，Emacs 将改为以archive-mode.

is how most major modes are applied. Emacs has a very large registry of patterns that match a file extension, file name or all or parts of a file’s path, stored in the variable auto-mode-alist.

For instance, if you open /etc/passwd, Emacs will detect this and open the file with etc-passwd-generic-mode major mode. If the filename ends with .zip, Emacs will instead open the file in archive-mode.

尽管不同的启发式方法可能看起来很复杂，但好消息是工作已经为您完成。 Emacs 的主要模式检测相当复杂，它几乎总是会为您选择正确的模式。

Although the different heuristics may look complicated, the good news is the work is done for you. Emacs’s major mode detection is rather sophisticated and it will almost always pick the right thing for you.

编码系统和行结尾

Coding Systems and Line Endings

Emacs 应用了您应该了解的另外两个重要启发式方法：编码系统和行结束符。

Emacs applies two other important heuristics you should know about: coding systems and line endings.

编码系统
Coding systems

Emacs 具有出色的 Unicode 支持（C-h h请键入查看演示），包括在不同编码系统之间透明读写、双向从右到左脚本支持、键盘输入法切换等等。

要查看当前缓冲区使用的编码系统，您可以键入C-h C <RET>。 Emacs 将显示大量信息，包括与缓冲区关联的所有编码系统 - 但对于文件来说，它们几乎总是设置为相同的编码系统。

模型行也会给你一个粗略的想法：

U:**-  helloworld.c       92% of 5k   ...

第一个字符U表示缓冲区helloworld.c具有多字节编码系统。如果表示1，则它通常是任意数量的 ISO 字符编码的第 1 部分。确切的助记符将取决于您正在使用的数百种受支持的编码系统中的哪一种 - 因此，whyC-h C <RET>是查看它是什么的可靠方法。
