Emacs has excellent Unicode support (type C-h h to see it demonstrated), including transparently reading and writing between different coding systems, bidirectional right-to-left script support, keyboard input method switching, and more.

To see the coding system in use for the current buffer, you can type C-h C <RET>. Emacs will display a lot of information, including all the coding systems associated with the buffer — but for files, they are almost always set to the same coding system.

The modeline will also give you a rough idea:

U:**-  helloworld.c       92% of 5k   ...

The first character, U, means the buffer helloworld.c has a multi-byte coding system. If it said 1, it would typically be part 1 of any number of ISO character encodings. The exact mnemonic will depend on which of the hundreds of supported coding systems you are using — hence why C-h C <RET> is a sure-fire way to see what it is.

行结尾
Line endings

当您打开文件时，Emacs 将确定使用的行结尾。如果文件使用 DOS 行结尾，那么当您打开文件和保存文件时，它们会被保留。对于 UNIX 和 OSX 之前的 Macintosh 编码也是如此。

模型行会告诉您正在使用的行结尾：

U:**-  helloworld.c       92% of 5k   ...

U如上所述，第一个字符表示编码系统。这:意味着它是 UNIX 风格的行结尾。对于 DOS 来说，它会说(DOS)，(Mac)对于 Macintoshes 来说，它会说 。

When you open a file, Emacs will determine the line endings used. If the file uses DOS line endings, then they are preserved when you open the file and when you save it. Likewise for UNIX and pre-OSX Macintosh encodings.

The modeline will tell you what line ending you are using:

U:**-  helloworld.c       92% of 5k   ...

The first character U, as explained above, indicates the coding system. The : means it’s UNIX-style line endings. For DOS it would say (DOS), and (Mac) for Macintoshes.

C-x C-s：保存缓冲区

C-x C-s: Save Buffer

在缓冲区中，我解释了在 Emacs 中，缓冲区不必是文件系统上的文件，但它可以是用于网络 I/O 之类的临时缓冲区，甚至只是用于处理文本的临时文件。因此，这在实践中意味着您可以在 Emacs 中保存任何缓冲区 - 甚至是内部缓冲区，例如帮助或网络 I/O 缓冲区。

In The Buffer, I explained that in Emacs a buffer need not be a file on your file system, but it could be a transient buffer used for things like network I/O or even just a scratch file for processing text. So, what that means in practice is that you can save any buffer in Emacs — even internal ones like a help or a network I/O buffer.

当您要求 Emacs 保存缓冲区时，它会将其保存到与该缓冲区关联的文件中（当且仅当该缓冲区具有关联的文件名时），或者在没有文件名的情况下询问您一个名称。如果您正在保存尚未分配文件的缓冲区，则通常会发生后一种情况；也许它是一个临时缓冲区，甚至是帮助命令的输出。

When you ask Emacs to save a buffer, it will save it to the file associated with the buffer – if, and only if, the buffer has a filename associated – or ask you for a name if there isn’t one. The latter instance will typically happen if you’re saving a buffer that does not yet have a file assigned to it; maybe it’s a temporary buffer or even the output from a help command.

将缓冲区写入文件
Writing a buffer to a file

如果您想将缓冲区保存到不同的文件（类似于其他编辑器中的另存为...），您可以使用该命令C-x C-w写入新文件。

If you want to save a buffer to a different file – akin to Save As… in other editors – you can use the command C-x C-w to write to a new file.

保存所有文件
Saving all files

您可以键入内容C-x s，然后系统会依次要求您保存每个未保存的文件。

You can type C-x s and are asked, in turn, to save each unsaved file.

C-x C-c: 退出 Emacs

C-x C-c: Exits Emacs

您可以退出 Emacs – 或者如果您在客户端-服务器模式下使用 Emacs，则终止与它的连接 – 但 Emacs 仅在询问您是否要保存未保存的文件后才会退出。

You can exit Emacs – or just terminate your connection to it, if you are using Emacs in client-server mode – but Emacs will only exit after asking you if you want to save unsaved files.

当 Emacs 要求您保存文件时，您有多种选择：

You have several options when Emacs asks you to save a file:

按键绑定 目的
Y或者yes 保存文件
N或者DEL 跳过当前缓冲区
q或者RET 中止保存，继续退出
C-g 中止保存并退出
! 保存所有剩余的缓冲区
d 比较文件系统上的文件
与缓冲区中的那个

上面的大多数命令都是不言自明的。 Emacs 将遍历未保存文件的整个列表，但不是所有未保存的缓冲区。您可能还记得之前的内容，缓冲区可能不附加到任何一个文件。

Most of the commands above are self-explanatory. Emacs will traverse the entire list of unsaved files but not all unsaved buffers. As you may recall from earlier, it is possible to have buffers that are not attached to any one file.

如果您尝试在不保存的情况下退出，Emacs 总会最后一次询问您是否要继续。

And if you try to exit without saving, Emacs will always ask you one last time if you want to proceed.

C-x b：开关缓冲器

C-x b: Switch Buffer

如果您一次编辑多个文件 – 或者在文档缓冲区或特定于模式的缓冲区（例如 Python 的 shell）之间切换 – 了解如何快速有效地切换缓冲区非常重要。

If you edit more than one file at a time – or switch between documentation buffers or mode-specific buffers, such as Python’s shell – knowing how to switch buffers quickly and efficiently is very important.

Alt+TAB与大多数窗口管理器一样，Emacs 会记住您访问的最后一个缓冲区，因此，当您键入 时C-x b，前一个缓冲区的名称是默认操作- 这意味着按下RET将带您前往该缓冲区。

Like Alt+TAB in most window managers, Emacs will remember the last buffer you visited so that, when you type C-x b, the name of the former buffer is the default action — meaning pressing RET will take you to it.

切换缓冲区是 Emacs 黑客的第二天性。一旦你适应了它，你就不会去想；您将无需多想就可以快速、即时地切换缓冲区。

Switching buffers is second nature to Emacs hackers. Once you’re comfortable with it, you won’t even think about; you’ll switch through buffers quickly and instantaneously without so much as a second thought.

缓冲区命名约定

Emacs 中的一些缓冲区与外部程序（可能是类似 shell bash）交互，或者保存由 Emacs 本身生成的瞬时信息。为了将它们与用户创建的缓冲区区分开来，它们*的名称中包含字符，如下所示：*buffername*。

Buffer naming conventions

Some buffers in Emacs interact with external programs – perhaps a shell like bash – or they hold transient information generated by Emacs itself. To distinguish them from user-created buffers, they have * characters in their names, like so: *buffername*.

当您考虑暂存缓冲区（您创建和使用但不打算永久保存的缓冲区）的性质时，文件和缓冲区是两个不同（但相关）的概念这一事实是有意义的。例如，如果您想运行键盘宏或对代码区域进行大量文本编辑，Emacs 黑客会将其复制到虚构的暂存缓冲区（只需切换到不存在的缓冲区名称即可创建），进行必要的编辑，然后切换回原始缓冲区。

The fact that files and buffers are two distinct (but related) concepts makes sense when you consider the nature of scratch buffers — buffers that you create and use but don’t intend to permanently save. For instance, if you want to run a keyboard macro or do extensive text editing on a region of code, an Emacs hacker would copy it to a made-up scratch buffer (created simply by switching to a buffer name that does not exist), do the requisite editing, and switch back to the original buffer.

将缓冲区写入文件
Writing buffers to files

如果您稍后决定要将缓冲区保存到文件系统，可以按C-x C-s保存它。

If you later decide you want to save the buffer to the file system, you can press C-x C-s to save it.

列出缓冲区
Listing buffers

另一个有用的命令是C-x C-b.它显示系统上运行的所有缓冲区的列表。

One more useful command is C-x C-b. It displays a list of all buffers running on your system.

缓冲器切换替代方案

Buffer Switching Alternatives

内置的缓冲区切换接口比较差；它提供基本的TAB补全和一些模糊匹配，但除此之外就没有什么了。事实上，完成工具对您的用户体验非常重要，因此我建议您留出时间来研究适合您的工作流程和个性的完成框架。如果您使用的是入门工具包，您可能已经在 Emacs 中预先配置并启用了该工具包。

The built-in interface for buffer switching is rather poor; it offers basic TAB-completion and some fuzzy matching, but little else. In fact, completion tooling is so important to your user experience that I recommend you set aside time to investigate completion frameworks that fit your workflow and personality. If you are using a starter kit you may already have one preconfigured and enabled in your Emacs.

尽管如此，对于大多数刚开始使用的人来说，如果您使用早于版本 27 的 Emacsen，我建议使用 IDO，而对于版本 27 或更高版本则建议使用 FIDO（直接替代品）。

Nevertheless, for most people starting out, I recommend IDO if you are using Emacsen earlier than version 27, and FIDO (a drop-in replacement) for versions 27 or later.

无论哪个版本，我都使用这两个版本，并且没有它们就无法生活 — 事实上，大多数 Emacs 用户肯定在某个时候使用过 IDO 或类似的东西。

Regardless of the version, I use both and couldn’t live without them — indeed, most Emacs users will most certainly have used IDO or something like it at some point.

对于 IDO 模式
For IDO Mode

键入M-x ido-mode，然后重试C-x b或C-x C-f重试。

您可以通过自定义选项永久启用它ido-mode：

M-x customize-option RET ido-mode RET

您还可以通过启用Flex 匹配来改进 IDO 的模糊匹配：

M-x customize-option RET ido-enable-flex
-matching RET

您还可以通过运行来自定义更多功能M-x customize-group ido。要进一步阅读此主题，我建议您阅读IDO 模式简介。2

Type M-x ido-mode and then try C-x b or C-x C-f again.

You can enable it permanently by customizing the option ido-mode:

M-x customize-option RET ido-mode RET

You can also improve IDO’s fuzzy matching by enabling flex matching:

M-x customize-option RET ido-enable-flex
-matching RET

And you can customize many more features by running M-x customize-group ido. For further reading on this subject, I recommend you read Introduction to IDO mode.2

对于 FIDO 模式（Emacs 27 或更高版本）
For FIDO Mode (Emacs 27 or later)

类型M-x fido-mode。有一些与此模式相关的完成选项，但它们位于伞组下icomplete，内置了父完成机制 FIDO。要查看它们，请键入M-x customize-group icomplete。

Type M-x fido-mode. There are some completion options related to this mode, but they are under the umbrella group icomplete, the parent completion mechanism FIDO is built in. To view them, type M-x customize-group icomplete.

额外的完成框架

如今，包管理器中有数十个可用的完成框架。大多数人都会相互权衡，用一种便利或利益来交换另一种：无论是速度还是速度；简单;功能以及与主要模式或外部资源的集成；搜索和完成方法；或者如何将结果呈现给用户。

除了 FIDO 和 IDO 之外，一些比较常见的还包括：Helm、ivy、Selectrum、Icicles、Icomplete。

完成或搜索信息的内容以及方式是 Emacs 社区中一场持续不断的争论，也是探索组合和访问信息和工作流程的不同方式的好方法。我建议您尝试大多数这些框架，看看它们的能力：它们是真正的力量倍增器；尤其是那些合并来自第三方来源（命令行工具、语言服务器等）的结果的结果

Additional Completion Frameworks

There are dozens of completion frameworks available in the package manager today. Most trade off one another, swapping one convenience or benefit for another: be it speed; simplicity; features and integration with major modes or external sources; search and completion methodology; or how results are presented to the user.

Some of the more common ones in addition to FIDO and IDO include: Helm, ivy, Selectrum, Icicles, Icomplete.

What, and how, you complete or search for information is a self-perpetuating debate in the Emacs community, and a great way to explore the different ways of combining and accessing information and workflows. I recommend you try most of these frameworks and see what they’re capable of: they are true force multipliers; especially the ones that merge results from third-party sources (command line tools, language servers, etc.)

C-x k：杀死缓冲区

C-x k: Kill Buffer

在 Emacs 中杀死缓冲区意味着关闭它。您不必杀死不使用的缓冲区。让它们坐在后台直到您再次需要它们是完全正常的。通常，认真的 Emacs 用户一次会打开数百甚至数千个缓冲区。

Killing a buffer in Emacs means closing it. You don’t have to kill buffers you don’t use. It’s perfectly normal to let them sit in the background until you need them again. Normally, serious Emacs users have hundreds or even thousands of open buffers at a time.

ESC ESC ESC：键盘转义

ESC ESC ESC: Keyboard Escape

单击脚跟键三下。如果你被困在某个地方或者想要“恢复正常”——那么按下按钮ESC ESC ESC（可能）会解决你的问题。

The click your heels three times key. If you’re stuck somewhere or want to “go back to normal” — then pressing ESC ESC ESC will (probably) solve your problems.

所有窗口都被删除（意味着它们从视图中隐藏），提示被退出，特殊缓冲区被隐藏，前缀参数被取消，递归编辑级别被取消。

All windows are deleted (meaning they’re hidden from view), prompts are exited out of, special buffers are hidden, prefix arguments are cancelled, and recursive editing levels are unwound.

C-/：撤消

C-/: Undo

撤消是一项常见的活动，它绑定到多个键：C-/、C-_、C-x u、Edit -> Undo，甚至是物理撤消按钮（如果您的键盘有）。

Undoing is a common activity and it is bound to several keys: C-/, C-_, C-x u, Edit -> Undo, or even a physical undo button if your keyboard has it.

您更喜欢哪个命令取决于您：我认为C-/这是最容易键入的，但如果您的字符集不是美国或英国，那么您可能更喜欢另一个。大多数初学者指南都会建议您使用C-x u或 ，C-_但我发现它们比 更难输入C-/。

Which command you prefer is up to you: I think C-/ is the easiest to type, but if your character set is not US or UK, then you may prefer another. Most beginner’s guides will recommend you use C-x u or even C-_ but I find them harder to type than C-/.

与其他编辑器不同，Emacs 没有专用的重做命令，这与 Emacs 独特的撤消系统（称为撤消环）有关。

Unlike other editors, Emacs does not have a dedicated redo command, and that has to do with Emacs’s unique undo system known as the undo ring.

大多数编辑器都具有线性撤消列表：您可以撤消和重做，但如果您撤消然后更改文本，您将丢失撤消的步骤；它们将无法恢复并永远丢失。

Most editors feature a linear undo list: you can undo and redo, but if you undo and then change the text, you will lose the undone steps; they will be unrecoverable and lost forever.

在 Emacs 中，情况并非如此。您采取的每个操作都会记录在撤消环中，这包括撤消某些操作。 Emacs 会将某些命令组合成一个有凝聚力的撤消单元，例如键入字符或连续多次重复同一命令。有些事件总是会“密封”撤消记录并开始一个新的记录。按RET、backspace或移动点就是三个这样的示例。

In Emacs, this is not the case. Every action you take is recorded in the undo ring, and this includes the act of undoing something. Emacs will group certain commands together into one cohesive undo unit — like typing characters or repeating the same command many times in a row. Some events will always “seal” the undo record and start a new one. Pressing RET, backspace, or moving the point around are three such examples.

重复的撤消命令将撤消越来越多的事情，但如果您打破循环（例如通过移动或编辑文本），Emacs 将不会从您中断的位置恢复。相反，您刚刚撤消的项目会作为重做记录添加到撤消环中。这意味着当您再次撤消时，您实际上会撤消（重做）刚刚执行的操作，直到达到上次停止时的状态 - 然后 Emacs 将撤消缓冲区中的其余更改。

Repeated undo commands will undo more and more things but if you break the cycle – for instance by moving around or editing text – Emacs will not resume from where you left off. Instead, the items you just undid were added to the undo ring as redo records. That means when you undo again, you will actually undo (redo) the actions you just did until you get to the state you were at when you last stopped — then Emacs will undo the rest of the changes in your buffer.

这意味着丢失撤消历史记录几乎是不可能的，因为撤消操作本身就是一个可撤消的操作。这意味着您可以撤消一些事情 - 例如重写您正在编写的文档中的一个段落 - 只是后来才意识到，实际上，您更喜欢旧文本。在其他编辑器中，您撤消的更改将永远消失，因为它们具有线性撤消列表；在 Emacs 中，您只需撤消新编写的段落，直到 Emacs 将缓冲区返回到上次撤消之前的状态。

This means it’s next to impossible to lose undo history as the act of undoing is itself an undo-able action. That means you can undo a few things – say rewriting a paragraph in a document you’re writing – only to realize later on that, actually, you liked the old text better. In other editors your undone changes would be gone forever as they have linear undo lists; in Emacs you simply undo your newly-written paragraphs until Emacs returns your buffer to the state it was in before you did your last undo.

使困惑？没关系。我花了很长时间才明白这在实践中是如何运作的。由于使用撤消环不可能真正丢失任何数据，因此进行试验更容易；但请记住，只要您不断撤消命令，Emacs 就会不断撤消环中的操作。只有打破这个“撤消循环”，您才能重做已撤消的更改。打破这个循环的最简单方法就是简单地转移你的观点。

Confused? That’s okay. It took me a long time to understand how this would work out in practice. As it’s impossible to really lose any data with the undo ring, it’s easier to just experiment; but remember that Emacs will keep undoing things from the ring as long as you keep undoing commands one after another. Only by breaking this “undo cycle” will you be able to redo the undone changes. And the easiest way to break the cycle is by simply moving your point.

这是一个简单的例子。这并不是 Emacs 的撤消环实际保留撤消信息的方式——它比这更复杂——但我认为这种详细程度是不必要的。

Here’s a simple example. It’s not how Emacs’s undo ring actually retains undo information – it’s rather more complex than that – but I think that level of detail is unnecessary.

作为一名作家，我写了一些文字，然后又重写了一些文字，我的撤消环现在如下所示。该环应从上到下读取，每个撤消记录由箭头分隔，从最新到最旧。当到达 END 标记时，撤消环为空，无法进行更多撤消操作。

As a writer, I have written and then rewritten some text and my undo ring now looks like the one below. The ring is to be read top to bottom, with each undo record separated by the arrow, going from newest to oldest. When the END marker is reached, the undo ring is empty and no more undo actions are possible.

*“VI 是罗马数字 6”

-->“VI VI VI是野兽的编号”

-->结尾

* “VI is the Roman numeral for 6”

--> “VI VI VI is the number of the beast”

--> END

该撤消环中有两个撤消记录，每个记录都是一行文本。环的头部是星星，*。头始终指向最新的撤消记录。如果我用 撤消一次C-/，我的撤消环现在看起来像这样：

This undo ring has two undo records in it, each one a line of text. The head of the ring is the star, *. The head always points to the latest undo record. If I undo once with C-/, my undo ring now looks like this:

“VI 是罗马数字 6”

*“VI VI VI是野兽的编号”

-->结尾

“VI is the Roman numeral for 6”

* “VI VI VI is the number of the beast”

--> END

原来的引用仍然在撤消环中；事实上，它根本没有真正去任何地方（尽管缓冲区中的文本已更改为指向的*内容。）相反，我们已将标题 ( *) 移至另一个引用。如果我执行另一个撤消步骤，我将最终到达 END，现在我的环是空的。但我不会这样做，因为我会写另一句话：

The original quote is still in the undo ring; in fact, it hasn’t really gone anywhere at all (though the text in the buffer has changed to what * points at.) Instead, we’ve shifted the head (*) to the other quote. If I did another undo step, I would end up at END, and now my ring is empty. I’m not going to do that though as I will instead write another quote:

“VI是一个文本编辑器”

“VI is a text editor”

现在我的撤销环看起来像这样：

And now my undo ring looks like this:

*“VI是一个文本编辑器”

-->“VI 是罗马数字 6”

-->“VI VI VI是野兽的编号”

-->结尾

* “VI is a text editor”

--> “VI is the Roman numeral for 6”

--> “VI VI VI is the number of the beast”

--> END

撤销环的头部已更改为指向我刚刚输入的最新报价，但我撤销的旧报价仍然存在。如果我输入C-/，我将撤消最新的报价，并且之前撤消的报价将会重新出现。

The head of the undo ring has changed to point at the latest quote I just entered, but the old quote I undid is still there. If I type C-/, I will undo my latest quote and the one I undid before would reappear.

还困惑吗？
Still confused?

这很正常。这是一个很难“理解”的概念（也更难解释），但大多数 Emacs 初学者会随着时间的推移而掌握它。主要的一点是，打破撤销环并丢失信息几乎是不可能的——所以继续尝试吧。首先，您很可能只关心撤消最近的更改。

That’s normal. It’s a difficult concept to “get” (and much harder to explain) but most Emacs beginners will pick it up over time. The main point to take away is that it’s almost impossible to break the undo ring and lose information — so go ahead and experiment. Chances are, to begin with, you only care about undoing the most recent changes anyway.

顺便一提

您可以下载 Emacs 的替代撤消实现。一种流行的方法是撤消树。3

By the way

You can download alternative undo implementations for Emacs. A popular one is Undo Tree.3

窗口管理

Window Management

管理窗口是您必须掌握的另一项核心技能。老实说，尽管章节介绍说它相当复杂，但事实并非如此：您只需要学习几个键绑定。让它变得复杂——或者对某些人来说，完全令人恼火——首先是对窗口的依赖，以及如何习惯窗口概念。

Managing windows is another core skill you have to master. Honestly, despite the chapter introduction saying it was rather complex, the truth of the matter is it isn’t: there are only a few key bindings you need to learn. What makes it complex – or to some people, downright infuriating – is the reliance on windows in the first place, and how to get used to the windowing concept.

让我们看一下您需要了解的键绑定。

Let’s take a look at the key bindings you need to know about.

按键绑定 目的
C-x 0 删除活动窗口
C-x 1 删除其他窗口
C-x 2 下面的分割窗口
C-x 3 右分割窗口
C-x o 切换活动窗口

这五个键是您使用、分割和删除窗口所需的全部。还有更多命令，如下所示，但首先，您可以使用这五个命令。

These five keys are all you need to use, split and delete windows. There are more commands, as you’ll see below, but to start with, you can get by with these five commands.

撤消窗口更改

有时您想返回到过去的窗口配置。模式M-x winner-mode会记住您的窗口设置，并允许您分别使用 和 撤消和C-c <left>重做C-c <right>。

要永久启用获胜者模式：

M-x customize-option RET winner-mode RET

Undoing window changes

Sometimes you want to return to a past window configuration. The mode, M-x winner-mode, remembers your window settings and lets you undo and redo with C-c <left> and C-c <right>, respectively.

To enable Winner mode permanently:

M-x customize-option RET winner-mode RET

Emacs 将平铺窗口并通常确保每个新窗口的屏幕空间大约为分割窗口的一半。如果您只有一个窗口并且向右拆分，那么您现在有两个窗口，每个窗口拥有 50% 的份额。

Emacs will tile windows and generally ensure each new window is given roughly half the screen estate of the splitting window. If you have just one window and you split to the right, you now have two windows, each with a 50% share.

删除窗口
Deleting windows

如果您使用C-x 0，那么 Emacs 将删除活动窗口（该窗口始终是该点处于活动状态的窗口），如果您键入C-x 1，Emacs 将删除所有其他窗口。

If you use C-x 0, then Emacs will delete the active window – which is always the one where the point is active – and if you type C-x 1, Emacs will delete all other windows.

分割窗口
Splitting windows

窗口分别用 和 进行水平或垂直（或“下方”和“右侧”）C-x 2分割C-x 3。如果您有一台大显示器，您可能需要垂直分割，以便一次可以有多个可见的缓冲区；您甚至可能更喜欢额外的细分。我总是分成两个甚至四个窗口，排列在2x2网格中。

A window is split either horizontally or vertically (or “below” and “right”) with C-x 2 and C-x 3, respectively. If you have a large monitor, you may want to split vertically so you can have more than one buffer visible at a time; you may even prefer additional subdivisions. I always split into two or even four windows, arranged in a 2x2 grid.

最后，要在窗口之间移动，请使用命令C-x o。我发现重新绑定它很有用，M-o因为这是很常见的事情。将其添加到您的初始化文件中：

Finally, to move between windows use the command C-x o. I find it useful to rebind it to M-o as it’s such a common thing to do. Add this to your init file:

(global-set-key (kbd "M-o") 'other-window)
(global-set-key (kbd "M-o") 'other-window)

定向窗口选择

有些人更喜欢Emacs 附带的Windmove软件包，因为它可以让您在基本方向上移动，而不是循环浏览所有窗口。

您可以通过将其添加到init 文件来启用它：

(windmove-default-keybindings)

S-<left>现在，您可以通过按, S-<right>, S-<up>,来使用 Shift 键切换窗口S-<down>。

Directional window selection

Some people prefer the windmove package that ships with Emacs, as it lets you move in cardinal directions instead of cycling through all windows.

You can enable it by adding this to your init file:

(windmove-default-keybindings)

You can now switch windows with your shift key by pressing S-<left>, S-<right>, S-<up>, S-<down>.

使用其他 Windows

Working with Other Windows

一旦您习惯了拆分和删除窗口，您就可以通过对其他窗口进行操作来在此基础上进行扩展。也就是说，如果你想切换另一个窗口的缓冲区，你必须C-x o先到该窗口，然后使用C-x b更改缓冲区。这有点乏味，而且打乱了你的节奏。在这种情况下，另一个窗口是运行时紧邻当前窗口之后的窗口C-x o。

Once you’re comfortable splitting and deleting windows, you can build on that by acting on other windows. That is, if you want to switch another window’s buffer, you have to C-x o to the window, then use C-x b to change the buffer. It’s a bit tedious and it breaks your tempo. The other window in this case is the one immediately after the current one when you run C-x o.

按键绑定 目的
C-x 4 C-f 在另一个窗口中查找文件
C-x 4 d M-x dired在另一个窗口中打开
C-x 4 C-o 在另一个窗口中显示缓冲区
C-x 4 b 切换另一个窗口中的缓冲区
并使其成为活动窗口
C-x 4 0 杀死缓冲区和窗口
C-x 4 p 在另一个窗口中运行项目命令

这些命令是在其他窗口上操作时最有用的命令。还有更多 - 您可以用来C-x 4 C-h列出它们 - 但您不会经常使用它们。

These commands are the most useful ones for operating on other windows. There are a few more – you can use C-x 4 C-h to list them – but you won’t use them as often.

如果您仔细观察上表中的键绑定，您会发现C-x 4和之间的对称性C-x— 事实上，它们在绑定和用途上几乎相同。这并非巧合，对称性将帮助您记住命令。

If you look closely at the key bindings in the table above, you will see a symmetry between C-x 4 and C-x — indeed, they are almost identical in binding and purpose. This is no coincidence, and the symmetry will help you remember the commands.

框架管理

Frame Management

您可以创建框架（在其他程序和窗口管理器中称为窗口），如果您使用平铺窗口管理器或利用多显示器设置，您可能更喜欢这样做。请注意，框架也可以在终端 Emacs 中使用。

You can create frames – what are called windows in other programs and window managers – and you may prefer to do this if you use a tiling window manager or to take advantage of multi-monitor setups. Note that frames also work in terminal Emacs.

用于帧的前缀键是C-x 5。与 Windows 的前缀键 ( C-x 4) 一样，命令大多相同。

The prefix key used for frames is C-x 5. Like the prefix key for windows (C-x 4) the commands are mostly the same.

按键绑定 目的
C-x 5 2 创建一个新框架
C-x 5 b 在其他帧中切换缓冲区
C-x 5 0 删除活动帧
C-x 5 1 删除其他帧
C-x 5 C-f 在另一个框架中查找文件
C-x 5 p 在另一个框架中运行项目命令
C-x 5 d M-x dired在另一个框架中打开
C-x 5 C-o 在另一帧中显示缓冲区

切换具有多个帧的缓冲区是无缝的，如果缓冲区可见（它显示在窗口中的框架中），Emacs 将切换到缓冲区已经可见的正确帧。

Switching buffers with multiple frames is seamless, if a buffer is visible (it is displayed in a frame in a window) Emacs will switch to the right frame where the buffer is already visible.

是否选择使用框架取决于您。在 Emacs 中处理多个框架的机制有点尴尬，因为所有框架共享同一个 Emacs 会话——这有时是福是祸。我发现框架对于多显示器设置很有用，但在其他地方就没那么有用了。我发现，框架的实用性受到 Emacs 中已经非常出色的平铺窗口管理系统的限制。我唯一的建议是尝试一下，看看框架是否适合您的工作流程。

Whether you choose to use frames or not is up to you. The mechanics of dealing with multiple frames is slightly awkward in Emacs as all frames share the same Emacs session — which is sometimes a blessing or a curse. I find frames useful with multi-monitor setups, but not so much elsewhere. The usefulness of frames, I find, is limited by the already excellent tiling window management system present in Emacs. My only recommendation is to try it out and see if frames fit your workflow.

选项卡栏和选项卡线

Tab Bars and Tab Lines

关于 Emacs 的一个常见抱怨是它缺乏原生“选项卡栏”——就像网络浏览器和大多数其他编辑器中的选项卡栏一样——但在 Emacs 27 中，他们添加了不是一种而是两种不同的实现来解决两个常见问题。这是一个很长的时间，但实现和用户体验是健全的，并且以真正的 Emacs 风格，完全可以为第三方包作者和用户定制。

One common complaint about Emacs was its lack of a native “tab bar” – like the ones in web browsers and most other editors – but in Emacs 27 they added not one but two distinct implementations that solve two common problems. It’s a long time coming, but the implementation and user experience is sound and, in true Emacs fashion, utterly customizable to third-party package authors and users alike.

如果您没有使用 Emacs 27，您可以在包管理器中找到第三方实现：它们是真实事物的复制品，依靠 Emacs 渲染引擎中的一个怪癖来提供真实功能的外观。但是，如果您是那种喜欢看到一行选项卡的心理模型的人，那么您可能会发现这两种实现都很有用。

If you’re not using Emacs 27, you can find third-party implementations in the package manager: they are facsimiles of the real thing, relying on a quirk in the Emacs rendering engine to provide a semblance of the real feature. But, if you are the sort of person who prefers the mental model of seeing a row of tabs, then you will likely find either implementation useful.

颜色主题

如果您使用的是 Emacs 27 之前的主题，您可能会发现主题的配色方案并未扩展到控制选项卡栏和选项卡行模式的新界面。您可以通过键入 来自定义它们M-x customize-apropos-faces tab-。

Color Themes

If you’re using a theme that predates Emacs 27, you may find the color scheme of your theme does not extend to the new faces that govern the tab bar and tab line modes. You can customize them by typing M-x customize-apropos-faces tab-.

有两种新的选项卡模式，它们各自解决不同的问题。

There are two new tab modes, and they each solve different problems.

标签栏模式

Tab Bar Mode

选项卡栏按窗口配置对选项卡进行分组。在 Emacs 中，窗口配置是窗口的集合（大小、位置、缓冲区等），代表 Emacs 框架的布局。与 Emacs 中的大多数内容一样，窗口配置是可配置的，可以保存到磁盘、寄存器（稍后会详细介绍）或者现在保存到选项卡栏。

Tab Bars group tabs by window configurations. In Emacs, a window configuration is a collection of windows – size, location, the buffer, and so on – that represents a layout of your Emacs frame. Like most of things in Emacs, window configurations are configurable and can be saved to disk, to a register (but more on them much later) or indeed now to a tab bar.

在 IDE 中，这可能被称为工作区或项目。如果您经常发现自己在整个工作流程之间切换（可能是 ORG 模式议程和计划员以及电子邮件用于一件事，而另一个用于编码），那么您将拥有两种不同的窗口配置。选项卡栏模式可以轻松地将您的想法组织到持久的窗口配置中。

In an IDE this would be referred to as workspaces or projects, perhaps. If you often find yourself switching between entire workflows – maybe an ORG mode agenda and planner along with your email for one thing, and another for your coding – then you’d have two distinct window configurations. The Tab Bar mode makes it easy to organize your thoughts into persistent window configurations.

对于 Emacs 的一个常见抱怨（来自新用户或经验丰富的用户）是管理窗口的复杂性，因为分割系统和缓冲区出现的位置是不透明且难以理解的。

One common complaint about Emacs – from new or experienced users alike – is the complexity in managing the windows as the system of splitting and where buffers appear is opaque and hard to understand.

选项卡栏模式通过与我之前演示的帧、缓冲区和窗口管理命令非常相似的直观界面来解决这种复杂性。

Tab Bar Mode takes aim at that complexity with an intuitive interface very similar to the Frame, Buffer and Window Management commands I demonstrated earlier.

要启用标签栏模式，您可以自定义M-x customize-option RET tab-bar-mode；类型M-x tab-bar-mode;或者简单地调用下面的键绑定之一。

To enable tab bar mode you can customize M-x customize-option RET tab-bar-mode; type M-x tab-bar-mode; or simply invoke one of the key bindings below.

标签栏模式的前缀键是C-x t。

The prefix key for tab bar mode is C-x t.

按键绑定 目的
C-x t 2 创建一个新选项卡
C-x t 0 关闭当前选项卡
C-x t RET 按名称选择选项卡
C-x t o,C-<tab> 下一个选项卡
C-S-<tab> 上一个选项卡
C-x t r 重命名选项卡
C-x t m 将选项卡向右移动一位
C-x t p ... 在其他选项卡中运行项目命令
C-x t t 在其他选项卡中执行命令
C-x t 1 关闭所有其他选项卡
C-x t C-f,C-x t f 在其他选项卡中查找文件
C-x t b 切换到其他选项卡中的缓冲区
C-x t d 在其他选项卡中打开 Dired

与框架、窗口和缓冲区管理键绑定一样，选项卡栏绑定遵循相同的模式：影响其他选项卡的操作类似于创建新选项卡。

Like the frame, window, and buffer management key bindings, the tab bar bindings follow the same pattern: actions that affect other tabs is akin to creating a new tab.

新选项卡根据触发其创建的缓冲区以及此后的活动缓冲区来命名。您可以根据需要重命名它们并在选项卡栏上移动它们。如果您愿意，可以C-x t RET通过选项卡名称来选择选项卡；同样，您可以使用C-<tab>、C-S-<tab>、 或鼠标切换到下一个或上一个选项卡。

New tabs are named according to the buffer that triggered their creation, and the active buffer thereafter. You can rename and move them around the tab bar as you see fit. If you prefer, you can use C-x t RET to select tabs by their name; likewise, you can switch to the next or previous tabs with C-<tab>, C-S-<tab>, or the mouse.

如果您不喜欢看到选项卡栏本身，可以使用 隐藏它M-x customize-option RET tab-bar-show，并且仍然可以受益于选项卡栏的所有功能。

If you dislike seeing the tab bar itself, you can hide it with M-x customize-option RET tab-bar-show, and still benefit from all the capabilities of the tab bar.

有一些有用的命令未绑定到任何键。

There are a handful of useful commands not bound to any key.

命令 目的
M-x tab-list 显示交互式选项卡列表
M-x tab-undo 撤消每次调用的关闭选项卡
M-x tab-recent 切换到上次访问的选项卡

我认为如果您喜欢修剪整齐的窗口配置和一组简单的工具来管理它们，那么选项卡栏模式会很适合。通过包含常见的实用功能，例如查找文件；切换缓冲区；打开 dired 等。它们可以让您从现有的选项卡栏配置快速跳转到新的选项卡栏配置。将其与快速关闭、重命名或跳回的功能相结合，您可以像框架一样考虑选项卡：窗口及其状态的逻辑集合，但无需管理多个框架的麻烦。

I think tab bar mode shines if you prefer manicured window configurations and a simple set of tooling to manage them. By including common utility functions like finding a file; switching a buffer; opening dired, etc. they let you jump from an existing tab bar configuration to a new one quickly. Combine it with the ability to quickly close, rename or jump back and you can consider tabs like you would, say, frames: a logical collection of windows and their state, but without the hassle of managing multiple frames.

然而，窗口配置出现故障的情况仍然很常见：前面在窗口管理中我谈到了winner-mode一种撤消和重做最近窗口配置的方法。它对于选项卡栏来说几乎没有那么有用，因为它不理解特定于选项卡的窗口配置。相反，我建议您M-x tab-bar-history-mode启用M-x customize-option RET tab-bar-history-mode.

However, it’s not uncommon still for a window configuration to get out of order: earlier in Window Management I talked about winner-mode, a way of undoing and redoing recent window configurations. It’s not nearly as useful with tab bars as it does not understand tab-specific window configurations. Instead, I recommend you enable M-x tab-bar-history-mode with M-x customize-option RET tab-bar-history-mode.

选项卡栏历史记录模式管理窗口配置的选项卡特定历史记录。不幸的是，单步浏览历史的命令没有绑定到任何东西。下面的代码片段借用了M-x winner-mode默认使用的键绑定。如果您想同时使用两者，您应该选择自己的按键绑定4。

Tab bar history mode manages a tab-specific history of window configurations. Unfortunately the commands to step through the history is not bound to anything. The snippet below borrows the key bindings M-x winner-mode uses by default. If you want to use both, you should choose your own key bindings4.

将其添加到您的初始化文件中：

Add this to your init file:

(global-set-key (kbd "M-[") 'tab-bar-history-back)
(global-set-key (kbd "M-]") 'tab-bar-history-forward)
(global-set-key (kbd "M-[") 'tab-bar-history-back)
(global-set-key (kbd "M-]") 'tab-bar-history-forward)

现在，当选项卡的窗口配置（或其中一个窗口中的缓冲区）发生更改时，您可以向前或向后浏览该历史记录。

Now when a tab’s window configuration (or a buffer in one of the windows) changes you can walk forward or backward through that history.

对于大多数工作流程，窗口和选项卡栏管理就足以让 Emacs 满足您的日常需求。

For most workflows, window and tab bar management is all you need to tame Emacs for your day-to-day needs.

制表符行模式

Tab Line Mode

与选项卡栏模式不同，选项卡行模式的功能更类似于您在网络浏览器中找到的选项卡。与选项卡栏模式一样，其主要目的是将相关的内容分组在一起：默认情况下，选项卡行在启用时将列出先前在该窗口中打开的缓冲区。

Unlike tab bar mode, the tab line mode is feature more akin to the tabs you’ll find in a web browser. Like the tab bar mode, its primary purpose is to group related things together: by default the tab line will, when enabled, list buffers previously opened in that window.

要启用它，请输入M-x customize-option RET global-tab-line-mode;或者M-x global-tab-line-mode。

To enable it, type M-x customize-option RET global-tab-line-mode; or M-x global-tab-line-mode.

只有两个按键绑定值得学习。

There are only two key bindings worth learning.

按键绑定 目的
C-x <left> 选择前一个缓冲区
C-x <right> 选择下一个缓冲区

使用键绑定，您可以循环浏览与您调用它的窗口相关的缓冲区列表。默认情况下，这是最近缓冲区的列表，但您可以自定义它，M-x customize-option tab-line-tabs-function例如将其限制为相同主要模式的缓冲区。例如，对于在一个窗口中循环浏览一种类型的文件很有用。

Using the key bindings you can cycle through the list of buffers relevant to the window you call it from. By default that is a list of recent buffers, but you can customize that with M-x customize-option tab-line-tabs-function and, say, limit it to buffers of the same major mode. Useful for cycling through one type of file in one window, for instance.

元素运动

Elemental Movement

导航键

Navigation Keys

您（实际上，每个编辑器）可用的最基本的移动命令是不起眼的箭头键。它们按照您的预期工作，如果您是 Emacs 新手，我建议您使用它们，直到您学习更高级的移动命令。

The most elemental movement commands available to you – and indeed, to every editor – are the humble arrow keys. They work as you would expect, and if you’re new to Emacs, I recommend you use them until you learn the more advanced movement commands.

与其他编辑器一样，您可以将箭头键（写为<left>、<right>、<up>和<down>）与控制键结合起来按单词移动。同时，其他导航键（例如page up和page down）也可以在 Emacs 中使用。

As with other editors, you can combine the arrow keys – written as <left>, <right>, <up>, and <down> – with the control key to move by word. Simultaneously, the other navigation keys, like page up and page down, also work in Emacs.

按键绑定 目的
<left>, … 箭头键按字符移动
四个方向
C-<left>, … 如上所述，但通过文字
<insert> 插入钥匙。激活overwrite-mode
<delete> 删除键。删除后面的字符
观点
<prior>, Page up 和 Page down 上下移动
<next> 将近一页
<home>,<end> 移至行首或行尾

一旦您熟悉了 Emacs 的基础知识（处理缓冲区、分割和删除窗口、保存和打开文件），您就应该不再使用导航键。尽管它们很好地实现了它们的目的，但它们距离主行太远，并且将右手移离主行只是为了在屏幕上移动点是非常耗时的。

Once you’re comfortable with the basics of Emacs – handling buffers, splitting and deleting windows, saving and opening files – you should move away from using the navigation keys. Though they serve their purpose well, they are too far away from the home row, and moving your right hand away from the home row just to move the point around on the screen is time consuming.

顺便一提

向上/向下翻页按钮将向上或向下滚动一屏文本，保留 2 行文本作为上下文。您可以通过next-screen-context-lines直接在初始化文件中更改变量或使用 Emacs 的自定义界面来更改分页文本时的重叠量，如下所示： M-x customize-option，然后输入next-screen-context-lines。

By the way

The page up/down buttons will scroll up or down a screenful of text, retaining 2 lines of text for context. You can change the amount of overlap when you page through text by altering the variable next-screen-context-lines directly in your init file or by using Emacs’s customize interface, like so: M-x customize-option, then enter next-screen-context-lines.

如果您经常使用 bash 等 shell 或其他支持 GNU readline 的终端应用程序，那么这对您来说是个好消息：默认情况下，它们使用 Emacs 风格的键。尝试一下，M-f逐字前进。事实上，GNU readline 中存在数十个 Emacs 最常用的命令5，这意味着心理上下文切换是最小的，并且每个使用 readline 的终端程序都支持它们。

If you regularly use shells like bash or other GNU readline-enabled terminal applications, then good news for you: by default they use Emacs-style keys. Try it, M-f moves forward by word. In fact, dozens of Emacs’s most commonly-used commands5 exist in GNU readline, meaning the mental context switch is minimal and every terminal program that uses readline supports them.

按性格移动

Moving by Character

当您第一次遇到 Emacs 中的箭头键等效项时，它们会显得非常奇怪。很多人想知道为什么 Emacs 会绑定一个像将字符移动到 一样常见的动作C-f。事实上，如果您了解 Emacs，您几乎永远不会按字符移动。

The arrow key equivalents in Emacs will seem positively strange when you first encounter them. A lot of people wonder why Emacs would bind an action as common as moving forward a character to C-f. The fact is if you know Emacs, you’ll almost never move around by character.

按字符移动（也可以按行移动，因为从技术上讲，这是可以向上或向下移动的最小单位）是可以在缓冲区中进行的最小原子移动。角色的动作是为了技巧；如果您愿意的话，专为精密运动而设计。按字符在缓冲区中移动既低效又乏味；受键盘重复速度或打字速度的限制。这很慢，而且这种缓慢会随着我们花在移动上的时间和编辑文本的时间一样多而增加。仅当角色移动是最有效的可用命令时才应使用它。按单词移动固然很棒，但如果您想将 2 个字符移动到一个单词中，这将无济于事。

Moving by character – and also by line, as that is technically the smallest unit you can move up or down – is the smallest atomic movement you can make in a buffer. Character movement is for finesse; made for precision movement, if you like. Moving around a buffer by character is inefficient and tedious; limited by the speed of your keyboard’s repeat speed or how fast you can type it. That’s slow, and that slowness adds up as we often spend as much time moving around as we do editing text. You should only use character movement when it’s the most efficient command available. Moving by word is great, but that won’t help you if you want to move 2 characters into a word.

四个基本运动命令是：

The four basic movement commands are:

按键绑定 目的
C-f 按字符前进
C-b 按字符向后移动
C-p 移至上一行
C-n 移至下一行

正如您所看到的，从助记的角度来看，这些赋值是有意义的——p对于前一个，b对于后一个——并且所有的都绑定在C-修饰符下。

As you can see, mnemonically, the assignments make sense – p for previous, b for backwards – and all are bound under the C- modifier.

您可以将通用参数应用于字符键，它们将按您的预期工作。键入后C-8 C-f，您会将点向前移动八个字符。您甚至可以组合负参数来反转命令的方向 - 这对于移动键可能没有多大意义，但某些命令带有前进和后退命令。大多数人只朝着一个方向行动——即前进——而否定论点是改变这一方向的唯一方法。

You can apply universal arguments to the character keys and they will work as you expect. Type C-8 C-f and you will move the point forward eight characters. You can even combine the negative argument to reverse the direction of the command — that may not make much sense with movement keys, but some commands come with a forward and backward command. Most act in just in one direction – forward, that is – and the negative argument is the only way to change this direction.

当您了解 Emacs 的其他移动命令如何工作时，学习 Emacs 自己的移动命令（而不是使用键盘右侧的导航键）是有意义的。我看到经验丰富的 Emacs 用户执行精心设计的命令序列来执行有趣且复杂的操作，结果却停下来将右手移离主行并按字符移动点。在某些时候，您会意识到它有多么不和谐（以及它对您的速度的影响有多大），并切换到 Emacs 自己的命令。

Learning Emacs’s own movement commands (as opposed to using the navigation keys to the right on your keyboard) makes sense when you look at how Emacs’s other movement commands work. I see experienced Emacs users execute choreographed sequences of commands to do interesting and complex actions only to stop dead in their tracks to move their right hand away from the home row and move the point around by character. At some point you will realize how jarring (and how much it affects your speed) it is and switch to Emacs’s own commands.

沿线移动

Moving by Line

<home>和键<end>分别将您的点移动到行的开头和结尾，Emacs 的等效项是C-a和C-e。和 的C-a行为与和C-e完全相同（事实上，两组键都绑定到同一个命令），但我将在下一章中介绍行的定义。<home><end>

The <home> and <end> keys move your point to the beginning and end of a line, respectively, and the Emacs equivalents are C-a and C-e. Both C-a and C-e behave exactly the same as <home> and <end> (indeed, both sets of keys are bound to the same command) but I cover the definition of a line in the next chapter.

按键绑定 目的
C-a 将点移至行首
C-e 将点移动到行尾
M-m 将点移动到第一个非空白
这一行的字符

最后一个命令M-m是纯金粉。当您键入 时M-m，该点将移动到行首并向前移动，直到遇到非空白字符；因此，如果您在缩进的代码行上并且想要更改标识符bar：

The last command, M-m, is pure gold dust. When you type M-m, the point will move to the beginning of the line and move forward until it encounters a non-whitespace character; ergo, if you’re on an indented line of code and you want to change the identifier bar:

def foo():
    bar = 42-!-
def foo():
    bar = 42-!-

输入后M-m：

After you type M-m:

def foo():
    -!-bar = 42
def foo():
    -!-bar = 42

如果您所在的行没有缩进，则该命令将直接转到该行的开头。

If you’re on a line without indentation, the command will simply go to the beginning of the line.

屏幕、逻辑和视线

Screen, Logical and Visual Lines

默认情况下，Emacs 会将长行换行到窗口的右边缘，但这提出了一个重要问题：换行时，行在哪里开始和结束？

Emacs will, by default, wrap long lines to the right edge of the window, but that raises an important question: where does a line begin and end when it wraps?

不幸的是，答案需要一些解释，以及术语？嗯，很混乱：

The answer, unfortunately, requires a bit of explaining, and the terminology? Well, it’s jumbled:

视线
Visual lines

视线定义为您所看到的。如果您打开一个文件，并且缓冲区中的一条长行跨越了三个换行，那么您将拥有三个可视行，其中每行都被 Emacs 视为单独且不同的行，即使底层文件只有一个。

A visual line is defined as What You See. If you open a file and a long line spans three wrapped lines in your buffer, then you have three visual lines, each of which is treated as a separate and distinct line by Emacs, even if the underlying file has just one.

逻辑线
Logical lines

逻辑线与视线相反。逻辑行由缓冲区的内容控制，而不是其他任何东西；无论是否自动换行，文件中的一长行在 Emacs 中都被视为一长行。

A logical line is the opposite of a visual line. Logical lines are governed by the content of the buffer and nothing else; word wrapped or not, one long line in a file is treated as one long line in Emacs.

网线
Screen lines

在 Emacs 文档的某些部分中，您可能会看到术语“屏幕线”与“逻辑线”结合使用。屏幕线与视线相同，并且这些术语可以互换使用。

In some parts of Emacs’s documentation, you may see the term screen lines used in conjunction with logical lines. A screen line is identical to a visual line and the terms are used interchangeably.

从历史上看，当 Emacs 换行很长的一行时，用于向上或向下移动一行的C-p命令C-n并没有改变。一条长线（称为逻辑线）包裹成三行（称为视觉线）仍算作单（逻辑）线，用于逐行向上或向下移动；最终的结果是你无法使用直线命令通过视线移动。这是否是正确的道路确实是一个两极分化的问题。你要么喜欢它……要么你改变了 Emacs。

Historically, when Emacs wrapped a long line the C-p and C-n commands for moving up or down a line didn’t change. A long line (called a logical line) wrapped into three lines (called visual lines) would still count as a single (logical) line for moving up or down by line; the end result is that you couldn’t use the line commands to move by visual lines. Whether it was The Right Way was a polarizing thing, indeed. You either loved it… or you altered Emacs.

大多数人都改变了 Emacs。最终的结果是，在最新版本的 Emacs 中，上一行/下一行命令通过视线移动。您可以通过键入 切换到旧行为M-x customize-option RET line-move-visual。

And most people altered Emacs. The end result is today, in the latest versions of Emacs, the previous/next line commands move by visual lines. You can switch to the old behavior by typing M-x customize-option RET line-move-visual.

视觉线模式的添加增加了复杂性，这是一种基于视觉线概念并具有附加功能的次要模式。

Adding to the complexity is the addition of Visual Line Mode, a minor mode that builds on the concept of visual lines with additional functionality.

视觉换行模式按字边界换行，从而产生“更干净”的换行，就像您在传统文字处理器中看到的那样。次要模式还将禁用边缘指示器。

Visual Line Mode wraps by word boundary resulting in “cleaner” line wrapping like what you’d see in a traditional word processor. The minor mode will also disable the fringe indicators.

此外，视觉线模式用视觉等效命令取代了许多移动和编辑命令。C-p并且C-n将像在默认 Emacs 安装中启用该选项一样运行line-move-visual。此外，像移动到行首和行尾（使用C-a和C-e）这样的命令现在适用于视觉行而不是逻辑行。 Kill 命令（绑定到C-k，但我们还没有介绍该命令！）也适用于可视线。

Additionally, Visual Line Mode replaces a number of movement and editing commands with visual equivalents. C-p and C-n will behave as they do in default Emacs installations with the line-move-visual option enabled. Furthermore, commands like moving to the beginning and end of a line (with C-a and C-e) now work on visual lines instead of logical lines. The kill command (bound to C-k, but we haven’t covered that command yet!) will also work on visual lines.

如果您想要这种行为（我鼓励您尝试一下，看看它是否适合您的工作流程），您可以通过M-x customize-option RET global-visual-line-mode输入全局或在缓冲区中一次启用它M-x visual-line-mode。

If you want this behavior – and I encourage you to try it out and see if it fits your workflow – you can enable it globally with M-x customize-option RET global-visual-line-mode or in a buffer at a time by typing M-x visual-line-mode.

如果您不想自动换行怎么办？
What if you don’t want word wrapping?

您可以使用 切换自动换行（在 Emacs 中称为截断）M-x toggle-truncate-lines。

You can toggle word wrapping – called truncation in Emacs – with M-x toggle-truncate-lines.

显示行号和列号

Displaying Line and Column Numbers

行号的显示是一些人离不开的工作流程。 Emacs 26 引入了一种以高性能方式显示和渲染行号的新方法。该功能已被调用，您可以使用或M-x display-line-numbers-mode永久启用它。M-x customize-option RET global-display-line-numbers-modeM-x customize-option RET display-line-numbers-mode

The display of line numbers is a workflow that some people cannot live without. Emacs 26 introduces a new method of displaying and rendering line numbers in a performant way. The feature is called M-x display-line-numbers-mode and you can enable it permanently with M-x customize-option RET global-display-line-numbers-mode or M-x customize-option RET display-line-numbers-mode.

正如您所期望的，该功能是可扩展的，并且附带了许多您可以使用M-x customize-group RET display-line-numbers.相对数和绝对数都是可能的，并且您可以配置许多显示选项，以帮助计算和执行行上的命令。

The feature is extensible, as you’d expect, and comes with a number of default line number counting methods that you can configure with M-x customize-group RET display-line-numbers. Both relative and absolute numbers are possible, and you can configure a number of display options that aid in counting and executing commands on lines.

如果您只想查看当前所在的行号，M-x line-number-mode则可以启用。它显示您的点在模式行中所在的当前行。同样，还有M-x column-number-mode显示当前行点的列偏移是否开启。

If you only want to see the current line number you’re on, you can enable M-x line-number-mode instead. It displays the current line your point is on in the mode line. Likewise, there is also M-x column-number-mode to show the column offset of the current line point is on.

通过文字移动

Moving by Word

就像角色的动作一样，通过语言来移动几乎是相同的。向后和向前字符的助记符相同，仅将C-修饰符替换为M-。

Like character movement, moving by words is almost identical; the mnemonics are the same for backward and forward character, replacing only the C- modifier with M-.

按键绑定 目的
M-f 按字前进
M-b 按单词向后移动

如果您使用过其他编辑器，等效的箭头键是C-<left>和C-<right>，正如我之前提到的，它们也可以在 Emacs 中使用。在 Emacs 中，文字移动在幕后相当复杂，文字移动的确切行为由您使用的主要模式决定。

If you’ve used other editors, the equivalent arrow keys are C-<left> and C-<right>, and as I mentioned earlier they are also available to you in Emacs. In Emacs, word movement is rather complex behind the scenes, and the exact behavior of word movement is dictated by the major mode you’re using.

什么构成一个词？

What Constitutes a Word?

什么是词？简单地将其视为由空格分隔的一系列字符是大多数人的想法 - 因此也期望 - 但在 Emacs 中，事实要复杂得多。

What is a word? Simply thinking of it as a series of characters separated by whitespace is what most people think – and therefore expect – but in Emacs the truth is a lot more complicated.

Emacs 中的模式编写器对缓冲区中文本的性质做出假设。您将写入的内容与您将在 中写入的内容M-x text-mode不同，并且处理方式M-x python-mode也不同。因此，模式作者需要一种方式来表示text-mode句点 ' .' 是 Python 中的句子分隔符和属性分隔符。

Mode writers in Emacs make assumptions about the nature of the text in the buffer. What you would write in M-x text-mode is different – and treated differently – from what you’d write in M-x python-mode. So, mode authors need a way of saying that in text-mode the period ‘.’ is a sentence separator and an attribute separator in Python.

事实上，每个字符（可打印字符，包括 Unicode 代码点）都由模式作者在将字符映射到特定语法含义的注册表中直接或间接赋予含义。这个注册表称为语法表，我将多次提到这个概念，以帮助您了解它如何影响移动和编辑，但除此之外，只有 elisp 黑客和模式编写者感兴趣。

Indeed, every character – printable characters, including Unicode code points – are given a meaning by the mode author, directly or indirectly, in a registry that maps the characters to a particular syntactic meaning. This registry is called a syntax table, a concept that I will refer back to several times to help you understand how it affects movement and editing, but is otherwise only of interest to elisp hackers and mode writers.

语法表记录诸如注释使用哪些字符？或哪些字符组成一个单词？尽管从视图中看不到，但它影响了 Emacs 的每个部分。

The syntax table keeps track of things like What characters are used for comments? or What characters make up a word? and, although obscured from view, affects every part of Emacs.

语法表单独决定了作为语法单元的单词（或符号、标点符号、注释等）的构成。因此，当您在屏幕上移动点时，它会根据语法表forward-word以及管理和 的一般规则移动backward-word。

The syntax table alone decides the makeup of a word (or symbol, punctuation, comment, etc.) as a syntactic unit. So when you move the point around on the screen, it moves according to the syntax table and the general rules governing forward-word and backward-word.

语法表

每个编辑器都有一个相当于 Emacs 的语法表，但 Emacs 与其他编辑器的不同之处在于您可以检查和更改语法表，这反过来会影响您在调用某些命令时点在屏幕上移动的方式。

您可以通过键入来查看当前缓冲区的语法表C-h s- 加载可能需要一段时间。在其中您将看到字符及其指定的语法类的人类可读版本。

The syntax table

Every editor has an equivalent of Emacs’s syntax table, but what sets Emacs apart from other editors is that you can inspect and change the syntax table, which in turn will affect how your point moves across the screen when you invoke certain commands.

You can view your current buffer’s syntax table by typing C-h s — it may take a while to load. In it you will see a human readable version of the characters and their assigned syntax class.

运动不对称

Movement Asymmetry

关于单词移动，您还应该了解的一件事是它不是对称的：不能保证先输入M-f后输入M-b（理论上它应该带您回到原来的位置）。 Emacs 会巧妙地跳过您移动的方向（向前或向后）遇到的符号和标点符号。

One more thing you should know about word movement is that it’s not symmetric: typing M-f followed by M-b – in theory it should take you back to your old position – is not guaranteed. Emacs will cleverly skip symbols and punctuation it encounters in the direction (forward or backward) you’re moving.

考虑一下当您键入M-f向前移动一个单词时会发生什么：

Consider what happens when you type M-f to move forward one word:

Before: Hello, -!-World.

After: Hello, World-!-.
Before: Hello, -!-World.

After: Hello, World-!-.

由于点 , 后面的字符-!-都是字母字符，因此命令一词的行为如您所期望的。现在看看如果我们将点移动到行尾M-b并键入向后移动一个单词会发生什么：

Because the characters succeeding the point, -!-, are all alphabetical characters, the word command behaves as you would expect. Now look at what happens if we move the point to the end of the line and type M-b to move backward one word:

Before: Hello, World.-!-

After: Hello, -!-World.
Before: Hello, World.-!-

After: Hello, -!-World.

word 命令足够聪明，可以意识到，虽然句号不是单词字符，但它应该简单地忽略它，因为标点符号之前有一个单词。键入后键入不会让我们回到原来的示例：M-fM-b

The word command is smart enough to realize that, although a period is not a word character, it should simply ignore it as there is a word immediately before the punctuation. Typing M-f after we type M-b will not take us back to our original example:

Before: Hello, -!-World.

After: Hello, World-!-.
Before: Hello, -!-World.

After: Hello, World-!-.

这强化了我的观点：单词命令不是对称的。这需要一些时间来适应。 Emacs 通常会忽略紧跟在您行进方向上的点之后的非单词字符。例如，我们跳过了句点 ，.因为它是一个非单词字符，并且是该点向后移动时遇到的第一个字符。这种行为的原因很简单：如果 Emacs不这样做，那么单词命令在文本和代码中遇到的每个非单词字符都将被视为自己的单词并结束移动命令。

This reinforces my point that word commands are not symmetric. That will take a bit of getting used to. Emacs will generally ignore non-word characters immediately following the point in the direction you are travelling. For instance, we skipped over the period, ., because it was a non-word character and it was the first character the point would encounter going backwards. The reason for this behavior is simple: if Emacs didn’t do this, then every non-word character the word commands would encounter, in both text and code, would count as a word of its own and end the movement command.

这是一个更极端的例子——但你很可能在源代码中遇到这个例子：

Here is a more extreme example — but one you may well encounter in source code:

print(add_two(num_table[10]))-!-
print(add_two(num_table[10]))-!-

上面的点位于该行的末尾，如果您键入M-b并向后移动一个单词，您最终会到达10：

The point above is at the end of the line and if you type M-b and move backward one word, you end up right before 10:

print(add_two(num_table[-!-10]))
print(add_two(num_table[-!-10]))

这是因为，和以前一样，当且仅当在遇到单词字符之前遇到符号和标点符号时，Emacs才会忽略它们。再次前进并不会让我们回到行尾，因为我们已经在一句话了：

This is because, as before, Emacs ignores symbols and punctuation if, and only if, it encounters them before it has encountered a word character. Moving forward again does not take us back to the end of the line as we are already at a word:

print(add_two(num_table[10-!-]))
print(add_two(num_table[10-!-]))

所以，您可能想知道为什么这是一件好事。对于初学者来说，您可以按照原始命令M-b来M-d删除数字10，并且由于不对称性，您不会删除]))符号（但稍后会详细介绍删除命令。）另一个原因是，考虑这样是没有意义的一个仅由空格分隔的单词——它引发了太多问题。如果连续有很多空格以及标点符号怎么办？当您必须像大多数源代码一样导航符号和文本的组合时，Emacs 的行为是完全明智的；继续点击M-b，您可以向后移动连续的文本单词，但您可以方便地跳过在行进方向上遇到的任何符号。人们感到困惑的一件事是不对称性。这些规则看起来毫无意义 — 但现在您知道了 Emacs 的运行方式，它的行为应该更有意义。

So, you might be wondering why this is a good thing. For starters, you can follow up the original M-b with M-d to kill the number 10 and because of the asymmetry you don’t kill the ])) symbols (but much more on the kill commands later.) Another reason is that it just does not make sense to think of a word as separated by just white spaces — it raises too many questions. What if there are many whitespaces in a row and what about punctuation and symbols? When you have to navigate a mix of symbols and text, like most source code is, Emacs’s behavior is perfectly sensible; keep tapping M-b and you move back consecutive words of text but you conveniently skip any symbols you encounter in the direction of travel. The one thing people find confusing is the asymmetry; the rules seem insensible — but now that you know how Emacs moves, its behavior should make a lot more sense.

子词和超词移动

Sub- and Superword Movement

如果您使用 编辑大量代码CamelCase，您可能希望移动和编辑命令将每个子单词（由大写字母界定）视为其自己的单词。同时，您可能想要相反的情况：Emacs 的单词移动通常命令的文本written_like_this（但这又完全取决于语法表和主要模式的变幻莫测）将其视为三个不同的单词（written、like和this），而不是仅仅一个。

If you edit a lot of code with CamelCase, you may want your movement and edit commands to treat each sub-word – delineated by a capitalized letter – as its own word. Simultaneously, you may want the opposite: that text written_like_this which Emacs’s word movement commands usually – but again this is all down to the syntax table and vagaries of the major mode – treat as three distinct words (written, like, and this) instead of just one.

命令 目的
M-x subword-mode 治疗的次要模式CamelCase
作为不同的词
M-x superword-mode 治疗的次要模式snake_case
作为一个词

全局小调模式

两者都有可用的全局模式，您可以通过键入以下内容来启用它们：

M-x customize-option global-subword-mode
M-x customize-option global-superword-mode

Global minor modes

There are global modes available for both and you can enable them by typing:

M-x customize-option global-subword-mode
M-x customize-option global-superword-mode

当您启用 时M-x subword-mode，您将启用对 中每个单独的大写单词进行操作的特殊移动、转置和终止命令CamelCase。如果您用使用 的语言编写大量代码CamelCase，您会发现子字模式很有用。

When you enable M-x subword-mode, you enable special movement, transpose and kill commands that operate on each individual, capitalized word in CamelCase. If you write a lot of code in languages that use CamelCase, you’ll find subword mode useful.

眼镜模式

有一种异想天开的次要模式 ，M-x glasses-mode它在视觉上（它不会改变您的缓冲区文本）将CamelCase单词分隔成Camel_Case。

Glasses mode

There is a whimsical minor mode, M-x glasses-mode, that visually (it does not alter your buffer text) separates CamelCase words into Camel_Case.

superword 命令M-x superword-mode类似，但作用相反：它重新连接符号（通常但不总是包含下划线），因此它们被视为单词的一部分。请注意，该命令并不完美。主要模式作者决定字符 like_或.应该属于哪个语法类，如果他们不将字符 like 设置_为符号，则该命令将不起作用。

The superword command, M-x superword-mode, is similar but does the opposite: it rewires symbols (which usually, but not always, include the underscore) so they’re considered part of a word. Note that this command is not perfect. Major mode authors decide what syntax class a character like _ or . should fall under, and if they don’t set a character like _ to be a symbol, the command will not work.

通过 S 表达式移动

Moving by S-Expressions

也许 Emacs 中最有用但未充分利用的功能是通过s-表达式（或只是sexp）进行移动的能力。这个神秘的名称值得解释一下：它是一个 LISP 术语，如今涵盖了广泛的操作命令平衡的表达。

Perhaps the most useful – but underused – feature in Emacs is the ability to move by s-expression (or just sexp.) The cryptic name deserves an explanation: it’s a LISP term that, today, covers a wide range of commands that operate on balanced expressions.

平衡表达通常包括：

Balanced expressions typically include:

弦乐
Strings

编程语言是字符串的主要示例，字符串是平衡表达式，因为它们以"or开头和结尾'。

Programming languages being the primary example of strings, which are balanced expressions because they begin and end with " or '.

括号
Brackets

在大多数主要模式中，括号被认为是平衡的，因为它们定义了开始和结束字符：[and ]、(and )、{and }、<and >。

In most major modes brackets are considered balanced as they have defined open and close characters: [ and ], ( and ), { and }, < and >.

平衡表达式可以跨越多行——例如多行字符串——Emacs 知道这一点。

Balanced expressions can span multiple lines – multi-line strings for instance – and Emacs knows this.

特定字符集是否定义平衡表达式将取决于您的主要模式，而主要模式又将在我之前讨论的语法表中定义这些特征。

Whether a particular set of characters defines a balanced expression will depend on your major mode, and the major mode in turn will define these characteristics in the syntax table I talked about earlier.

与单词和字符命令一样，这些命令遵循与以前相同的助记符，但具有不同的修饰符。这次是C-M-.

Like the word and character commands, these follow the same mnemonic as before but with a different modifier. This time it’s C-M-.

按键绑定 目的
C-M-f 通过 s 表达式向前移动
C-M-b 通过 s 表达式向后移动

这些命令的用处怎么强调都不为过。考虑这个 Python 示例；当您按下时查看该点移动的位置C-M-f

The usefulness of these commands cannot be overstated. Consider this Python example; look where the point moves when you press C-M-f

d = -!-{
    'Hello': 'World',
    'Foo': 'Bar',
}
d = -!-{
    'Hello': 'World',
    'Foo': 'Bar',
}

后

After

d = {
    'Hello': 'World',
    'Foo': 'Bar',
}-!-
d = {
    'Hello': 'World',
    'Foo': 'Bar',
}-!-

Emacs 知道{and }inpython-mode是一个平衡表达式（因为语法表），因此将{and}视为平衡表达式，并在您键入 时立即移动到结束大括号C-M-f。

Emacs knows that { and } in python-mode is a balanced expression – because of the syntax table – and thus treats { and } as a balanced expression, and immediately moves to the end brace when you type C-M-f.

一旦你开始用平衡表达式来思考代码，你就会发现它们无处不在。您不仅会发现它们在 LISP 中很有用，而且在 LISP 中也很有用。几乎所有主要模式都充满了平衡表达式 - 作为额外的好处，当您在“不平衡”表达式（例如常规文本）上调用 s-expr 移动命令时，它们的作用就像单词命令一样。

Once you start thinking about code in terms of balanced expressions, you’ll see them everywhere. It’s not just in LISP that you’ll find them useful; almost all major modes are full of balanced expressions — and as an added bonus, the s-expr movement commands act like the word commands when you invoke them on “unbalanced” expressions such as regular text.

学习如何使用这些命令绝对是至关重要的。

It’s absolutely vital that you learn how to use these commands.

向下和向上列表

Down and Up List

按键绑定 目的
C-M-d 向下移动到列表中
C-M-u 从列表中上移

与 s-表达式 移动命令一样，列表命令原本是为 LISP 设计的，但已经在该语言之外找到了生命。当您按 时C-M-d，该点将跳转到该点当前所在位置之前最接近的括号平衡表达式：

Like the s-expression movement commands, the list commands were meant for LISP but have found a life outside that language. When you press C-M-d, the point will jump into the nearest balanced expression of parentheses ahead of where the point currently is:

Before:

-!-result = foo(bar())

After:

result = foo(-!-bar())
Before:

-!-result = foo(bar())

After:

result = foo(-!-bar())

该点在最近的平衡表达式内移动。为此，该点将跳跃任意距离，重复调用将深入嵌套结构，反之C-M-u将返回。与单词命令一样，列表命令也不对称；向上走将带你升一级，但将你的观点留在开头字符上：

The point moves inside the nearest balanced expression. To do this, the point will jump an arbitrary distance, and repeated calls will go deeper into nested structures and conversely C-M-u will go back up. Like the word commands, the list commands are not symmetric; going up will take you up one level but leave your point at the opening character:

Before:

result = foo(bar(-!-))

After:

result = foo(bar-!-())
Before:

result = foo(bar(-!-))

After:

result = foo(bar-!-())

脱离弦乐

在较新版本的 Emacs 中，您可以使用C-M-uinside 字符串跳转到开头引号。

Moving out of strings

In newer versions of Emacs, you can use C-M-u inside a string to jump to the opening quote.

就其本身而言，这些命令只不过是跳入和跳出“列表”表达式，但要意识到将此行为与另一个命令kill-sexp6结合起来会杀死点前面的平衡表达式 - 因此键入C-M-u和C-M-kforkill-sexp将向上移动并杀死你刚才的平衡表达：

On their own, the commands do little more than jump in and out of “list” expressions, but realize that combining this behavior with another command, kill-sexp6, will kill the balanced expression in front of the point — so typing C-M-u and C-M-k for kill-sexp will move up and kill the balanced expression you were just in:

; Before:
(+ (* -!-5 2) (- 10 10))

; After going up one level with C-M-u:
(+ -!-(* 5 2) (- 10 10))

; After killing the s-expression with C-M-k:
(+ -!- (- 10 10))
; Before:
(+ (* -!-5 2) (- 10 10))

; After going up one level with C-M-u:
(+ -!-(* 5 2) (- 10 10))

; After killing the s-expression with C-M-k:
(+ -!- (- 10 10))

我一直在使用这个功能；它是 Emacs 的隐藏瑰宝之一，即使您不使用 LISP 编程，它也能让您提高工作效率。例如，像 Python 这样的语言到处都使用括号：用于字典、元组和列表。将列表命令与 结合起来C-M-k，您可以轻松重构大量代码并保持节奏，因为大多数适用于平衡表达式的命令都绑定到修饰符C-M-。

I use this functionality all the time; it’s one of Emacs’s hidden gems that will make you very productive, even if you don’t program in LISP. For instance, languages like Python use parentheses all over the place: for dictionaries, for tuples, and for lists. Combine the list commands with C-M-k and you can refactor large swathes of code easily and maintain your tempo because most commands that work on balanced expressions are bound to the C-M- modifier.

因为C-M-d跳转到点后的下一个“列表”表达式 - 无论它位于缓冲区中的哪个位置 - 它也是移动的强大工具。就像 Emacs 中的所有事情一样，认识到命令的潜力并将其放入工作记忆中以便您使用它是很困难的，但回报是值得的。

Because C-M-d jumps into the next “list” expression following point – regardless of where it is in the buffer – it’s a powerful tool for moving around as well. Like everything in Emacs, realizing the potential of a command and committing it to working memory so you use it is hard, but the reward is well worth it.

前进和后退列表

Forward and Backward List

两个更有用的导航辅助工具是C-M-n和C-M-p。它们移动到同一嵌套级别中的下一个或上一个列表表达式。

Two more useful navigational aids are C-M-n and C-M-p. They move to the next or the previous list expression in the same nested level.

按键绑定 目的
C-M-n 前进到下一个列表
C-M-p 向后移动到上一个列表

例如，当您C-M-n重复键入时会发生以下情况：

For instance, here’s what happens when you type C-M-n repeatedly:

(+ -!-(* 5 2) (- 10 10))

(+ (* 5 2)-!- (- 10 10))

(+ (* 5 2) -!-(- 10 10))

(+ (* 5 2) (- 10 10)-!-)
(+ -!-(* 5 2) (- 10 10))

(+ (* 5 2)-!- (- 10 10))

(+ (* 5 2) -!-(- 10 10))

(+ (* 5 2) (- 10 10)-!-)

正如您所看到的，它从一个表达式移动到下一个表达式，这包括平衡表达式的开头和结尾。再次键入C-M-n会产生错误：我们已到达此嵌套级别的平衡表达式的末尾。如果我们键入C-M-u以在列表中向上移动：

As you can see, it moves from one expression to the next, and this includes the beginning and end of the balanced expression. Typing C-M-n again yields an error: we have reached the end of balanced expressions at this nested level. If we type C-M-u to move up the list:

-!-(+ (* 5 2) (- 10 10))
-!-(+ (* 5 2) (- 10 10))

现在，我们移出嵌套表达式并进入其父表达式。随后的调用将C-M-n我们带到平衡表达式的末尾：

Now, we move out of the nested expression and into its parent. A subsequent call to C-M-n takes us to the end of the balanced expression:

(+ (* 5 2) (- 10 10))-!-
(+ (* 5 2) (- 10 10))-!-

对于 LISP，这些命令是无价的。嵌套括号表示层次结构，因此 LISP 黑客需要一套有效的工具来向上、向下和围绕平衡表达式移动。对于所有其他编程语言，该实用程序完全取决于您遇到平衡表达式的频率。在大多数语言中——比如 C、Java、Python 或 JavaScript——它们都非常有用；这是在大括号或方括号等平衡表达式之间移动的一种优雅方式。

For LISP, the commands are invaluable. Nested parentheses indicate hierarchy so LISP hackers require an efficient set of tools to move up, down and around balanced expressions. For all other programming languages, the utility depends entirely on how frequently you encounter balanced expressions. In most languages – like C, Java, Python, or JavaScript – they are very useful; it’s an elegant way of moving between some balanced expressions like curly or square braces.

其他移动命令

Other Movement Commands

我认为按字符、线条、单词和 s 表达式移动是最重要的移动命令。它们在各种编辑任务中具有最大的实用性 - 特别是编程和文本编辑 - 但有一些移动命令最适合特定任务 - 它们是否对您有用完全取决于您所做的事情。

I consider moving by character, line, word and s-expression to be the most important movement commands. They have the greatest utility across a wide range of editing tasks – specifically programming and text editing – but there are some movement commands that are best suited for specific tasks — and whether or not they are useful to you depends entirely on what you do.

按段落移动

Moving by Paragraph

按键绑定 目的
M-} 前进至段落末尾
M-{ 向后移动到段落开头

段落的定义取决于您询问的对象和您的个人风格，Emacs 会尽力满足其中的大多数要求。段落命令本身依赖于一组定义段落开头和结尾的变量：

The definition of a paragraph depends on who you ask and your personal style, and Emacs tries to cater to most of them. The paragraph commands themselves rely on a set of variables that define the beginning and end of a paragraph:

变量名 目的
paragraph-start 定义段落的开头
使用大的正则表达式
paragraph-separate 将段落分隔符定义为
正则表达式
use-hard-newlines 通过命令设置
M-x use-hard-newlines并定义
硬换行符是否定义
段落

我建议您描述变量（使用C-h v）以更好地了解 Emacs 的段落系统如何工作。特别是变量paragraph-start是一堆正则表达式，试图为每个人做所有事情。默认情况下，当您使用M-}和 时M-{，Emacs 会将换行符分隔的文本块视为段落。

I recommend you describe the variables (using C-h v) to get a better picture of how Emacs’s paragraph system works. The paragraph-start variable in particular is a jumble of regular expressions that tries to do everything for everyone. By default, when you use M-} and M-{, Emacs will treat newline-delimited blocks of text as a paragraph.

您可以更改段落命令的行为，以便通过运行前导空格来标记新段落的开头M-x paragraph-indent-minor-mode。

You can alter the behavior of the paragraph commands so leading spaces mark the beginning of a new paragraph by running M-x paragraph-indent-minor-mode.

段落命令在编程模式中也很有用。许多开发人员将代码行组合在一起，并用空行将它们彼此分开，使它们成为段落命令的理想候选者。

The paragraph commands are useful in programming modes also. A lot of developers group lines of code together and separate them from each other with blank lines making them an ideal candidate for the paragraph commands.

按句子移动

Moving by Sentence

句子命令与行命令共享对称性，将C-修饰符替换为M-：

The sentence commands share symmetry with the line commands, replacing the C- modifier with M-:

按键绑定 目的
M-a 移至句首
M-e 移至句末

与段落一样，句子的定义是一种不同的内部风格，但 Emacs 假设您的句子以句点后的两个空格开始：

Like a paragraph, the definition of a sentence is a house style that varies, but Emacs assumes you begin your sentences with two whitespaces after a period:

This is one sentence. This is another.
This is one sentence. This is another.

您可以通过自定义（使用M-x customize-option）以下变量来更改此行为：

You can alter this behavior by customizing (with M-x customize-option) the following variables:

变量名 目的
sentence-end-double-space 非零表示单个空格
不结束一个句子。
sentence-end-without-period 非零表示一个句子将
不带句号结束。
sentence-end-without-space 一串字符
结束一个句子而不
后面需要空格。

您最有可能自定义的一项是sentence-end-double-space.

The one you are most likely to customize is sentence-end-double-space.

由德芬搬家

Moving by Defun

defun这个词是 LISP 的另一个奥秘，代表定义函数——在 Emacs 中，你会在命令作用于函数的地方看到它。

The word defun is another piece of LISP arcana that stands for define function — and in Emacs you will see it in places where commands act on functions.

与句子和行命令一样，defun 命令C-M-用作修饰符：

Like the sentence and line commands, the defun commands use C-M- as their modifier:

按键绑定 目的
C-M-a 移至 defun 开头
C-M-e 移至 defun 末尾

defun 命令移动到函数点所在的逻辑开头或结尾。我必须指出，函数实际上是一个相当松散的术语。它不一定是函数，但在编程模式中它通常是函数、类或两者；对于其他模式，它可能会执行其他操作 - 例如，在 reStructuredText 中，它将跳转到节或章节的开头和结尾。

The defun commands move to the logical beginning or end of the function point is in. I must point out that function is really a rather loose term. It doesn’t have to be a function but in programming modes it’s usually functions, classes, or both; for other modes, it might do other things — in reStructuredText, for instance, it will jump to the beginning and end of a section or chapter.

如果您想快速更改编程语言中函数的名称或函数参数，那么移到 defun 的开头确实非常有用。

Moving to the beginning of defun is really useful if you want to, say, quickly change the name or function arguments of a function in a programming language.

考虑点的位置：

Consider the location of point:

int addtwo(int x)
{
  return x + 2-!-;
}
int addtwo(int x)
{
  return x + 2-!-;
}

按下C-M-a将带我们到 defun 的开头addtwo：

Pressing C-M-a will take us to the beginning of defun, addtwo:

-!-int addtwo(int x)
{
  return x + 2;
}
-!-int addtwo(int x)
{
  return x + 2;
}

随后的调用C-M-a将带您越来越深入地“沿着链向上”到达父块，或者如果您位于根目录，则到达文件的顶部。

Subsequent calls to C-M-a will take you further and further “up the chain” to a parent block, perhaps, or the top of the file if you are at the root.

按页移动

Moving by Pages

Emacs 中的页面仅与现实生活中的页面概念无关。在 Emacs 中，页面是由变量中定义的字符分隔的任何内容page-delimiter，默认情况下是控制代码^L— 更广为人知的名称是 ASCII 控制代码form feed。您不太可能使用这些命令，因此我不担心记住它们。

A page in Emacs is only tangentially related to the real-life concept of a page. In Emacs, a page is anything delimited by the character defined in the variable page-delimiter, which by default is the control code ^L — better known as the ASCII control code form feed. It is unlikely that you will ever use these commands, so I would not worry about memorizing them.

在某些 LISP 圈子中，按页面对事物进行分组是很常见的，并且由于 Emacs 与 LISP 社区有着密切的联系，因此它附带了一系列与页面交互的命令。

In some LISP circles, it is common to group things by pages and as Emacs has close ties to the LISP community it comes with a battery of commands to interact with pages.

按键绑定 目的
C-x ] 向前移动一页
C-x [ 向后移动一页

发现页面命令

以下是查找页面命令的一种方法：（C-h a对于M-x apropos-command），然后搜索以page$查找以单词“page”结尾的所有命令。

知道如何向 Emacs 提出正确的问题——使用 apropos 或描述系统——是精通 Emacs 的基石。

Discovering the page commands

Here’s one way to find page commands: C-h a (for M-x apropos-command), then search for page$ to find all commands ending with the word “page.”

Knowing how to ask Emacs the right questions – using apropos or the describe system – is the cornerstone of Emacs mastery.

滚动

Scrolling

与箭头键一样，<prior>和<next>命令（分别为Pg. Up和Pg. Down）都有自己的 Emacs 等效项，但 Emacs 的滚动机制非常不同，以至于有些人觉得它令人沮丧。这是因为 Emacs 将滚动几乎全屏，其中全屏是该窗口中可见的行数。为了帮助您滚动时保持连续性，Emacs 将保留两到三行（由变量 控制next-screen-context-lines），这样您就不会忘记自己所在的位置。

Like the arrow keys, the <prior> and <next> commands (Pg. Up and Pg. Down respectively) have their own Emacs equivalents, but Emacs’s scrolling mechanism is different enough that some people find it frustrating. That’s because Emacs will scroll by nearly full screens, where a full screen is the number of lines visible in that window. To help with continuity when you scroll, Emacs will retain two or three lines (as governed by the variable next-screen-context-lines) so you don’t lose track of where you are.

按键绑定 目的
C-v 向下滚动接近全屏
M-v 向上滚动接近全屏
C-M-v 向下滚动另一个窗口
C-M-S-v 向上滚动另一个窗口

C-v其M-v工作方式与导航键<prior>和相同<next>。

C-v and M-v work the same way as the navigational keys <prior> and <next>.

奇怪的是滚动另一个窗口的两个命令。这是一个非常有用的命令。我几乎总是使用多个窗口，并且能够滚动另一个窗口（包含帮助缓冲区、日志文件，甚至另一个源代码文件）对我来说是很常见的事情。

The odd ones out are the two commands that scroll the other window. It’s a surprisingly useful command. I almost always work with multiple windows and being able to scroll another window – containing a help buffer, or a log file, or even another source code file – is a common thing for me to do.

大多数编辑器都缺乏此功能；相反，你必须：

Most editors lack this functionality; instead you have to:

使用鼠标
Use the mouse

使用鼠标在窗口上移动，最后使用滚轮上下滚动，或单击并按<prior>和<next>。

With your mouse, move over the window, and finally use the scroll wheel to scroll up and down, or click and press <prior> and <next>.

使用键盘
Use the keyboard

切换到另一个分割窗口或选项卡，使用<prior>或<next>上下滚动。

Switch to the other split window or tab, use <prior> or <next> to scroll up and down.

在 Emacs 中，您可以使用其他窗口滚动命令。

In Emacs, you can use the other window scroll commands.

我不C-M-S-v经常使用。我发现使用C-M-- C-M-v负参数键入来反转滚动方向比键入更容易C-M-S-v。后一个命令需要特别灵巧的手指操作，如果滚动得太远，则必须交换手指位置才能键入C-M-v。使用C-M--起来要容易得多C-M-v。

I don’t use C-M-S-v often. I find it easier to type C-M-- C-M-v to reverse the direction of the scroll with a negative argument than typing C-M-S-v. The latter command requires a particularly dexterous finger maneuver and if you scroll too far, you have to swap finger positions so you can type C-M-v. It’s far easier to use C-M-- and C-M-v.

保持节奏

请注意，负参数命令C-M--可以方便地绑定到与 相同的修饰键C-M-v。正如我在有关普遍论证的章节中所解释的那样，这并非巧合。通过将参数命令绑定到所有主要修饰符组合，您不必在命令之间扭曲手指即可为命令添加参数前缀。

Maintaining tempo

Notice that the negative argument command, C-M--, is conveniently bound to the same modifier keys as C-M-v. Like I explained in the chapter on universal arguments, this is no coincidence. By binding the argument commands to all major modifier combinations, you don’t have to contort your fingers between commands to prefix a command with an argument.

您还可以水平滚动 — 或者用 Emacs 的说法左右滚动：

You can also scroll horizontally — or just left and right in Emacs parlance:

按键绑定 目的
C-x < 向左滚动
C-<next> 向左滚动
C-<prior> 向右滚动
C-x > 向右滚动

如果您编辑大量行很长的文本文件（也许是 CSV 文件），您可能会发现首先使用M-x toggle-truncate-lines.除非你真的需要它们，否则我不会费心去记住水平滚动命令。

If you edit a lot of text files with very long lines – CSV files, perhaps – you may find it useful to first disable word wrapping (or line truncation as it’s known in Emacs) with M-x toggle-truncate-lines. I would not bother memorizing the horizontal scrolling commands unless you really need them.

当然，您仍然可以使用鼠标滚轮进行滚动，但它是否在终端中工作将取决于您的系统。

You can, of course, still use the mouse wheel to scroll, though whether it works in the terminal or not will depend on your system.

另外两个命令对于移动很有用，即能够转到缓冲区的开头和结尾：

Two more commands are useful for moving around, namely the ability to go to the beginning and end of the buffer:

按键绑定 目的
M-< 移动到缓冲区的开头
M-> 移动到缓冲区末尾

当您移动到缓冲区的开头或结尾时，Emacs 会在您原来的位置放置一个标记（一个不可见的位置标记），以便您可以返回到原来的位置。例如，如果您键入M-<要跳转到缓冲区的开头，则可以键入C-u C-<SPC>返回。C-u正如您所记得的，这是普遍的论点；在这种情况下，它会设置一个标志，以便当您键入时C-<SPC>Emacs 会将其解释为跳转到最后一个标记。该标记及其在 Emacs 中的实用性是我稍后将讨论的主题。

When you move to the beginning or end of the buffer, Emacs will place the mark – an invisible location marker – where you came from, so you can return to your old position. For instance, if you type M-< to jump to the beginning of the buffer, you can type C-u C-<SPC> to go back. C-u, as you remember, is the universal argument; in this case, it sets a flag so that when you type C-<SPC> Emacs will interpret that to mean jump to the last mark. The mark, and its utility in Emacs, is a topic I will discuss a little bit later.

书签和寄存器

Bookmarks and Registers

Emacs 中的书签与 Web 浏览器中的书签的工作方式相同，但明显的例外是支持更广泛的来源。这使得 Emacs 的书签系统足够灵活，您可以为文件、M-x dired目录、M-x man页面、Org 模式、DocView（包括 PDF 文件）和信息手册页添加书签。由于 Emacs 的 TRAMP 系统，因此还可以为远程文件和目录添加书签以便快速访问。

Bookmarks in Emacs work identically to the ones in your web browser but with the notable exception of supporting a wider variety of sources. That makes Emacs’s bookmarking system flexible enough for you to bookmark files, M-x dired directories, M-x man pages, Org mode, DocView (including PDF files), and info manual pages. Because of Emacs’s TRAMP system, it is therefore also possible to bookmark remote files and directories for speedy access.

Emacs 中的书签是永久的，这意味着它们会自动保存到~/.emacs.d/名为bookmarks.

Bookmarks in Emacs are permanent, meaning they are automatically saved to a bookmark file in ~/.emacs.d/ called bookmarks.

书签文件

该变量bookmark-default-file决定 Emacs 存储书签的位置。该文件是纯文本（实际上是 elisp s 表达式），这意味着可以手动编辑它（如果您绝对必须），或者如果您定期从多台计算机添加或删除书签，则可以合并文件。

Bookmark file

The variable bookmark-default-file determines where Emacs stores your bookmarks. The file is plain text (elisp s-expressions, actually) meaning it is possible to edit it manually (if you absolutely must) or merge the files if you regularly add or remove bookmarks from multiple machines.

按键绑定 目的
C-x r m 设置书签
C-x r l 列出书签
C-x r b 跳转至书签

书签是跳转到常用文件或目录的一种非常有效的方法；如果您想经常查看 Emacs 手册中的某些部分，它也很有用。由于 Emacs 的统一性质（缓冲区），这三者可以从同一书签列表中无缝存储和调用。最重要的是，与 Emacs 的所有东西一样，书签系统足够灵活，elisp 黑客可以轻松地使用自定义处理程序对其进行扩展。

Bookmarks are a very efficient way of jumping to frequently-used files or directories; it is also useful if there are sections of Emacs’s manual that you want to return to frequently. And because of the unified nature of Emacs – buffers – the three are seamlessly stored and recalled from the same list of bookmarks. And best of all, like all things Emacs, the bookmark system is flexible enough that elisp hackers can easily extend it with custom handlers.

然而，寄存器是不同的；它们是硬币的另一面——书签是永久性的，而寄存器是暂时性的。寄存器是一种单字符存储和调用机制，适用于多种类型的数据，包括：

Registers, however, are different; they are the flip side of the coin — where bookmarks are permanent, registers are transient. A register is a single-character store-and-recall mechanism for several types of data, including:

窗口配置和框架集
Window configurations and framesets

您可以存储和调用窗口配置的布局，尽管我认为有更好的工具（例如我在Window Management和Tab Bar ModeM-x winner-mode中谈到的）来完成这项工作。

框架集与窗口配置相同，但保存有关 Emacs 框架的信息。

You can store and recall the layout of your window configuration, though I would argue there are much better tools (such as M-x winner-mode I talked about in Window Management, and Tab Bar Mode) for the job.

Framesets are identical to window configurations but hold information about Emacs’s frames instead.

积分
Points

点的位置是您可以存储在寄存器中的另一件事。如果您习惯于其他 IDE 或编辑器中的基于行的书签，那么这些是 Emacs 中最接近的等效项。不幸的是，按键绑定（如下所示）削弱了它们的实用性。

The location of point is another thing you can store in a register. If you are used to line-based bookmarks from other IDEs or editors, these are the closest equivalents in Emacs. Unfortunately, the key bindings (as you will see below) diminish their usefulness.

数字和文字
Numbers and text

纯文本也可存储；如果您想插入多于一段文本，从而使杀戮环成为不太理想的候选者，这一点特别有用。您还可以存储数字，但文本和数字之间的唯一区别是能够在包含数字的寄存器上使用简单的算术（加法）。

Plain text is also storable; that is particularly useful if you want to insert more than one piece of text, making the kill ring a less ideal candidate. You can also store numbers, though the only distinction between text and number is the ability to use simple arithmetic (addition) on a register containing a number.

按键绑定 目的
C-x r n 将号码存储在寄存器中
C-x r s 将区域存储在寄存器中
C-x r SPC 将点存储在寄存器中
C-x r + 寄存器中的数字递增
C-x r j 跳转至注册
C-x r i 插入寄存器内容
C-x r w 将窗口配置存储在寄存器中
C-x r f 将框架集存储在寄存器中

寄存器只是一个字符。当您想要存储或调用某些内容时，系统会要求您输入单个字符进行查询。在 Emacs 24.4 之前，你没有真正的方法知道寄存器包含什么（除非你有很好的记忆力），但现在 Emacs 会在register-preview-delay几秒钟（默认 1 秒）后弹出一个预览窗口。

A register is a single character only. When you want to store or recall something, you are asked for a single character to query. Before Emacs 24.4, you had no real way of knowing what the registers contained (unless you had a good memory, that is) but now Emacs pops up a preview window after register-preview-delay seconds (default 1 second).

C-x r s是我最常使用的。它将区域存储在寄存器中——简单而有用——并C-x r i在指定位置插入寄存器的内容。一个重要的注意事项C-x r i是，在 Emacs 24.4 之前，它会将您的点放在插入文本的开头，而不是像(yank) 那样放在后面C-y。现在，这一点在 Emacs 24.4 中发生了变化，但对于早期版本的 Emacs，您必须给它一个前缀参数 ( C-u C-x r i) 以将点放在后面。

C-x r s is the one I use most frequently. It stores the region in a register – simple and useful – and C-x r i which inserts the content of a register at point. One important note about C-x r i is that, prior to Emacs 24.4, it would put your point at the beginning of the inserted text and not after, like C-y (yank) would. That is now changed in Emacs 24.4 but for earlier versions of Emacs you must give it a prefix argument (C-u C-x r i) to place the point after.

您可以使用 存储点位置C-x r SPC，但要跳转到该位置，您必须使用C-x r j;可以说C-x r i应该在这里做正确的事情，如果寄存器存储了一个点，则跳转到该点。相反，Emacs 会插入内部点位置，这对任何人都没有用处。

You can store the point location with C-x r SPC, but to jump to it you must use C-x r j; arguably C-x r i should Do The Right Thing here and jump to the point if the register stores a point. Instead, Emacs inserts the internal point location which is not useful at all to anyone.

框架集和窗口配置都是可存储的，但我自己从不使用它们。M-x winner-mode正如我之前提到的，有更好的软件包。

Both framesets and window configurations are storable but I never use them myself. There are better packages out there like M-x winner-mode as I talked about earlier.

要存储数字，请将点放在其前面并键入C-x r n。要增加它prefix-numeric-value（默认为1），请键入C-x r +并增加它任意数量，给它一个数字参数（和一个负数来减少。）您可以使用 调用一个数字寄存器C-x r i。

To store a number, place the point before it and type C-x r n. To increment it by prefix-numeric-value (default 1), type C-x r + and to increment it by an arbitrary amount, give it a numeric argument (and a negative one to decrement.) You can recall a number register with C-x r i.

寄存器和书签都很有用，它们有两个不同的用途。我会专注于记住书签命令，因为它们更有可能是您每天使用的东西。

Both registers and bookmarks are useful and they serve two different purposes. I would focus on memorizing the bookmark commands as they are more likely something you use daily.

选择和地区

Selections and Regions

选择文本是一个常见的操作，但在 Emacs 的信息文档和描述系统中，它被称为“区域”。正如我在点和标记中提到的，区域边界由点和标记组成。

Selecting text is a common action, but in Emacs’s info documentation and describe system it’s referred to as the region. As I mentioned in The Point and Mark, a region boundary is made up of the point and the mark.

其他编辑器很少或根本不区分区域的开头和结尾，但在 Emacs 中，这种区分相当重要。区域始终定义为点和标记之间的连续文本块。

Other editors make little or no distinction between the beginning and end of the region but in Emacs that distinction is rather important. The region is always defined as the contiguous block of text between the point and the mark.

要进行视觉演示，请在 Emacs 中尝试此操作：按C-<SPC>在回显区域中，将出现一条消息“Mark Set”。现在，使用箭头键或我之前介绍的其他移动命令在缓冲区周围移动您的点，并观察该区域的变化，因为它现在已被激活。再次按下C-<SPC>- 或通用的摆脱麻烦命令C-g- 可停用该区域。请注意，区域始终定义为点的标记，无论点是否位于标记之前。因此，此功能类似于您在按住shift箭头键并四处移动时在其他编辑器中看到的功能。

For a visual demonstration, try this in Emacs: press C-<SPC> In the echo area, a message will appear saying “Mark Set.” Now, move your point around the buffer – with the arrow keys or the other movement commands I introduced earlier – and watch as the region changes because it is now activated. Press C-<SPC> again – or the universal get-out-of-trouble command C-g – to deactivate the region. Note that the region is always defined as the mark to the point, whether the point comes before the mark or not. This functionality is thus similar to what you see in other editors when you hold down shift and move around with the arrow keys.

因此，当您进行视觉选择时，您正在使用 Emacs 的瞬态标记模式，也称为 TMM。 TMM 在 Emacs 历史上的出现比您想象的要晚得多。事实上，它最近才默认开启。

Therefore, when you make visual selections, you are using Emacs’s Transient Mark Mode, also known as TMM. TMM came about much later in Emacs’s history than you might think; in fact, it was only recently switched on by default.

那么TMM之前发生了什么？好吧，对于初学者来说，你根本没有视觉突出显示- 所以你必须记住你在哪里留下了标记。而且许多命令根本不了解诸如区域之类的事情。像这样的简单命令M-x replace-string会在缓冲区中进行简单的字符串替换，从缓冲区的起点到缓冲区的末尾，没有例外。因此，如果您想修改缓冲区的特定部分，则必须使用 Emacs 神秘的缩小命令，将缓冲区的可见内容缩小到您希望命令执行的内容。可以想象，这对初学者学习 Emacs 没有帮助。

So what came before TMM? Well, for starters, you didn’t have visual highlighting at all — so you had to remember where you left the mark. And a lot of the commands didn’t know about things like regions at all. Simple commands like M-x replace-string that does a simple string replacement in a buffer worked from the point to the end of the buffer, no exceptions. So if you wanted to modify particular parts of a buffer, you had to use Emacs’s cryptic narrowing commands that shrink the visible content of a buffer to what you wanted the command to act on. As you can imagine, that didn’t help beginners learn Emacs.

因此，今天您不必担心区域缩小（除了专门编辑之外的任何事情），也不必记住标记的位置，因为 TMM 会向您显示区域。

So, today you don’t have to worry about region narrowing (for anything except specialized editing), nor do you have to memorize the location of the mark as TMM will show you the region.

然而，TMM 和 Emacs 的区域系统的结合并不完美。 Emacs 中的标记不仅仅针对区域。它是在缓冲区中跳转的重要工具，因为一些让您离开当前位置的命令会在标记环上留下标记（实际上是面包屑痕迹），您可以稍后返回。一个例子是M-<and M->– 用于跳转到缓冲区开头和结尾的命令 – 它们都在跳转之前标记您的旧位置，以便您稍后可以通过键入返回到旧位置C-u C-<SPC>。

However, the union of TMM and Emacs’s region system is not perfect. The mark in Emacs is not just for the region.
