It’s an important tool for jumping around in a buffer as some commands that whisk you away from your current location will leave a mark (a breadcrumb trail, effectively) on the mark ring that you can return to later. One example would be M-< and M-> – the commands for jumping to the beginning and end of the buffer – they both mark your old position before they jump so you can later return to your old position by typing C-u C-<SPC>.

标记环

与撤消环一样，标记环包含您放置在缓冲区中的所有标记 - 两者都是直接使用标记命令，例如C-<SPC>;以及间接地，来自M-<和 之类的命令M->。还有用于跨缓冲区边界工作的命令的全局标记环。

您可以判断标记环何时发生变化，因为文本标记集（或其变体）出现在回波区域中。

The mark ring

Like the undo ring, the mark ring contains all the marks you have placed in a buffer — both directly, using mark commands like C-<SPC>; and indirectly, from commands like M-< and M->. There is also the global mark ring for commands that work across buffer boundaries.

You can tell when the mark ring has changed because the text Mark set (or a variation thereof) appears in your echo area.

因此，该命令C-<SPC>将设置标记，并且在启用 TMM 的情况下，当您四处移动点时，它还会激活区域突出显示。这意味着，如果您只想设置标记以便稍后返回（使用C-u C-<SPC>），则必须按C-<SPC> C-<SPC>— 一次设置标记，再按一次停用该区域。另一个问题是， Emacs 中一些对区域进行操作的命令（文本替换、将区域中的文本更改为大写等）即使该区域未激活也能正常工作，因为 Emacs 不会检查该区域是否处于活动状态（只是你使用的是 TMM。）

And because of this, the command C-<SPC> will set the mark and with TMM enabled it also activates the region highlighting when you move the point around. That means if you just want to set the mark just so you can return to it later (with C-u C-<SPC>), you have to press C-<SPC> C-<SPC> — once to set the mark, and once more to deactivate the region. Another gotcha is that some commands in Emacs that operate on regions – text replace, changing text to uppercase in a region, and so on – work just fine even if the region isn’t activated as Emacs will not check if the region is active (just that you are using TMM.)

以下是激活选择并跳转到标记所需的按键。如果您是 Emacs 新手，请随意使用 Shift 选择键，直到您熟悉 Emacs 自己的选择机制为止。

Here are the keys needed to activate selection and jump to the mark. If you are new to Emacs, feel free to use the shift selection keys until you are comfortable with Emacs’s own selection mechanism.

按键绑定 目的
C-<SPC> 设置标记并切换区域
C-u C-<SPC> 跳转到目标并重复调用
进一步回到标记环
S+<left>, … 与其他编辑器类似的 Shift 选择
C-x C-x 交换点和标记并重新激活
您最后一个地区

该C-x C-x命令（称为exchange-point-and-mark）很有趣。它从点（缓冲区中当前位置）以及标记所在的位置重新激活区域；然后，它交换点和标记位置。如果您想重新激活最后一个区域或只是想交换标记和点的位置，则此命令特别有用。如果您想要编辑标记或点附近的文本，或者只是想重新激活最后一个标记和点之间的区域，则交换点和标记非常有用。

The C-x C-x command (called exchange-point-and-mark) is interesting. It reactivates the region from point – which is your current location in the buffer – and wherever the mark is; then, it swaps the point and mark positions. This command is especially useful if you want to reactivate the last region or if you simply want to swap the position of mark and point. Exchanging the point and mark is useful if you want to edit text near the mark or point or if you simply want to reactivate the region between your last mark and point.

最后让我们列出一些需要记住的简单规则：

Let’s finish with a list of simple rules to remember:

  1. 区域是由点和标记界定的连续块。
  2. A region is a contiguous block bounded by the point and mark.
  3. 您可以使用 激活一个区域C-<SPC>，这会设置标记，然后激活该区域（如果您使用 TMM，那么您应该这样做！）。再次按下C-<SPC>可停用该区域。
  4. You activate a region with C-<SPC>, which sets the mark then activates the region (if you use TMM, and you should!). Pressing C-<SPC> again deactivates the region.
  5. 当您四处移动时，活动区域会跟随该点，但当您使用非移动命令时，活动区域会中断。
  6. An active region follows the point as you move around but breaks when you use a non-movement command.
  7. 该标记有双重用途，即作为信标，您可以使用 来返回C-u C-<SPC>，甚至可以使用“重复呼叫”设置C-<SPC>为C-u C-<SPC>越来越远地返回标记环。
  8. The mark serves a dual purpose as a beacon you can return to with C-u C-<SPC>, even one you set with C-<SPC> Repeat calls to C-u C-<SPC> go further and further back the mark ring.
  9. 交换点和标记会C-x C-x重新激活该区域并切换您的点和标记。
  10. Exchanging the point and mark with C-x C-x re-activates the region and switches your point and mark around.
  11. 一些 Emacs 命令并不关心该区域是否实际上处于活动状态并且无论如何都可以工作（所以要小心）。
  12. Some Emacs commands don’t care if the region isn’t actually active and work anyway (so be careful).

一如既往，我鼓励您及时学习 Emacs 自己的命令，但如果您不知所措，可以使用鼠标单击拖动选择或使用箭头键选择S+<arrow key>。

As always, I encourage you to learn Emacs’s own commands in time but if you are overwhelmed, you can use the mouse to click-drag selections or use the arrow key selection with S+<arrow key>.

选择兼容模式

Selection Compatibility Modes

为了轻松过渡到 Emacs，您可以启用多种帮助程序模式来模仿其他编辑器的行为。 Emacs 现在默认启用其中一两个，作为 Emacs 现代化的一部分。我个人的建议是从您所知道的开始，随着您提高 Emacs 技能，慢慢摆脱兼容性模式。

To ease the transition to Emacs, there are several helper modes you can enable to mimic the behavior of other editors. Emacs enables one or two of them by default now as part of their drive to modernize Emacs. My personal recommendation is to start off with what you know and slowly wean yourself off the compatibility modes as you improve your Emacs skills.

M-x delete-selection-mode
M-x delete-selection-mode

当该区域处于活动状态并且您在缓冲区中键入文本时，Emacs 将首先删除所选文本。这种行为模仿了大多数其他编辑器。

要启用（或禁用）它，请使用自定义界面：

M-x customize-option RET delete-selection-mode

When the region is active and you type text into the buffer, Emacs will delete the selected text first. This behavior mimics most other editors.

To enable (or disable) it, use the customize interface:

M-x customize-option RET delete-selection-mode
shift-select-mode（变量，默认启用）
shift-select-mode (variable, enabled by default)

移动运动键（包括箭头键等传统导航键和 Emacs 自己的命令）激活该区域并将其沿您移动的方向延伸。

班次选择的工作方式与使用 设置标记不同C-<SPC>。当您移动选择某个区域时，任何未移​​动的移动命令都会停用该区域。与 一样delete-selection-mode，此功能模仿其他编辑器中的行为。

例如，S-<left>、S-<right>等将一次区域选择一个字符，并且C-S-f会执行相同的操作，但使用 Emacs 自己的移动命令。

要禁用（或启用）它，请使用自定义界面：

M-x customize-option RET shift-select-mode

Shifted motion keys – both traditional navigation keys like the arrow keys and Emacs’s own commands – activate the region and extend it in the direction you are moving.

The shift selection works differently from setting the mark with C-<SPC>. When you shift select a region, any non-shifted movement command will deactivate the region. Like delete-selection-mode, this functionality mimics the behavior in other editors.

For instance, S-<left>, S-<right>, etc. will region select one character at a time, and C-S-f will do the same but with Emacs’s own movement commands.

To disable (or enable) it, use the customize interface:

M-x customize-option RET shift-select-mode
M-x cua-mode
M-x cua-mode

也许，与 Emacs 的选择和剪贴板系统最根本的不同是 CUA 模式。以 IBM 的Common User Access命名，cua-mode允许您使用C-z、C-x、C-c、 和C-v来撤消、剪切、复制和粘贴，就像在其他程序中一样。

由于 CUA 模式与 Emacs 自身的前缀键绑定C-x和C-c冲突，所以 CUA 模式默认是禁用的。如果启用它，前缀键C-x和C-c会继续工作，但会产生轻微的副作用和额外的限制：

  1. 要在活动区域​​中键入前缀C-x或，您必须快速连续双击前缀键（例如）。C-cC-x C-x
  2. 要键入前缀键C-x或C-c后跟另一个键，您必须快速连续键入它们，否则将触发剪贴板命令。
  3. 或者，对于第 1 点和第 2 点，您可以键入带有修饰符的前缀键S-：C-S-xreplacementC-x和C-S-creplacement C-c。

CUA 模式是影响生活质量的功能之一，它决定了某些人是否会采用 Emacs。如果您是其中之一，请务必启用它！随着时间的推移，您可以随时戒掉 CUA 键，或者只是忍受我提到的副作用。

要启用（或禁用）它，请使用自定义界面：

M-x customize-option RET cua-mode

Probably, the most radical departure from Emacs’s selection and clipboard system is CUA mode. Named after IBM’s Common User Access, cua-mode lets you use C-z, C-x, C-c, and C-v to undo, cut, copy and paste like you would in other programs.

Because CUA mode and Emacs’s own prefix key bindings C-x and C-c conflict, CUA mode is disabled by default. If you enable it, the prefix keys C-x and C-c continue to work but with minor side effects and additional constraints:

  1. To type the prefixes C-x or C-c with an active region, you must double tap the prefix key in rapid succession (e.g., C-x C-x).
  2. To type the prefix key C-x or C-c followed by another key, you must type them in rapid succession or you will trigger a clipboard command.
  3. Alternatively, to points 1 and 2, you can type the prefix key with the S- modifier: C-S-x replacing C-x and C-S-c replacing C-c.

CUA mode is one of those quality of life features that will make or break Emacs adoption for some people. If you’re one of them, by all means enable it! You can always wean yourself off the CUA keys over time or simply live with the side effects I mentioned.

To enable (or disable) it, use the customize interface:

M-x customize-option RET cua-mode

我个人的建议是学习 Emacs 自己的区域命令（稍后会详细介绍），因为 Emacs 从未围绕 CUA 模式的理念进行设计。7话虽如此，消除进入壁垒（这是 Emacs 维护者正在努力的事情）对于新 Emacs 用户来说在短期内更为重要。

My personal recommendation is to learn Emacs’s own region commands (and more on that shortly) as Emacs was never designed around the idea of CUA mode.7 Having said that, eliminating barriers to entry – and this is something the Emacs maintainers are working on – is more important in the shorter term for a new Emacs user.

设置标记

Setting the Mark

我已经向您展示了如何使用箭头键 ( )交互地激活标记，但 Emacs 有许多可作用于句法单元的标记命令，您可能还记得之前的内容，例如单词、s 表达式和段落。S+<arrow key>C-<SPC>

I have shown you how to activate the mark interactively with the arrow keys (S+<arrow key>) and C-<SPC> but Emacs has a host of mark commands that work on syntactic units which, as you may recall from earlier, are things like words, s-expressions and paragraphs.

设置标记C-<SPC>很有用，但使用起来很麻烦。您必须设置标记，移动到所需位置，然后运行命令。更糟糕的是，它会打乱你的节奏。

Setting the mark with C-<SPC> is useful but it is cumbersome to use. You have to set the mark, move to your desired location, and then run your command. Worse, it breaks your tempo.

如果您想进行精确选择，最好使用 Emacs 的专用标记命令：

If you want to make precise selections, you are better off using Emacs’s dedicated mark commands:

按键绑定 目的
M-h 标记下一段
C-x h 标记整个缓冲区
C-M-h 标记下一个 defun
C-x C-p 标记下一页
M-@ 标记下一个单词
C-M-<SPC>和
C-M-@ 标记下一个 s 表达式
C-<SPC>,C-g 停用该区域

如果您已经有一个活动区域，则所有标记命令都会附加到现有选择。因此，如果您想标记连续的两个单词，您只需按M-@两次或将其与数字参数组合：M-2 M-@。同样，您可以使用负参数修饰符来反转方向。

All mark commands append to the existing selection if you already have a region active. So if you want to mark two words in a row, all you have to do is press M-@ twice or combine it with a numeric argument: M-2 M-@. Likewise, you can reverse the direction by using the negative argument modifier.

附加功能特别有用，因为您的观点保持静态。 Emacs 只是将标记从一个位置移动到下一个位置。这使得执行主题编辑变得很容易，例如删除选择或针对它执行命令。

The append functionality is particularly useful since your point remains static. Emacs simply moves the mark from one position to the next. That makes it easy to do topical edits like deleting the selection or executing a command against it.

在“什么构成单词？”一章中我讨论了语法表以及主要模式的语法表如何影响移动命令。许多标记命令都是相似的，尤其是M-x mark-word命令M-@。但是，某些标记命令在某些主要模式下会被覆盖，因此它们可以在该特定模式下正常工作。例如，在 reStructuredText 中，M-x mark-defun绑定的命令C-M-h将选择整个章节；这是明智的，因为文本文件中没有defuns （函数的 LISP 术语）。并非所有主要模式都支持M-x mark-defun，但 Emacs 提供的大多数模式都支持 — 最终取决于主要模式的作者来告诉 Emacs 如何标记像 defuns 这样的复杂事物。

In the chapter What Constitutes a Word? I talked about syntax tables and how a major mode’s syntax table affects movement commands. A lot of mark commands are similar, notably the M-x mark-word command M-@. However, some mark commands are overridden in some major modes so they work correctly for that particular mode. For instance, in reStructuredText, the M-x mark-defun command bound to C-M-h will select a whole chapter; this is sensible, as there are no defuns (a LISP term for a function) in a text file. Not all major modes support M-x mark-defun but most modes supplied with Emacs do — ultimately it’s down to the author of the major mode to tell Emacs how to mark complex things like defuns.

停用该区域

请记住，您可以使用Emacs 的通用退出C-<SPC>命令或 来停用该区域。C-g

Deactivating the region

Remember, you can deactivate the region with C-<SPC> or C-g, Emacs’s universal quit command.

我建议您忽略C-x C-p（标记下一页的键绑定）。专注于记忆，C-x h因为它标记了整个缓冲区；C-M-h，因为这将标志着 defun；和C-M-<SPC>，因为它将用 s-表达式进行标记，并且在大多数情况下，如果遇到单词，其行为相同。

I recommend you ignore C-x C-p (the key binding that marks the next page). Focus on memorizing C-x h as that marks the entire buffer; C-M-h, as that will mark the defun; and C-M-<SPC>, as that will mark by s-expression and will, in most cases, act the same if it encounters a word.

我C-M-<SPC> 一直用。将其与负参数 ( C-M-- C-M-<SPC>) 结合起来可以反转方向，您也可以轻松地反向标记 s 表达式。

I use C-M-<SPC> all the time. Combine it with a negative argument (C-M-- C-M-<SPC>) to reverse the direction and you can mark s-expressions in reverse easily too.

最后，如果您使用kill 8命令进行后续操作，则许多手动标记都是多余的，因为Emacs 有自己的kill 命令直接作用于语法单元。我将在稍后的《编辑理论》中更详细地介绍 Kill 命令。

Finally, a lot of manual marking is redundant if you follow it up with a kill8 command, as Emacs has its own kill commands that act on syntactic units directly. I will go into much greater detail about the kill command later on in The Theory of Editing.

搜索和索引

Searching and Indexing

元素移动命令主要作用于句法单元。它们的主要目的是作为连续更精确的工具，让您从 A 到 B — 从按整个段落或解谜导航到按单个字符移动。

Elemental movement commands act mostly on syntactic units. Their primary purpose is to serve as successively more precise tools for getting you from A to B — from navigating by entire paragraphs or defuns down to moving by a single character.

然而，您通常想要搜索文本。也许您确切地知道自己在寻找什么，也许您不知道，但是无论如何，您都需要工具来有效地做到这一点。

Often, however, you want to search for text. Maybe you know exactly what you are looking for and maybe you are not, but, regardless, you need tools to do this effectively.

Isearch：增量搜索

Isearch: Incremental Search

Emacs 的增量搜索（或简称 Isearch）是一种极其强大的搜索功能，C-s您将在 Emacs 职业生涯中经常使用它。在其简单的外观之下是一组复杂的辅助命令：

Emacs’s incremental search – or just Isearch – is a supremely powerful search function bound to C-s and one you will use a lot in your Emacs career. Beneath its simple exterior is a sophisticated set of auxiliary commands:

按键绑定 目的
C-s 开始增量搜索
C-r 开始向后增量搜索
C-M-s 开始正则表达式增量搜索
C-M-r 开始正则表达式向后增量
搜索
RET 选择选定的比赛
C-g 退出搜索

使用 Isearch 很简单：

Using Isearch is easy:

选择搜索方向
Pick a direction of search

C-s您可以使用或开始向前或向后搜索C-r，如上表所示。迷你缓冲区将显示I-search:或I-search backward:。

如果您以前搜索过某些内容，则可以通过重复 Isearch 命令来调用上一个搜索词。因此，如果您想调用最后一个搜索词，您可以键入C-s C-s以首先打开 Isearch，然后调用最后一个搜索字符串。当您这样做时，Emacs 会自动进行增量搜索。

You can begin a forward or backward Isearch with C-s or C-r, as per the table above. The minibuffer will show I-search: or I-search backward:.

If you previously searched for something, you can recall the last search term by repeating the Isearch command. So, if you want to recall the last search term, you can type C-s C-s to first open Isearch and then recall the last search string. Emacs will automatically do an incremental search when you do.

开始打字
Begin typing

您按下的每个键都会触发增量搜索引擎，以查找搜索方向上与您的搜索字符串相匹配的第一个匹配项。当遇到第一个匹配项时，增量搜索引擎将突出显示缓冲区中该搜索字符串的所有其他匹配项；如果您的搜索字符串没有匹配项，Emacs 将在尽可能匹配后停止并告诉您搜索失败。

Every key you press will trigger the incremental search engine to find the first match in the direction of your search that matches your search string. When it encounters the first match, the incremental search engine will highlight all other matches of that search string in your buffer; if there are no matches to your search string, Emacs will stop when it has matched as much as it can and tell you it has failed.

浏览比赛
Browse the matches

如果您有多个匹配项，或者您只是想浏览所有匹配项，请持续点击要搜索的方向键（C-s或）。C-r如果您想反转方向，只需点击另一个方向，Emacs 就会切换方向。

如果到达匹配项的末尾，或者搜索方向上没有匹配项，您可以再次点击方向键，从缓冲区的开头或结尾继续搜索（取决于搜索的方向）。迷你缓冲区会告诉您是否将搜索绕到另一侧。

Isearch 还会通过以红色突出显示失败的匹配来告诉您搜索字符串的哪些部分无法匹配以及哪些部分没有匹配。9

If you have more than one match, or if you simply want to walk through all the matches, keep tapping the direction key (C-s or C-r) in which you want to search. If you want to reverse the direction, simply tap the other direction and Emacs will switch directions.

If you reach the end of the matches – or if there are no matches in your search direction – you can continue the search from the beginning or end of the buffer (depending on the directionality of your search) by tapping the direction key again. The minibuffer will tell you if it wrapped the search around to the other side.

Isearch will also tell you what part of your search string failed to match and what parts didn’t, by highlighting the failed match in red.9

选择一场比赛
Pick a match

一旦您对匹配感到满意，您可以通过两种方式终止搜索：

C-g退出Isearch

终止 Isearch 并返回到原来的位置。如果您的搜索字符串仅部分匹配，它将首先返回到最后一个已知的匹配。

RET选择选定的比赛

这也会终止 Isearch，但它会让您停留在当前所在的比赛位置，并在您的原始位置留下一个标记，以便您可以使用 返回到之前的位置C-u C-<SPC>。

Once you are happy with a match, you can terminate the search in two ways:

C-g exits Isearch

Terminates Isearch and returns to your original position. If you have a search string with only a partial match, it will first return you to the last known match.

RET picks the selected match

This also terminates Isearch but it leaves you at the match you are at and it drops a mark at your original location so you can return to your former location with C-u C-<SPC>.

Isearch 非常有用，我强烈鼓励您使用它进行移动，因为它是在 Emacs 中移动文本的最快方法之一。这也是我最常用的命令之一。我每天使用它数百次，甚至更多。将 Isearch 行为转化为肌肉记忆需要一些练习，但这是非常值得的！它有两个可访问的按键 -C-s和C-r- 并且它是可视的和即时的。没有干扰，没有仪式，没有弹出并遮盖缓冲区的模式对话框，没有需要改变搜索方向的繁琐的单选按钮，不需要鼠标，也不需要按标签键来操作它。

Isearch is so useful that I strongly encourage you to use it for movement as it is one of the quickest ways of moving around text in Emacs. It is also one of my most used commands. I use it hundreds of times a day, if not more. It takes a bit of practice to commit the Isearch behavior to muscle memory but it is so worth it! It has two accessible keys – C-s and C-r – and it is visual and instantaneous. There are no distractions and no ceremony, no modal dialog that pops up and obscures your buffer, no fiddly radio buttons to change the search direction, no mouse needed and no tabbing required to operate it either.

表壳折叠

默认情况下，Isearches 不区分大小写；小写字母搜索将匹配大写字母和混合大小写。但是，当您在搜索中使用一个或多个大写字母时，Emacs 将自动切换到区分大小写的搜索。这就是所谓的案例折叠。

这是又一个奇怪的 Emacs 功能，没人会想到在其他地方实现。它也比您想象的更有用。您可能正在寻找大写字符串，但您的搜索字符串不一定是大写字符串。如果您确实需要区分大小写，您所要做的就是拼出大写或大小写混合的名称，Emacs 将只查找文字匹配。当然，如果您只查找小写匹配项，而不查找大写或混合大小写匹配项，那么您别无选择，只能禁用大小写折叠或使用 Isearch 的切换功能暂时启用区分大小写。

如果您愿意，您可以完全禁用大小写折叠：

M-x customize-option case-fold-search RET

Case folding

By default, Isearches are not case sensitive; lowercase searches will match uppercase and mixed case. However, when you use one or more uppercase letters in your search, Emacs will automatically switch to a case-sensitive search. It’s called case folding.

This is another one of those strange Emacs features that nobody would think to implement elsewhere. It’s also more useful than you would think. You might be looking for an uppercase string, but your search string doesn’t have to be. And if you really need case-sensitivity, all you have to do is spell out the uppercase or mixed case name and Emacs will only look for literal matches. Of course, if you are looking for only lowercase matches but no upper- or mixed case matches, then you have no choice but to disable case folding or use Isearch’s toggles to temporarily enable case-sensitivity.

If you prefer, you can disable case folding entirely:

M-x customize-option case-fold-search RET

一旦您开始使用 Isearch，您将希望使用其历史记录（正式称为搜索环）功能更多：

Once you start using Isearch you’ll want to use its history (formally called search ring) features more:

Isearch 按键绑定 目的
M-n 移至搜索历史记录中的下一项
M-p 移至搜索历史记录中的上一项
C-M-i “TAB”-完整搜索字符串
上一个搜索环
C-s C-s 开始针对上次搜索进行 Isearch
细绳

前两个现在应该是不言自明的——因为它们在所有 Emacs 补全中普遍可用——但第三个值得仔细研究。

The first two should be self-explanatory by now – as they are universally available in all Emacs completions – but the third one warrants a closer look.

Emacs 中的“TAB”补全

在 Emacs 中，是另一种“TAB”完成机制，与您在提示符下C-M-i按时看到的机制没有什么不同。在支持它的模式中 – 并且不要忘记，当您运行 Isearch 时，您本质上是在与模式交互 – 该命令通常绑定到，这是一种通用完成机制，它查看当前文本并尝试根据已知集合来完成它完成情况。在 Isearch 的例子中，按下也会触发补全引擎 - 但考虑到 Isearch 的特殊性质，它是一个不同的引擎 - 但这次它会将你的 Isearch 搜索字符串与你的搜索历史进行比较。试试看。TABM-xcomplete-symbolC-M-i

“TAB”-completion in Emacs

In Emacs, C-M-i is another “TAB”-completion mechanism not unlike the one you see when you press TAB in the M-x prompt. In modes that support it – and do not forget, when you run Isearch you are essentially interacting with a mode – the command is typically bound to complete-symbol, a generic completion mechanism that looks at the text at point and tries to complete it against a known set of completions. In Isearch’s case, pressing C-M-i will also trigger the completion engine – but a different one built for Isearch given its specialized nature – but this time it’ll compare your Isearch search string against your search history. Try it out.

在点处搜索字符串是很常见的情况，因此有专门的命令可以帮助您做到这一点：

Searching for strings at point is such a common occurrence that there are dedicated commands to help you do just that:

Isearch 按键绑定 目的

C-M-y 在点处添加字符到搜索字符串

通常，您会发现自己想要搜索某个单词，为了省去手动输入的麻烦，您只需输入 即可C-w。重复调用会将后续单词添加到搜索字符串中。我发现C-M-y（一次添加一个字符）对大多数人来说用处不大，但如果您用外来字符编辑大量文本，您会发现它很有用。

It’s common that you will find yourself at a word you want to search for and, to save the hassle of typing it in manually, you can just type C-w. Repeated invocations will add subsequent words to the search string. I find C-M-y (which adds one character at a time) to be of marginal use to most, but if you edit a lot of text with foreign characters, you will find it useful.

键绑定的重要更改

如果您使用的 Emacs 版本早于 24.4 , 10，则必须将和C-y替换M-y为。新的排序更有意义，因为默认命令位于Isearch 之外。M-s C-eC-yyankC-y

Important changes to key binds

If you are using an Emacs version older than 24.4,10 then you must replace C-y with M-y and M-s C-e with C-y. The newer ordering makes a lot more sense as the default yank command is C-y outside of Isearch.

Isearch 是一种包容性搜索，它通常会谨慎行事，并匹配更传统、更严格的搜索不会匹配的内容。您可以使用其开关来控制 Isearch 的行为方式：

Isearch is an inclusive search and it will generally err on the side of caution and match things that a more traditional, stricter search, would not. You can control how Isearch behaves using its toggles:

Isearch 按键绑定 目的
M-s c 切换区分大小写
M-s r 切换正则表达式模式
M-s w 切换单词模式
M-s _ 切换符号模式
M-s <SPC> 切换宽松的空白匹配
M-s ' 切换字符折叠
（Emacs 25 或更高版本）

每个切换命令仅影响当前的 Isearch 并且不会持续。

Each toggle command only affects the current Isearch and will not persist.

区分大小写切换 ( M-s c) 只是打开严格区分大小写的匹配 - 如果默认情况下打开大小写折叠并且仅偶尔需要严格的大小写搜索，则非常有用。

The case-sensitivity toggle (M-s c) simply turns on strict case-sensitive matching — useful if you have case folding on by default and you only occasionally need strict case search.

使用 切换正则表达式模式M-s r类似于使用C-M-s或激活正则表达式 Isearch C-M-r，反之亦然。

Toggling regular-expression mode with M-s r is akin to activating regexp Isearch with C-M-s or C-M-r, and vice versa.

单词和符号切换 (M-s w和M-s _) 会改变 Isearch，因此单词和符号分隔符就像其他分隔符一样.，并且-可以自由匹配其他分隔符。

The word and symbol toggles (M-s w and M-s _) alter Isearch so word and symbol delimiters like . and - freely match other delimiters.

例如，考虑一个包含以下文本的缓冲区：

For instance, consider a buffer with this text:

this-is-a-hyphenated-string
this-is-a-hyphenated-string

单独搜索hyphenated stringwithC-s不会产生匹配，但如果您使用 重新运行搜索C-s，然后使用 切换单词搜索模式M-s w，就会产生匹配。在您想要匹配由（可能未知的）单词分隔字符分隔的两个连续单词的语言中，单词搜索特别有用，如以下 C 示例：

Searching for hyphenated string with C-s alone will not yield a match, but if you re-run the search with C-s and then toggle word search mode with M-s w, it will. Word search is especially useful in languages where you want to match two successive words separated by (possibly unknown) word-delimiting characters, like this C example:

mystruct->foo = 42;
mystruct->foo = 42;

如果您使用 切换单词搜索，搜索mystruct foo将与上面的元素访问匹配。M-s w

Searching for mystruct foo will match the element access above if you toggle word search with M-s w.

在 Emacs 25.1 中，您现在可以使用 启用字符折叠M-s '。它非常简洁：当您搜索aEmacs 时，它会尝试匹配诸如á或 之类的字符å；它适用于多种角色。您可以通过自定义默认启用它search-default-mode。

In Emacs 25.1 you can now enable character folding with M-s '. It’s quite neat: when you search for a Emacs will attempt to match characters like á or å; it works for a wide range of characters. You can enable it by default by Customizing search-default-mode.

我介绍的一些切换和命令非常频繁，以至于它们有自己的全局键绑定：

Some of the toggles and commands I have covered are so frequent that they have their own global keybindings:

按键绑定 目的
M-s w 我向前搜索单词
M-s _ I向前搜索符号
M-s . I向前搜索点处的符号
（Emacs 24.4 或更高版本）

您应该认识到前两个，因为它们与您在 Isearch 本身中可用的键绑定相同。最后一个，M-s .，仅可用作全局键绑定。它开始向前搜索该点的符号。如果您想要在源代码中的标识符上找到要在其他地方搜索的点，这会很有用。

You should recognize the first two as they are the same key bindings available to you inside Isearch itself. The last one, M-s ., is only available as a global key binding. It begins a forward Isearch for the symbol at point. This is useful if you have the point on an identifier in your source code that you want to search for elsewhere.

学习搜索
Learn Isearch

它本身就是一个强大的搜索工具，但它还可以让您通过搜索您想要去的地方附近的单词来快速移动缓冲区。传统的文本编辑器和 IDE 给 UI 带来了太多的大厦和复杂性，但在 Emacs 中，Isearch 几乎消除了视觉混乱和上下文切换，因此您可以保持节奏。

It is a powerful search tool in its own right, but it also lets you move around the buffer quickly by searching for words near where you want to go. Traditional text editors and IDEs attach too much edifice and complexity to the UI but in Emacs, Isearch nearly eliminates the visual clutter and context switching and hence you keep your tempo.

发生：打印并编辑与表达式匹配的行

Occur: Print and Edit lines matching an expression

Occur 模式是grepEmacs 中内置的类似实用程序。与 不同的是grep，它的功能要少得多，并且默认情况下仅对当前缓冲区进行操作。它的优点M-x occur在于它的速度，而且它是 Emacs 附带的，因此您不必调用外部进程。 Occur 还将在其匹配结果中保留语法突出显示。

Occur mode is a grep-like utility built into Emacs. Unlike grep, it has far fewer functions and will by default only operate on the current buffer. What makes M-x occur great is its speed and that it comes with Emacs, so you don’t have to call out to an external process. Occur will also preserve the syntax highlighting in its match results.

Isearch 逐步引导您完成缓冲区中的每个匹配项，而发生将创建一个新的缓冲区，并*Occur*在其中包含所有匹配结果。

Whereas Isearch incrementally walks you through every match in a buffer, occur will instead create a new buffer called *Occur* with all the match results in it.

您可以在全局范围内以及从 Isearch 本身内部激活发生：

You can activate occur globally and from within Isearch itself:

按键绑定 目的
M-s o 发生方式
M-s o 激活发生在当前搜索字符串上
内部搜索

与 Isearch 不同，您需要输入要搜索的正则表达式。发生模式搜索与正则表达式匹配的行，并在单独的缓冲区中显示结果。有时，您可能需要上下文行（匹配行本身之前和之后的行），您可以通过自定义变量来启用它们list-matching-lines-default-context-lines。

Unlike Isearch, you’re asked for a regular expression for which to search. Occur mode searches for lines that match the regular expression and shows you the results in a separate buffer. Occasionally, you may want context lines – lines before and after the matching line itself – and you can enable them by customizing the variable list-matching-lines-default-context-lines.

发生模式使用超链接，当您用鼠标左键单击或按下RET键盘时，超链接会跳转到匹配的行。缓冲区中使用的发生模式*Occur*有许多可以使用的有用键：

Occur mode uses hyperlinks that jump to the matching line when you left-click it with the mouse or press RET on your keyboard. The occur mode used in the *Occur* buffer has a number of useful keys you can use:

发生按键绑定 目的
M-n,M-p 转到下一个和上一个出现的位置
<,> 转到缓冲区的开头和结尾
g 恢复缓冲区，刷新
搜索结果
q 退出发生模式
e 切换到发生编辑模式
C-c C-c 退出编辑模式并
应用更改

这些键仅在发生缓冲区本身中可用。

The keys are only available in the occur buffer itself.

在 Emacs 中，该键g将恢复缓冲区。执行此操作时会发生什么情况取决于模式，但从原始源刷新内容是常见的 Emacs 约定。在这种情况下，它将使用相同的正则表达式在缓冲区上重新运行搜索。该g命令值得记住，因为它是 Emacs 中的常见约定。

In Emacs, the key g will revert the buffer. What happens when you do that depends on the mode, but it’s a common Emacs convention to refresh the contents from the original source. In this case, it will re-run the search on the buffer with the same regular expression. The g command is worth remembering as it’s such a common convention in Emacs.

该e键会将发生缓冲区切换到可编辑状态。这是一个令人难以置信的强大编辑结构，它允许您在发生缓冲区中内嵌编辑文本，然后通过键入 来将更改提交到原始源代码行C-c C-c。

The e key will switch the occur buffer to an editable state. This is an unbelievably powerful editing construct that lets you edit the text in-line in the occur buffer and then commit the changes to the original source lines by typing C-c C-c.

发生模式的主要优点是，您可以获得包含结果的第二个缓冲区（通常在原始缓冲区旁边的第二个窗口中），以及匹配的概览视图以及在匹配行之间跳转的能力。然而，这需要你不断切换到另一个窗口来选择新的匹配；这不仅乏味，而且会破坏你的节奏。为了保持你的节奏，我建议你学习这两个命令：

The main advantage of the occur mode is that you get a second buffer with the results, usually in a second window next to your original buffer, and an at-a-glance view of the matches and the ability to jump between the matching lines. However, that requires that you keep switching to the other window to select new matches; that is not only tedious, but it ruins your tempo. To maintain your tempo, I suggest you learn these two commands:

按键绑定 目的
M-g M-n 跳转到下一个“错误”
M-g M-p 跳转到上一个“错误”

目的列显示“错误”，但这是因为命令名称是M-x next-error和M-x previous-error。实际上，它们是通用命令。当您运行M-x occur（或 Emacs 中的其他专用命令，例如M-x compile或M-x grep）时，Emacs 会记住该命令并在该匹配列表中进行上下移动M-g M-n。这些命令的好处是您只需要记住这两个命令，它们将与您执行的最后一次已知的发生、编译或 grep 搜索一起使用。M-g M-p

The purpose column says “error,” but that’s because the command names are M-x next-error and M-x previous-error. In reality, they are general-purpose commands. When you run M-x occur (or other specialized commands in Emacs like M-x compile or M-x grep), Emacs remembers that and makes M-g M-n and M-g M-p go up and down that list of matches. The great thing about these commands is you only have to remember those two and they will work with the last-known occur, compile or grep search you did.

多次发生

Multi-Occur

您可以在具有multi-occurr的多个缓冲区上使用发生模式。该命令M-x multi-occur-in-matching-buffers采用缓冲区的正则表达式进行匹配 - 例如\.py$搜索所有 Python 缓冲区 - 但其他方面与M-x occur.您还可以M-x multi-occur明确选择要搜索的缓冲区 - 也很有用，但使用速度较慢，因为您必须手动选择要运行的每个缓冲区。

You can use the occur mode on multiple buffers with multi-occur. The command M-x multi-occur-in-matching-buffers takes a regular expression of buffers to match – for instance \.py$ to search all Python buffers – but otherwise works the same as M-x occur. There is also M-x multi-occur where you explicitly select the buffers you want to search — also useful, but slower to use as you have to manually select each buffer on which to run occur.

对于多次发生，您可以使用我之前解释过的大部分命令：这意味着您可以e在匹配的缓冲区中进行编辑（使用 ）。现在，将其与 Emacs 的键盘宏或搜索和替换结合起来，您就拥有了一个异常强大的工具供您使用。

With multi-occur you can use most of the commands I explained earlier: that means you can edit (with e) across the buffers you matched. Now combine it with Emacs’s keyboard macros or search & replace and you have an exceptionally powerful tool at your disposal.

菜单：跳转到定义

Imenu: Jump to definitions

Imenu 是一个通用索引框架，用于跳转到缓冲区中的兴趣点。主要模式作者将编写一个 elisp 片段，生成一个兴趣点列表 - 它们的名称以及它们在缓冲区中出现的位置 - 因此当您使用 调用 imenu 时M-x imenu，您可以跳转到其中任何一个。

Imenu is a generic indexing framework for jumping to points of interest in a buffer. A major mode author will write a snippet of elisp that generates a list of points of interest – their name and where in the buffer they occur – so when you invoke imenu with M-x imenu, you can jump to any one of them.

大多数（但不是全部）主要模式都支持 imenu。对于编程模式，最明显的兴趣点是诸如函数和类定义之类的东西；其他模式也可以使用它们，例如邮件程序或结构化文本模式（如 Markdown 或 reStructuredText）。

Most, but not all, major modes support imenu. For programming modes, the most obvious points of interest are things like functions and class definitions; other modes may make use of them as well, such as mail programs or structured text modes like Markdown or reStructuredText.

Imenu 是您工具箱中的另一个用于中长距离移动的工具。我发现当我不确定缓冲区中的内容时我最常使用它；对于跳转到我在屏幕上看到的内容，Isearch 或元素移动命令可能会更好（而且更快）。

Imenu is another tool in your toolbox for medium and long-distance movement. I find that I use it most when I am not sure of where something is in a buffer; for jumping to things I see on the screen, Isearch or elemental movement commands might be better (and faster).

奇怪的是，imenu 根本没有绑定到任何键。要使用它，您必须键入M-x imenu。不幸的是，我认为它在历史上阻碍了它的采用，因为它不受任何已知或可访问的密钥的约束。当您亲自探索 Emacs 时，您会发现这种情况很常见 — 事实上，如此常见，以至于 20 年的老手仍然可以在 Emacs 中找到他们以前从未听说过的新东西。

Oddly, imenu is not bound to any key at all. To use it, you must type M-x imenu. That is unfortunate as I think it has historically hampered its adoption since it is not bound to any known or accessible key. As you will see as you explore Emacs yourself, that is a common occurrence — so common in fact that 20-year veterans still find new things in Emacs that they had never heard about before.

我将 imenu 绑定到M-i.然而，该密钥已被使用。现有的命令M-x tab-to-tab-stop，将插入空格或制表符以到达下一个制表位，这一概念可以追溯到打字机时代，并且自那以后就没有使用过。就我个人而言，我没有用这样的东西，当然也没有使用这样一个可访问的密钥。

I bind imenu to M-i. That key is already in use, however. The existing command, M-x tab-to-tab-stop, will insert spaces or tabs to get to the next tab stop, a concept that dates back to – and hasn’t been used since – the era of the typewriter. Personally, I have no use for such a thing and certainly not on such an accessible key.

要将 Imenu 绑定到M-i，请将其添加到您的初始化文件中：

To bind Imenu to M-i, add this to your init file:

(global-set-key (kbd "M-i") 'imenu)
(global-set-key (kbd "M-i") 'imenu)

与大多数 Emacs 的完成提示一样，Imenu 仅支持TAB开箱即用的 - 样式完成。我建议您阅读下一章并使用 Helm 的 Imenu 支持。

Like most of Emacs’s completion prompts, Imenu only supports TAB-style completion out of the box. I recommend you read the next chapter and use Helm’s Imenu support instead.

Helm：增量完成和选择

Helm: Incremental Completion and Selection

Helm 是一个很棒的包。它是一个通用框架，用于“按类型过滤”完成；也就是说，您开始输入内容，Helm 将自动过滤并显示匹配的内容 — 与 Isearch 的实时增量搜索不同。

Helm is an amazing package. It’s a generic framework for filter-as-you-type completion; that is, you begin typing and Helm will automatically filter and show you what matches — not unlike Isearch’s real-time, incremental search.

Helm 之所以如此出色，是因为它附带了许多开箱即用的完成命令。我个人的建议是您按照下面的安装说明进行操作并立即开始使用 Helm 。 Helm 与 Emacs 一贯的低调补全机制截然不同——特别是如果您已经有了适合您的工作流程——但 Helm 广泛的补全源选择及其“按类型过滤”功能显然优于Emacs 自己TAB的许多（但不是全部）任务的完成机制。

What makes Helm so fantastic is that it comes with a lot of completion commands out of the box. My personal recommendation is that you follow the installation instructions below and start using Helm right away. Helm is a radical departure from Emacs’s usual low-key completion mechanism – particularly if you already have a workflow that works for you – but Helm’s extensive selection of completion sources and its filter-as-you-type is clearly superior to Emacs’s own TAB-based completion mechanism for many (but not all) tasks.

如何安装

Helm 是第三方软件包，不随 Emacs 一起提供。安装方法有很多种，但这是最简单的：

  1. 确保您已按照包管理器中的说明进行操作。
  2. 运行M-x package-install，然后输入helm并按RET。
  3. 重新启动您的 Emacs。

How to install

Helm is a third-party package and does not ship with Emacs. There are many ways of installing it, but this is the easiest:

  1. Ensure you have followed the instructions in The Package Manager.
  2. Run M-x package-install, then enter helm and press RET.
  3. Restart your Emacs.

所有 Helm 命令共享前缀 key C-x c。我不能说我是那个前缀键的忠实粉丝，因为它后面的许多键使它成为手指扭曲的练习。它也非常接近C-x C-c退出 Emacs 的命令。

All Helm commands share the prefix key C-x c. I can’t say I am a big fan of that prefix key as a lot of the keys that follow it make it an exercise in finger contortion. It is also remarkably close to C-x C-c — the command that exits Emacs.

前缀键绑定 目的
C-x c 所有 Helm 完成的前缀键
命令。

探索头盔

Exploring Helm

Helm 是一个深入而复杂的工具，如果您花时间探索它的功能，它会给您带来回报。

Helm is a deep and complex tool that rewards you if you spend the time discovering what it can do.

在 Emacs 中发现事物的技巧是向 Emacs 提出正确的问题。在这种情况下，正确的问题是：Helm 向我提供了哪些命令？ Helm有按键绑定吗？

The trick to discovering things in Emacs is to ask Emacs the right questions. The right questions in this case are: What commands does Helm make available to me? and Does Helm have any key bindings?

使用得当
Use apropos

正如我在Apropos中谈到的，apropos将列出所有与您给出的模式匹配的 elisp 符号——变量、命令、elisp 函数等等。在这种情况下，要求M-x apropos-command（使用C-h a）向您显示所有匹配的命令^helm-将是一个不错的起点。同样，M-x apropos-variable将执行相同的操作，但对于变量。

Elisp 没有命名空间，因此包作者在其命令前加上包的名称。由于包名称是 Helm，因此使用apropos查找以helm-- 或者更准确地说以正则表达式 开头的命令是有意义的^helm-。

巧合的是，Helm 有自己的 apropos 完成引擎：M-x helm-apropos.它将完成命令、变量和函数 - 确保您只查看命令标头，因为函数是内部 elisp 函数，不适合一般用途。

As I talked about in Apropos, apropos will list all elisp symbols – variables, commands, elisp functions, and so on – that match the pattern you give it. In this case, asking M-x apropos-command (using C-h a) to show you all commands that match ^helm- would be a good place to start. Likewise, M-x apropos-variable will do the same but for variables.

Elisp does not have namespaces so package authors prefix their commands with the name of the package. As the package name is Helm, it makes sense to use apropos to find commands beginning with helm- — or more precisely as the regular expression ^helm-.

Coincidentally, Helm has its own apropos completion engine: M-x helm-apropos. It will complete commands and variables & functions — make sure you only look in the Commands header as Functions are internal elisp functions not meant for general use.

描述前缀键
Describe the prefix key

我之前提到 Helm 有自己的前缀键C-x c.在描述系统C-h中，您可以通过用:结束前缀键来告诉 Emacs 列出前缀键中的所有键绑定C-x c C-h。

I mentioned earlier that Helm has its own prefix key, C-x c. In The Describe System, you can tell Emacs to list all key bindings in a prefix key by finishing a prefix key with C-h: C-x c C-h.

这两种方法产生的答案略有不同 - 因为你实际上是在问两个不同的问题 - 所以你应该同时做。

The two methods yield slightly different answers – because you are in fact asking two different questions – so you should do both.

最后：

And finally:

  • M-x apropos-command( C-h a) 不限于绑定到前缀键的命令，它会很高兴地向您显示未绑定的命令（如果您的搜索模式太通用，甚至完全不相关），但这仍然是发现隐藏命令、绑定或不是。
  • M-x apropos-command (C-h a) is not limited to commands bound to a prefix key and it will happily show you commands that are unbound (or even completely unrelated if your search pattern is too generic) — but this is still a great way of discovering hidden commands, bound or not.
  • 描述前缀键C-h只会显示绑定到该前缀键的命令。有时，您会发现一些命令虽然绑定到该前缀键，但与其他命令无关。
  • Describing a prefix key with C-h will only show you the commands bound to that prefix key. Occasionally, you will discover commands that, although bound to that prefix key, have nothing to do with the other commands.

头盔绑带

Helm Bindings

由于 Helm 命令数量众多，我将列出我认为最重要的命令。我鼓励您遵循探索 Helm中的建议并亲自探索 Emacs 和 Helm。

Because of the sheer number of Helm commands, I will list the ones I think are the most important. I encourage you to follow the suggestions in Exploring Helm and explore Emacs and Helm yourself.

在此之前，我应该谈谈 Helm actions。在 Helm 中，您还可以针对匹配项执行操作；可用的操作完全取决于您正在执行的完成情况。

Before I do that, I should talk about Helm actions. In Helm, you can also carry out actions against the matches; the actions available depend entirely on the completion you are doing.

Helm 有自己的一组密钥，您需要学习：

Helm has its own set of keys that you need to learn:

头盔按键绑定 目的
RET 主要行动
C-e 次要动作
C-j 第三次行动
TAB 切换到动作选择器
C-n,C-p 下一位和上一位候选人
M-<,M-> 完成清单的开始和结束

RET是您想要对所选候选人执行的主要（也是最常见的）操作。通常，它会跳转到、打开或显示候选人。第二个动作（如果有的话）是绑定到的，您可能还记得它是一个跳到行尾的C-e基本移动命令；该命令仍然会在 Helm 中执行此操作，但前提是您的点不在行尾 - 如果是，则它充当次要操作。

RET is the primary (and most common) action you’d want to carry out on the selected candidate. Usually, it will jump to, open or display the candidate. The secondary action, if there is one, is bound to C-e which you may remember is an elemental movement command that jumps to end of the line; the command will still do that in Helm but only if your point is not at the end of the line — if it is, it acts as the secondary action.

退出头盔

要快速退出 Helm，请按C-g通用退出键。

Exiting Helm

To quickly exit Helm, press C-g, the universal get-out-of-anything key.

该TAB键将切换到操作选择器并列出所选候选人的所有可用操作。与 Helm 完成界面一样，操作界面也是filter-as-you-type。

The TAB key will switch to the action selector and list all available actions for the selected candidate. Like the Helm completion interface, the action interface is also filter-as-you-type.

以下是一些更有用的 Helm 完成引擎：

Here are some of the more useful Helm completion engines:

按键绑定 目的
C-x c b 恢复上次 Helm 命令
C-x c / 调用命令行实用程序find
在活动缓冲区的当前目录上
C-x c a 完成M-x apropos结果
C-x c m man页面的补全引擎
程序
C-x c i 列出来自以下来源的完成内容
M-x imenu或语义
C-x c r 交互式正则表达式生成器
C-x c h r 在以下位置搜索 Emacs 主题M-x info

C-x c M-s o 使用 Helm 来匹配M-x occur模式
C-x c C-c g 显示来自 Google Suggest 的匹配项

一些 Helm 命令具有明显的拜占庭键绑定，例如C-x c C-c g显示Google Suggest匹配项。即使按照 Emacs 标准，它们也是迟钝的。

Some of the Helm commands have positively byzantine key bindings, like C-x c C-c g to show Google Suggest matches. Even by Emacs standards, they’re obtuse.

学习 Helm 将极大改善您的 Emacs 体验。它配备了强大的模糊搜索和大量有用的完成机制。它还拥有自己蓬​​勃发展的第三方软件包生态系统。

Learning Helm will greatly improve your Emacs experience. It comes with a powerful fuzzy search and a large range of useful completion mechanisms. It also has its own burgeoning ecosystem of third-party packages.

Emacs 的有趣之处在于，您可以通过Google Suggest完成机制等方式获得意想不到的生产力提升。当您可以在 Emacs 中进行搜索并从 Google 获得输入时的建议时，为什么还要切换到网络浏览器并在浏览器中进行搜索呢？

The interesting thing about Emacs is the unexpected productivity improvements you’ll get from things like the Google Suggest completion mechanism. Why switch to a web browser and search in the browser when you can do it in Emacs and get as-you-type suggestions from Google?

IDO：交互式做事

IDO: Interactively DO Things

正如我在缓冲区切换替代方案中谈到的，IDO 模式是一个强大的迷你缓冲区完成引擎。 Helm 和 IDO 的用途重叠，有些人更喜欢使用其中一种而不使用另一种；大多数人都使用这两种方法，但目的不同：

As I talked about in Buffer Switching Alternatives, IDO mode is a powerful minibuffer completion engine. Helm and IDO overlap in purpose and some prefer to use one to the exclusion of the other; most use both but for different purposes:

IDO 是一种无干扰、目标感知的搜索
IDO is a distraction-free, target-aware search

与 Helm 不同，IDO 不使用单独的缓冲区（和窗口）来显示完成匹配。相反，它在您的迷你缓冲区本身中内嵌完成。对于诸如缓冲区切换和文件查找之类的事情来说，这是更可取的，因为您大致知道您要去哪里以及您正在寻找什么。这就是我使用 IDO 模式的方式，我认为这是一个很好的开始方式；对于几乎每个人来说，这肯定是比基于默认的TAB完成机制更好的选择。

然而，当您不完全确定自己在寻找什么时，IDO 就会失败。当您想要的只是与查询匹配的所有内容的概述时，单步执行迷你缓冲区中的匹配项是乏味的。

Unlike Helm, IDO does not use a separate buffer (and window) to show completion matches. Instead, it completes in-line in your minibuffer itself. This is preferable, for things like buffer switching and file finding, as you roughly know where you’re going and for what you are looking. That is how I use IDO mode and I think it’s a great way to start out; for almost everyone out there, it is certainly a better choice than the default TAB-based completion mechanism.

However, IDO fails when you’re not entirely sure what you are looking for; stepping through the matches in the minibuffer is tedious when all you want is an overview of everything that matches your query.

Helm是为了深度搜索和补全
Helm is for in-depth searching and completion

Helm 将打开一个瞬态缓冲区和窗口来显示匹配项，这会大大增加视觉混乱和干扰 - 如果您不确定自己在寻找什么，这本身并不是坏事。但是，如果您知道自己在做什么——例如您在缓冲区中foobar.txt并且想要打开widgets.c——IDO 是更好的选择，因为您可以无缝切换缓冲区而不会遭受视觉开销。

事实上，如果您是盲打打字员，您很快就会从一个缓冲区跳到另一个缓冲区，而无需看一眼迷你缓冲区，因为您的直觉告诉您，如果您键入C-x b wc，IDO 将灵活匹配widgets.c。

当您不确切知道自己在寻找什么或需要对类似匹配进行额外的上下文感知时， Helm 会表现出色。

Helm will open a transient buffer and window to display matches and that greatly increases visual clutter and distraction — that is not in itself bad if you are unsure what you are looking for. But if you know what you are doing – for instance you are in buffer foobar.txt and you want to open widgets.c – IDO is a better choice as you can seamlessly switch buffers and not suffer the visual overhead.

Indeed, if you are a touch-typist you will quickly reach a point where you jump from buffer to buffer without so much as glancing at the minibuffer because your primed intuition tells you that if you type C-x b wc, IDO will flex match to widgets.c.

Helm excels when you don’t know exactly what you’re looking for or if you require additional, contextual awareness of similar matches.

我建议您通过将以下行添加到init 文件中来启用 IDO 模式以进行文件和目录查找以及缓冲区切换：

I recommend you enable IDO mode for file and directory finding, and buffer switching by adding the following lines to your init file:

(ido-mode 1)
(setq ido-everywhere t)
(setq ido-enable-flex-matching t)
(ido-mode 1)
(setq ido-everywhere t)
(setq ido-enable-flex-matching t)

现在，当您查找文件或目录（C-x C-f和C-x d）或切换缓冲区（使用C-x b）时，您将使用 IDO 优越得多的完成机制。当然，如果您愿意，也可以自由使用 Helm。

Now, when you find files or directories (C-x C-f and C-x d) or switch buffers (with C-x b), you will use IDO’s far superior completion mechanism. Of course, you are free to use Helm as well if you prefer.

我建议您只学习 IDO 的几个广泛的键绑定。

I recommend you learn just a couple of IDO’s extensive key bindings.

文件和目录切换

File & Directory Switching

仅当您运行要求您选择文件或目录的命令时，这些键才可用。其中分别包括C-x C-f和C-x d，但还包括使用以下命令保存C-x C-s文件之类的内容：

These keys are only available when you run a command that requires you to pick a file or directory. That includes C-x C-f and C-x d, respectively, but it also includes things like file saving with C-x C-s:

Buffer Switching

通常仅在您键入以下内容时才会遇到缓冲区切换C-x b：

Buffer switching is usually only encountered when you type C-x b:

按键绑定 目的
C-s和C-r 移至下一场和上一场比赛

进一步阅读

我建议您阅读我的网站上的文章Ido Mode 11简介，以获取有关如何使用 IDO 模式的更多深入信息。

Further reading

Grep：搜索文件系统

Grep: Searching the file system

搜索已在 Emacs 中打开的文件很有用，但您通常希望搜索未在 Emacs 中打开的文件，而命令行实用程序grep是实现此目的的好方法。

Searching files already open in Emacs is useful but more often than not you want to search files that aren’t open in Emacs and the command line utility grep is a great way to do just that.

grep在微软视窗中

Windows 中没有类似的grep程序 - 并且内置程序findstr虽然功能强大，但 Emacs 并不支持开箱即用 - 因此我建议您安装 GNU Coreutils 的交叉编译 Windows 版本。12它们在 Windows 中工作得非常出色，并且为您提供了 Windows 中合理的 Linux 命令行传真。

grep in Microsoft Windows

There is no like-for-like grep program in Windows – and the built-in one findstr, though powerful, is not supported out of the box by Emacs – so I recommend you install the cross-compiled Windows versions of the GNU Coreutils.12 They work splendidly in Windows and they give you a reasonable Linux command line facsimile in Windows.

您如何与grep（或更一般地与任何外部工具）交互取决于您的编辑器。许多 Vim 用户会退出 Vim 或使用tmux或等工具screen并切换到终端并运行命令，然后返回 Vim。 Emacs 用户更喜欢可以融入 Emacs 的工具。正如您很快就会看到的那样，从 Emacs 内部使用grep是提高生产力的主要方式。

How you interact with grep – or more generally with any external tool – depends on your editor. Many Vim users would exit Vim or use a tool like tmux or screen and switch to a terminal and run the command(s) and then return to Vim. Emacs users prefer tools they can assimilate into Emacs. Using grep from inside Emacs is a major productivity-booster as you’ll soon see.

ack，ag和ripgrep

尽管功能强大，但您可能更喜欢其他东西grep，例如ripgrep.您可以在支持它们的包管理器中找到第三方包。

ack, ag and ripgrep

Though powerful, you may prefer something other than grep, like ripgrep. You can find third-party packages in the package manager that supports them.

Emacs 支持大量的grep和grep派生命令。默认情况下没有绑定到键，因此您必须直接调用命令，M-x然后将经常使用的命令绑定到键：

Emacs supports a large array of grep and grep-derivative commands. None are bound to a key by default so you will have to call the commands directly with M-x and later bind the ones you use frequently to keys:

命令 目的
M-x grep 提示传递参数grep
M-x grep-find 提示传递参数grep
和 find
M-x lgrep 提示输入查询和全局模式
搜索与grep
M-x rgrep 提示输入查询和 glob 模式
然后递归搜索grep
和find
M-x rzgrep 喜欢M-x rgrep但搜索
压缩的gzip 文件

命令grep分为两类：

The grep commands fall into two categories:

低级命令
Low-level commands

喜欢M-x grep和M-x grep-find。他们为您提供建议的grep命令字符串，您所要做的就是添加搜索模式和您需要的任何其他选项。

我不经常使用它们。我通常想在一组文件中搜索模式，而这些命令对于此来说太低级了。有时，我想grep使用特定选项进行调用，在这种情况下我别无选择，只能使用M-x grep或M-x grep-find。

like M-x grep and M-x grep-find. They supply you with a suggested grep command string and all you have to do is add the search pattern and any additional options you require.

I don’t use them frequently. I usually want to search for a pattern in a group of files and these commands are too low-level for that. Occasionally, I want to call grep with specific options and in that case I have no choice but to use M-x grep or M-x grep-find.

高级命令
High-level commands

喜欢M-x lgrep,M-x rgrep和M-x rzgrep.它们完全隐藏命令字符串，而是询问您要搜索的文件和要匹配的搜索字符串。

Emacs 还将根据您当前缓冲区的文件类型巧妙地建议文件类型，并且 Emacs 还将查看您所在的当前符号并询问您是否要搜索该符号。这很方便，因为您经常发现自己位于或靠近要搜索的标识符或单词，在这种情况下，您只需键入M-x rgrep并键入RET两次即可接受默认值。

like M-x lgrep, M-x rgrep and M-x rzgrep. They hide the command string completely and instead ask you for the files you want to search and the search string you want to match.

Emacs will also cleverly suggest a file type based on your current buffer’s file type and Emacs will also look at the current symbol your point is on and ask if you want to search for that. That is convenient because you often find yourself on or near an identifier or word you want to search for and in that case you can just type M-x rgrep and type RET twice to accept the defaults.

Grep 猜测

Grep Guesswork

特别是高级命令在调用 时rgrep会进行许多巧妙的幕后猜测find。首先，Emacs 可以在任意数量的平台上运行，并且它必须在所有平台上一致地工作。并非所有平台都附带xargs，因此 Emacs 将检查这一点并使用find自己的-exec开关。字符串中的引用和转义字符因平台和 shell 的不同而不同 — Emacs 需要与所有这些平台和 shell 兼容。

The high-level commands – particularly rgrep – do a lot of clever behind-the-scenes guesswork when it calls out to find. First of all, Emacs runs on any number of platforms and it has to work consistently on all of them. Not all platforms come with xargs, so Emacs will check for this and use find’s own -exec switch instead. Quoting and escaping characters in strings vary on platforms and shells — and Emacs needs to work with all of them.

Windows 注释

在 Windows 上，已经有一个名为find.要覆盖 Emacs 中的默认选择，您应该将其添加到init 文件中，确保更改C:\\gnuwin32\\bin\\为 GNU 的位置find，然后重新启动 Emacs：

(setenv "PATH" (concat "C:\\gnuwin32\\bin\\"
                       path-separator
                       (getenv "PATH")))

Windows note

On Windows, there is already a program called find. To override the default choice in Emacs, you should add this to your init file, making sure to change C:\\gnuwin32\\bin\\ to the location of GNU find and then restart Emacs:

(setenv "PATH" (concat "C:\\gnuwin32\\bin\\"
                       path-separator
                       (getenv "PATH")))

Emacs 箭袋中的另一个箭头是能够自动将负匹配传递给find.例如，您不想搜索源代码管理目录.git或垃圾文件，从而产生误报。

Another arrow in Emacs’s quiver is the ability to automatically pass negative matches to find. For instance, you don’t want to search source control directories like .git or trash files that yield false positives.

许多人使用类似ack或rg的工具，您可以轻松地包含或排除文件模式 - 但幸运的是，Emacs 自动化了这一单调乏味的工作。

A lot of people use tools like ack or rg for the ease of which you can include or exclude file patterns — but Emacs thankfully automates that tedium.

我鼓励您使用自定义浏览类别grep并根据您的喜好进行配置：

I encourage you to browse the grep category with Customize and configure it to your liking:

M-x customize-group RET grep RET
M-x customize-group RET grep RET

使用 Grep 界面

Using the Grep Interface

按键绑定 目的
M-g M-n 跳转到下一场比赛
M-g M-p 跳至上一场比赛

就像我在谈论 时提到的那样M-x occur，您可以重复使用跳转命令。和以前一样，它们是全局的并且跨缓冲区边界工作。它们值得了解，因为您可以快速轻松地在*grep*缓冲区中的匹配项之间跳转。如果文件尚未打开，Emacs 将打开文件并跳转到右侧行（如果已打开，Emacs 将简单地切换到已打开的文件。）

Like I mentioned when I talked about M-x occur, you can re-use the jump commands. As before, they are global and work across buffer boundaries. They are worth knowing as you can quickly and easily jump between matches in a *grep* buffer. Emacs will open the files and jump to the right line if they are not already open (and if they are, Emacs will simply switch to the already-open file.)

在 Emacs 中查找

就像 Emacs 中的所有内容一样，它归结为模式，而 grep 的主要模式被命名为 - 你猜对了 - grep-mode。 Emacs 实际上所做的归结为是将输出从管道传输grep到名为 的缓冲区，*grep*然后调用grep-mode.激活后，grep-mode将突出显示匹配项并将它们超链接到行号和文件名，以便您可以跳转。

如果仔细观察，缓冲区中的输出*grep*看起来与其本身相同grep！您可以通过打开一个空白缓冲区（C-x b然后选择一个未使用的名称）并输入如下内容来测试这一点：

my_file.txt:10:This does not exist!

然后键入M-x grep-mode并观看，Emacs 将突出显示匹配项，就好像它是来自 的真实输出一样grep。这是 Emacs 中的常见模式：重新使用命令的原始输出是一种技术含量低但有效的方法。

Grepping in Emacs

Like everything in Emacs, it comes down to modes and the major mode for grep is named – you guessed it – grep-mode. What Emacs actually does boils down to is piping the output from grep to a buffer named *grep* followed by a call to grep-mode. When activated, grep-mode will highlight the matches and hyperlink them to the line number and filename so you can jump around.

If you look closely, the output in a *grep* buffer looks identical to that of grep itself! You can test this by opening a blank buffer (C-x b and then pick a name not in use) and enter something like this:

my_file.txt:10:This does not exist!

and then type M-x grep-mode and watch as Emacs will highlight the match as though it were real output from grep. This is a common pattern in Emacs: re-using the raw output from a command is a low-tech but effective approach.

其他移动命令

Other Movement Commands

对于大多数 Emacs 用户来说，这些移动命令的日常使用有限。了解它们很有用，一旦您熟悉了本章中的所有其他命令，其中一两个就值得纳入您的工作流程中。

These movement commands are of limited day-to-day use for most Emacs users. They are useful to know about and one or two of them worth incorporating into your workflow once you are comfortable using all the other commands in this chapter.

按键绑定 目的
M-r 将点重新定位到左上角，
左中或左下
C-l 将点重新居中到中间、顶部或
缓冲区底部
C-M-l 重新定位注释或定义
所以它在缓冲区中可见
C-x C-n 设置目标列、水平方向
点的位置
C-u C-x C-n 重置目标列、水平方向
点的位置
M-g M-g 前往线路
M-g TAB 前往专栏
M-g c 转到角色位置

M-r并且C-l功能相似。M-r首先将你的点移动到行的开头，然后在缓冲区的顶部、中间和底部之间交替。它所做的只是在这三个位置之间切换。C-l类似，只是它会滚动您的窗口，因此线点重新居中为顶部、中间或底部。C-M-l类似，只是它会智能地尝试重新定位窗口，以便定义或注释点在缓冲区中可见。换句话说，它会尝试将事物滚动到视图中。

M-r and C-l are functionally similar. M-r will first move your point to the beginning of the line and then alternate between the top, the middle and the bottom of the buffer. All it does is toggle between those three locations. C-l is similar only it will scroll your window so the line point is on is re-centered as the top, middle, or bottom. C-M-l is similar only it will intelligently try and re-position the window so the definition or comment point is visible in the buffer. In other words, it will try and scroll things into view.

我C-l一直用。我用它来重新定位我所在的线，这样我就可以看到我所在的线上方或下方的更多缓冲区。我鼓励你尝试M-r一下C-l。

I use C-l all the time. I use it to recenter the line I’m on so I can see more of the buffer above or below the line I am on. I encourage you to try out M-r and C-l.

大多数人对目标列命令C-x C-n的兴趣有限。当您向上或向下移动一行时，Emacs 将在您从一行移动到下一行时尝试保持您的水平位置。如果您设置了目标列，Emacs 不会执行此操作，而是使您的点的水平位置与目标列相匹配。因此，如果您将目标列设置为 10（通过将点放在第 10 个字符上），Emacs 将尝试（如果该行足够长！）确保您的点始终放置在第十个字符上。要禁用目标列，请键入C-u C-x C-n。

The goal column command C-x C-n is of limited interest to most people. When you move up or down a line, Emacs will try to maintain your horizontal position as you move from one line to the next. If you have a goal column set, Emacs will not do that and instead make your point’s horizontal position match the goal column. So if you set the goal column to 10 – by putting point on the 10th character – Emacs will try (if the line is long enough!) to ensure your point is always placed at the tenth character. To disable goal column, type C-u C-x C-n.

跳转到一行已经足够频繁，但由于 Emacs 的交互式编译模式和对 grep 等内容的内置支持，您不必像使用更简单的编辑器那样频繁地跳转到显式行。该命令绑定到M-g M-g，其工作方式与您所期望的完全一样：它要求您输入要跳转到的行。您还可以给它一个前缀参数，例如M-5 M-5 M-g M-g，以跳转到第 55 行 - 并确保使用M-数字参数来保持节奏。

Jumping to a line is frequent enough but because of things like Emacs’s interactive compilation mode and built-in support for things like grep, you don’t have to jump to explicit lines as often as you’d have to if you used a simpler editor. The command, bound to M-g M-g, works exactly as you would expect: it asks you for a line to which to jump. You can also give it a prefix argument, for instance M-5 M-5 M-g M-g, to jump to the 55th line — and make sure you use the M- digit argument to maintain your tempo.

该命令M-g TAB执行相同的操作，只是跳转到特定的列位置。M-g c从缓冲区开头开始跳转到缓冲区中的绝对位置。如果您想跳转到缓冲区中的第 42 个字符，您可以输入M-g c或M-4 M-2 M-g c。

The command M-g TAB does the same only it jumps to a particular column position instead. M-g c jumps to the absolute position in the buffer starting from the beginning of the buffer. If you want to jump to the 42nd character in a buffer, you’d type M-g c or M-4 M-2 M-g c.

结论

Conclusion

正如前面的子章节所示，您可以通过多种方式在 Emacs 中移动。 Emacs 经常被批评为一个操作系统，但却是一个糟糕的文本编辑器，但事实并非如此。 Emacs 是一个高度复杂的文本编辑器，它的功能可以轻松与 Vim 相媲美——即使这两个编辑器在功能上和方法上有所不同。 Emacs 的修饰键是一种瞬态形式。 Emacs 明显是模态的，因为您的命令会随着修饰键的变化而变化，并且在您释放修饰键之前一直保持这种状态。最重要的一件事是将 Caps Lock 重新映射为 Control：没有它我就活不下去，即使在 Emacs 之外也是如此。如果您是触摸打字员，控制键的位置会很尴尬。

As the previous sub-chapters have shown, there are a multitude of ways you can move around in Emacs. Emacs is often lambasted for being an operating system but a terrible text editor, but that could not be farther from the truth; Emacs is a highly sophisticated text editor and it easily rivals Vim in capability — even if the two editors are functionally different in their approach. Emacs’s modifier keys are a form of transient modality. Emacs is distinctly modal as your commands change with the modifier keys and remain so until you release the modifier keys. The one thing that will make the biggest difference is remapping Caps Lock to Control: I could not live without this, even outside of Emacs. The control keys are awkwardly placed if you’re a touch typist.

Emacs 的命令也有很多对称性，特别是基本移动命令。并非所有的键绑定都有意义，并且存在诸如不绑定M-x imenu到键之类的愚蠢的疏忽。

There is also a lot of symmetry to Emacs’s commands, particularly the elemental movement commands. Not all key bindings make sense and there are silly oversights like not binding M-x imenu to a key.

如果您是 Emacs 新手，我建议您继续使用箭头键。您可以一次一键采用 Emacs 的移动命令。最终，您将慢慢采用某些 Emacs 主义，并且您很快就会意识到将右手从主行移开以使用箭头键会减慢您的速度。

If you are new to Emacs, I suggest you keep using the arrow keys. You can adopt Emacs’s movement commands one key at a time. Eventually, you will slowly adopt certain Emacs-isms and you’ll soon realize that moving your right hand off the home row to use the arrow keys is slowing you down.

我的下一个建议是进行实验。不断地回顾这本书，直到形成肌肉记忆；不断尝试不同的组合并训练你的大脑识别模式。这一切都与肌肉记忆和模式匹配有关——知道如果你执行这个命令，你就会得到那个结果。没有人能在一夜之间掌握 Emacs，而且掌握 Emacs 无论如何都是转移注意力的；对于一百个人来说，这意味着一百件事。

My next suggestion is to experiment. Keep referring back to the book until it’s muscle memory; keep experimenting with different combinations and train your brain to recognize patterns. It’s all about muscle memory and pattern matching — knowing that if you do this command, you’ll get that outcome. Nobody mastered Emacs overnight and Emacs mastery is a red herring anyway; it means a hundred things to a hundred people.

在本章中，我向您展示了如何使用 Emacs 的内部文档（特别是apropos和描述C-h系统）查找内容，这比任何事情都更能帮助您“掌握”Emacs。如果您知道如何在 Emacs 中查找答案，那么忘记命令的名称或它所绑定的键并不重要。

Over the course of the chapter, I showed you how to look things up using Emacs’s internal documentation – particularly apropos, C-h and the describe system – and that more than anything will help you “master” Emacs. Forgetting the name of a command or the key it is bound to is immaterial if you know how to look up the answer in Emacs.

我的最后建议是关于实验。每当你做一些你认为可以以更聪明或更有效的方式做的事情时，请另一个人通读这本书或在互联网上搜索建议。当我意识到我一直面临的特定问题除了简单的手动方式之外还有其他解决方案时，我自己的大部分技术和工作流程都有机地发展。

My final advice is about experimentation. Every time you do something that you think you can do in a smarter or more efficient way — have another read through the book or search the Internet for advice. Most of my own techniques and workflow grew organically as I realized that particular problems I kept facing had solutions other than the naive, manual way.

编辑理论

The Theory of Editing

“无数只猴子在 GNU Emacs 中输入永远不会产生一个好的程序。”

– Linus Torvalds，Linux 内核编码风格文档

“An infinite number of monkeys typing into GNU Emacs would never make a good program.”

– Linus Torvalds, Linux Kernel Coding Style Documentation

在 Emacs 中编辑可能比学习如何在 Emacs 中有效移动更容易。大多数日常编辑是编写或删除由专业命令打断的文本。然而，在 Emacs 中，即使是删除文本或使用Kill Ring（剪贴板）等平常的事情也得到了高度优化。

Editing in Emacs is perhaps even easier than learning how to move around effectively in Emacs. Most day-to-day editing is writing or deleting text punctuated by specialist commands. Nevertheless, in Emacs, even mundane things like deleting text or using the kill ring (the clipboard) are highly optimized.

我认为更重要的是你首先掌握移动，因为这意味着你学习如何切换缓冲区并有效地使用 Emacs 的窗口系统。这就是为什么直到现在，这本书已经读了三分之二，我才根本没有谈论过编辑文本。一旦您能够轻松地打开和保存文件并在 Emacs 中四处走动，而不会忘记自己正在做什么，那么您就可以准备好处理更高级的编辑概念了。

I think it’s more important that you master movement first as that means you learn how to switch buffers and use Emacs’s windowing system effectively. That is why I have not talked about editing text at all, until now, two thirds of the way through the book. Once you’re comfortable opening and saving files and getting around in Emacs without losing track of what you were doing — then you’re ready to tackle more advanced editing concepts.

如果您正在阅读本章并且仍在使用导航键（箭头键、向上翻页和向下翻页等），那么也没有问题。您会发现这种体验有点脱节，因为 Emacs 的移动键之所以如此有效，很大程度上是因为它们与文本编辑对应的关系近乎和谐。

If you are reading this chapter and are still using the navigation keys – the arrow keys, page up and down, and so on – then that is fine too. You will find the experience a bit disjointed as a lot of what makes Emacs’s movement keys so effective is the near-harmonious relationship they have with their text-editing counterparts.

本章将介绍如何编辑文本；其中包括传统的主要功能，例如搜索和替换；如何使用杀戮环或剪贴板；如何使用文本宏；以及如何使用文本转换工具。

This chapter will cover how to edit text; that includes traditional staples like search and replace; how to use the kill ring, or clipboard; how to use text macros; and how to use text transformation tools.

杀戮和掠夺文本

Killing and Yanking Text

其他文本编辑器只是剪切文本，而在 Emacs 中你可以删除它。正如我在Killing、Yanking 和 CUA中谈到的，这个术语很奇怪，并且完全早于大多数图形用户界面。

Where other text editors merely cut text, in Emacs you kill it. The terminology, as I talked about in Killing, Yanking and CUA, is bizarre and predates most graphical user interfaces entirely.

发现 Kill 命令

使用 Emacs 的apropos功能查找此处未列出的其他终止命令。

Discovering the Kill Commands

Use Emacs’s apropos functionality to find additional kill commands not listed here.

Emacs 的 Kill 命令使用与移动命令相同的语法单元概念。其中一些还共享修饰符对称性，从而可以轻松地在kill命令之间切换。

Emacs’s kill commands use the same syntactic unit concept as the movement commands do. Some of them also share modifier symmetry, making it easy to switch between kill commands.

按键绑定 目的
C-d 删除字符
<backspace> 删除前一个字符
M-d,C-<backspace> 杀字
C-k 杀掉剩下的线
M-k 杀句
C-M-k 杀死s-表达
C-S-<backspace> 杀死当前行

上表中最突出的是C-d，它删除下一个字符；和<backspace>，其作用相同，但方向相反。所有其他命令都会杀死而不删除.区别很重要：已删除的文本不会保留在您的 Kill Ring 中，而已删除的文本则会保留在您的Kill Ring 中。

The ones that stand out in the table above are C-d, which deletes the next character; and <backspace>, which does the same but backwards. All other commands kill and don’t delete. The distinction is important: deleted text is not retained in your kill ring whereas killed text is.

数字参数和否定参数
Digit Arguments and Negative Arguments

与移动命令一样，您可以使用数字参数一次杀死多个单位。为了保持节奏，请确保使用与要调用的 Kill 命令的修饰符相同的数字修饰符。如果您想用 终止 3 个 s 表达式C-M-k，请输入C-M-3 C-M-k。

否定参数会反转方向，就像移动命令一样。毫无疑问：这比看起来更有用。我经常写完一些东西，却发现我想把它移到别处，或者，也许，完全删除它。

考虑这个例子：

s = make_upper_case("hello, world!"-!-)

后C-M-- C-M-k：

s = make_upper_case(-!-)

Like the movement commands, you can use the digit arguments to kill more than one unit at a time. To maintain your tempo, ensure you use the same digit modifier as the modifier of the kill command you want to call. If you want to kill 3 s-expressions with C-M-k, type C-M-3 C-M-k.

The negative argument reverses direction, just like the movement commands. Make no mistake: that is more useful than it seems. I frequently finish writing something only to realize I want to move it elsewhere or, perhaps, delete it entirely.

Consider this example:

s = make_upper_case("hello, world!"-!-)

After C-M-- C-M-k:

s = make_upper_case(-!-)

Kill 命令很有用，但 Emacs 中也有通用的、与剪贴板等效的命令：

The kill commands are useful, but there are generalist, clipboard-equivalent commands in Emacs too:

按键绑定 杀环目的 剪贴板
C-w 杀死活动区域 切
M-w 复制到杀环 复制
C-M-w 追加杀戮
C-y 猛拉最后的杀戮 粘贴
M-y 循环通过杀环，
替换拉出的文本

删除与删除

Killing versus Deleting

删除和删除之间的这一关键区别让许多 Emacs 新用户感到困惑。在大多数编辑器中，剪贴板命令（仅作用于所选文本）和删除文本的命令之间有明确的界限。在 Emacs 中，除了少数例外（如我上面提到的两个命令），所有命令都会直接杀死文本到您的终止环。如果您是 Emacs 新手，它会让您感到困惑，甚至可能会激怒您。除非您明确告诉它，否则没有其他编辑器会修改您的剪贴板内容，但 Emacs 会这样做，而且一旦您习惯了它，它就是一个很棒的功能。

This one crucial difference between killing and deleting trips up a lot of new Emacs users. In most editors, there is a clear delineation between clipboard commands – that act solely and exclusively on the selected text – and commands that delete text. In Emacs, all commands will, with few exceptions like the two I mentioned above, kill text straight to your kill ring. If you are new to Emacs, it will confuse you and maybe even infuriate you. No other editor fiddles with your clipboard content unless you explicitly tell it to — but Emacs does, and it’s a great feature once you get used to it.

Emacs 的 Kill 命令可以用五个简单的规则来最好地概括：

Emacs’s kill commands are best summarized with five simple rules:

连续杀死追加
Consecutive kills append

到杀戮环。所有终止命令都会附加到终止环中，也就是说，它们会附加到终止环中的文本，当且仅当最后一个命令也是终止命令时。如果通过移动、写入或运行命令来打破循环，则下一个终止​​命令将在终止环中创建一个新条目。

例如，如果您输入M-d M-d M-d– 连续删除三个单词 – 当您下次拉动文本时，您的删除环将保留您删除的三个单词。如果您输入M-d M-d M-d，则移动到下一行C-n并删除另外三个单词。你的最后三个词是你从杀戮环中拉出来的，而不是全部六个！移动命令打破了循环。

正如我之前提到的，这通常会让初学者感到困惑，但这是一种聪明的工作方式，因为您不必先选择文本。

to the kill ring. All kill commands append to the kill ring – that is to say they append to the text in the kill ring – if, and only if, the last command was also a kill command. If you break the cycle, by moving or writing or running a command, the next kill command will create a new entry in the kill ring.

For instance, if you type M-d M-d M-d – killing three words in a row – your kill ring will hold the three words you killed when you next yank the text. If you type M-d M-d M-d, then move to the next line with C-n and kill another three words. Your last three words are what you yank from the kill ring, not all six! The movement command broke the cycle.

As I mentioned earlier, this is often confusing to beginners but it’s a smart way of working as you don’t have to select text first.

杀戮环可以容纳许多物品
The kill ring can hold many items

与撤消环一样，您不会轻易丢失杀戮环中的信息；如果你杀了一些东西，然后用另一个杀戮替换了你的第一个杀戮条目，那么你并没有失去你的第一个杀戮。它很容易恢复，事实上，如果您正在重写文本，杀戮环通常被用作片段的临时和辅助“存储”。

and like the undo ring you cannot easily lose information in the kill ring; if you kill something and then later on replace your first kill entry with another kill, you have not lost your first kill. It’s easily recoverable and in fact the kill ring is often used as a temporary and secondary “store” of snippets if you are rewriting text.

杀戮环是全球性的
The kill ring is global

以及 Emacs 中的所有缓冲区之间。您可以通过运行来查看杀戮环——尽管它清晰可见，但它应该是机器可读的C-h v kill-ring。

and between all the buffers in Emacs. You can view the kill ring – though legible it’s meant to be machine-readable – by running C-h v kill-ring.

杀也是删除
Killing is also deleting

当你不关心被杀死的文本时。杀戮环既是不需要的文本的垃圾场，又是有用文本的剪贴板。很少有直接删除文本的命令 - Emacs 很少会将您置于可能发生意外数据丢失的位置 - 因此，这就是为什么所有边界命令都将文本发送到终止环。但这也很好：杀戮环是有限的，但比你可能关心的要大。如果你选择利用一个近乎无限的杀戮环，它不会忘记你过去的杀戮，这是一个强大的功能。

忘记你的杀戮戒指很珍贵的想法吧——事实并非如此。

when you don’t care about the killed text. The kill ring is as much a dumping ground for unwanted text as it is a clipboard for useful text. There are few outright commands that delete text – Emacs will rarely put you in a position where accidental data loss is likely – so that’s why all bounds commands send text to the kill ring instead. But that’s fine too: the kill ring is finite but larger than you would ever likely care about. A near-infinite kill ring that won’t forget your past kills is a powerful feature if you choose to take advantage of it.

Forget the idea that your kill ring is precious — it’s not.

无需标记
Marking is unnecessary

对于大多数涉及句法单元的操作。M-d连续点击三次将三个单词删除到删除环比M-@先用 标记它们然后用 删除要快得多C-w。

有两个例外：

  • 如果要复制 ( M-w) 区域，先标记然后复制会更快。
  • 如果您想删除或复制不符合语法单元倍数的奇形区域。

for most operations that involve syntactic units. It’s far quicker to tap M-d three times in a row to kill three words to the kill ring than mark them with M-@ first and then kill with C-w.

There are two exceptions:

  • If you want to copy (M-w) the region, it’s quicker to mark first and then copy.
  • If you want to kill or copy odd-shaped regions that don’t conform to multiples of syntactic units.

Kill 附加是 Emacs 中的一个多功能且独特的功能。我经常发现自己在重构代码或文本，并能够删除文本，以便将其移动到其他地方——也许首先重写或调整一些现有的代码或文本——然后再将C-y文本拉回来。

Kill appending is a versatile and unique feature in Emacs. I often find myself re-factoring code or text and the ability to kill text with the intent on moving it somewhere else – and maybe rewriting or massaging some existing code or text first – before yanking (with C-y) the text back.

附加到杀戮环

有时，您想要将新的杀戮附加到杀戮环中的现有杀戮中。如果您想要终止缓冲区的不同部分，而不是一个、连续的区域或一系列终止命令，则通常会发生这种情况。为此，首先键入C-M-w，Emacs 会在回显区域告诉您，如果下一个命令是kill 命令，它将附加到kill 环。

Appending to the kill ring

Occasionally, you want to append a new kill to the existing one in the kill ring. This often happens if you want to kill different parts of a buffer that are not one, contiguous region or series of kill commands. To do this, first type C-M-w and Emacs will tell you in the echo area that if the next command is a kill command, it will append to the kill ring.

回想一下，当您重构函数时，您是否经常发现自己想要“收集”部分文本；也许您想将几条评论整理成一大组。杀戮环可以让你做到这一点。

Think back to how often you have found yourself wanting to “collect” parts of text as you are re-factoring a function; perhaps you want to collate several comments into one big group. The kill ring lets you do that.

杀戮线

Killing Lines

如果你想杀死整行，你应该使用C-S-<backspace>- 但该命令在终端中不起作用，因为由于终端模拟器的技术限制，这是不可能的。

If you want to kill the whole line, you should use C-S-<backspace> — but that command won’t work in a terminal as it is not possible owing to technical limitations of the terminal emulator.

另一种方法，也是我喜欢的一种方法，是修改杀死活动区域的命令的行为，这样如果没有活动区域，C-w它就会杀死该点所在的当前行。我建议您安装该软件包：whole-line-or-region

The other approach, and one favored by me, is to modify the behavior of C-w – the command that kills the active region – so it kills the current line the point is on if there are no active regions. I recommend you install the package whole-line-or-region:

M-x package-install RET whole-line-or-region RET
M-x package-install RET whole-line-or-region RET

C-k类似地，还有M-x kill-line一个命令，可以从点到行尾进行杀死。该行为与大多数人期望的不同：C-k不会杀死行尾的换行符；保持这种行为是有利的，因为当您想要杀死行尾时很少需要换行符。与其他语法单元命令一样，通常C-k在您想要重组或重写文本时使用。如果该点位于行尾，则换行符将被终止 - 因此点击C-k两次将终止文本和换行符。

Similarly, there is C-k, M-x kill-line, a command that kills from point to the end of the line. The behavior is different from what most expect: C-k will not kill the newline character at the end of the line; it is advantageous to keep this behavior as the newline character is rarely desired when you want to kill to the end of the line. Often C-k is, like the other syntactic unit commands, used when you want to restructure or rewrite text. If the point is at the end of the line, the newline symbol is killed — so tapping C-k twice will kill the text and the newline.

如果您愿意，可以C-k通过自定义 Emacs 强制永久终止换行符：

If you prefer, you can force C-k to kill the newline permanently by customizing Emacs:

M-x customize-option RET kill-whole-line RET
M-x customize-option RET kill-whole-line RET

或者，您可以C-k使用数字参数进行调用：C-1 C-k。

Or, you can call C-k with a numeric argument: C-1 C-k.

猛拉文本

Yanking Text

在 Emacs 中，如果您想粘贴.在日常对话中将其称为“粘贴”很好，但您可能应该学习真正的 Emacs 术语，以便更轻松地在 Emacs 本身中查找内容。

In Emacs, you yank from the kill ring if you want to paste. It’s fine to refer to it as paste in daily conversation but you should probably learn the real Emacs terminology to make it easier to find things in Emacs itself.

您想了解的两个 yank 命令是：

The two yank commands you want to know about are:

按键绑定 目的 剪贴板
C-y 猛拉最后的杀戮 粘贴
M-y 循环通过杀环，
替换拉出的文本

Yanking 的工作原理与您所期望的一样：它将终止环中的当前条目插入到活动缓冲区中的点。重复调用 yank 将插入相同的文本。

Yanking works as you would expect: it inserts the current entry in the kill ring to the point in your active buffer. Repeat calls to yank will insert the same text.

正如我之前提到的，杀戮环是一个环，就像撤消环一样，它会记住以前的杀戮，以便您可以循环它们。

As I mentioned before, the kill ring is a ring, like the undo ring, and it remembers former kills so you can cycle through them.

骑自行车穿过杀戮环很容易：

Cycling through the kill ring is easy:

  1. 按C-y您想要显示拉出的文本的位置。
  2. Press C-y where you want the yanked text to appear.
  3. 无需执行其他命令（包括移动和编辑文本），只需键入M-y即可通过 Emacs 的终止环后退。
  4. Without executing another command – this includes moving around and editing text – type M-y to step back through Emacs’s kill ring.

转置文本

Transposing Text

转置文本是指将文本的两个句法单元相互交换的行为。乍一看，您可能会认为它们的用处有限；但实际上，它们的作用并不大。但实际上它们是有用的，如果你花功夫掌握它们，你就不会后悔。当您编辑文本时，您经常会错误地交换单词（在散文中），或者例如函数的参数（在代码中）。因此，交换事物的专用命令非常有用。

Transposing text is the act of swapping two syntactic units of text with one another. At first glance you may think they are of limited utility; but actually they are useful, and if you spend the effort and master them, you will not regret it. When you edit text, you often mistakenly swap words (in prose) or, for instance, arguments to a function (in code). Dedicated commands that swap things around are therefore very useful.

当您转置文本时，您可以使用句法单元来执行此操作，其方式与移动或删除文本的方式大致相同：

When you transpose text, you do so using syntactic units in much the same way you move or kill text:

按键绑定 目的
C-t 转置字符
M-t 调换单词
C-M-t 转置 s 表达式
C-x C-t 转置线
M-x transpose-paragraphs 转置段落
M-x transpose-sentences 调换句子

当您调用转置命令时，Emacs 将首先查看该点所在的位置，然后根据您发出的确切转置命令，交换该点周围的两个语法单元。

When you call a transpose command, Emacs will first look at where the point is and, depending on the exact transpose command you issued, swap two syntactic units surrounding the point.

在这种情况下，Emacs 如何定义语法单元有点复杂，因为您的主要模式决定了语法单元是什么。

How Emacs defines a syntactic unit in this case is a bit complicated as your major mode determines what a syntactic unit is.

否定论证也有效；数字参数也是如此，但不是您期望的方式。当您向转置命令提供数字参数时，它将获得该点之前的第 N 个单位（除非您还给它一个负参数，在这种情况下，情况正好相反），并将该单位与紧邻之前的单位交换观点。这很少有用。

Negative arguments also work; so do digit arguments, but not the way you would expect. When you give a digit argument to a transpose command it will get the Nth unit ahead of the point (unless you also give it a negative argument, in that case it is the other way around) and swap that unit with the one immediately before the point. That is rarely useful.

C-t：转置字符

C-t: Transpose Characters

转置字符会将字符移至该点的左侧和右侧并交换它们：

Transposing a character takes the character to the left and right of the point and swaps them:

A-!-BC
A-!-BC

后C-t：

After C-t:

BA-!-C
BA-!-C

请注意，该点向前移动了一个字符，因此您可以重复调用以C-t将字符“拉”到右侧：

Note that the point moved forward one character so you can repeat calls to C-t to “pull” the character to the right:

BCA-!-
BCA-!-

此规则的一个重要例外是当您位于一行末尾时。将交换点左侧的C-t两个字符：

One important exception to this rule is when you are at the end of a line. C-t will swap the two characters to the left of the point:

BCA-!-
BCA-!-

后C-t：

After C-t:

BAC-!-
BAC-!-

这种不对称性是修复拼写错误的一种非常有用的方法。使用 修复输入错误的字符C-t可以节省时间，因为它可以节省您删除两个字符并重新输入它们的精力。

This asymmetry is a surprisingly useful way of fixing typos as they occur. Fixing mistyped characters with C-t is a useful time saver as it saves you the effort of deleting both characters and retyping them.

M-t: 换位词

M-t: Transpose Words

M-t当单词是纯文本时，将两个单词互换，就像您所期望的那样：

Transposing two words with M-t works as you would expect when the words are plain text, like this:

Hello -!-World
Hello -!-World

后M-t：

After M-t:

World Hello-!-
World Hello-!-

就像用 调换字符一样C-t。点向前移动，就像您键入了M-f( M-x forward-word) 一样，这意味着您可以将单词“拉”到右侧。

Like transposing a character with C-t. the point moves forward as though you had typed M-f (M-x forward-word) and that means you can “pull” a word to the right.

真正的亮点M-t是当你将它与源代码一起使用时。在《什么构成一个词？》M-f和移动命令M-b会忽略您移动方向上的符号，并且M-t行为方式相同。

Where M-t really shines is when you use it with source code. In What Constitutes a Word? the M-f and M-b movement commands ignore symbols in the direction you are moving in and M-t behaves the same way.

考虑这个示例 Python 代码，其中我们有一个字典（键值哈希映射）：

Consider this example Python code where we have a dictionary (a key-value hash map):

names = {
  'Jerry':-!- 'Seinfeld',
  'Cosmo': 'Kramer',
}
names = {
  'Jerry':-!- 'Seinfeld',
  'Cosmo': 'Kramer',
}

有了键和值之间的点，调用M-t就纯粹是魔法：

With the point between the key and value, a call to M-t is pure magic:

names = {
  'Seinfeld': 'Jerry',
  'Cosmo': 'Kramer',
}
names = {
  'Seinfeld': 'Jerry',
  'Cosmo': 'Kramer',
}

正如您所看到的，键和值交换了位置，但符号保留在原处。再次重复，Emacs 将继续并替换Jerry为Cosmo;再重复一次，然后交换Jerry和Kramer。

As you can see, the key and value swapped places but the symbols remained in place. Repeat it again and Emacs will continue and swap Jerry with Cosmo; repeat it once more and you swap Jerry and Kramer.

移调实际上是如何工作的

该命令与( ) 命令M-t有内在联系。大大简化了，Emacs 将调用两次：一次带有否定参数，使左侧单词转置；一次带有负参数，使左侧单词转置；并再次在没有否定参数的情况下，将右侧的单词转置。现实情况要复杂一些，但也复杂不了多少。这也是一个易于测试的理论：从原始位置调用和- 确保在调用之间将点移回原始位置 - 你会发现单词的左右边缘将调换。M-x forward-wordM-fM-fM-- M-fM-fM-t

How Transposing Actually Works

The M-t command is intrinsically linked to the M-x forward-word (M-f) command. Greatly simplified, Emacs will call M-f two times: once with a negative argument, to get the left-side word to transpose; and once again without a negative argument, to get the right-side word to transpose. The reality is a little more complicated but not by much. It’s also an easy theory to test: call M-- M-f and M-f from your original position – making sure to move the point back to the original position between the calls – and you will find the left and right edge of the words M-t will transpose.

如果 Emacs 的文字移动行为以前毫无意义，我希望它现在更有意义了。虽然不是每个人都喜欢，但它在移动、杀戮和移调方面是一致的。

If Emacs’s word movement behavior made no sense before, I hope it makes a bit more sense now. It’s not to everyone’s liking but it is consistent across movement, kill and transpose.

它也适用于散文：

It also works on prose:

Hello,-!- World!
Hello,-!- World!

后M-t：

After M-t:

World, Hello-!-!
World, Hello-!-!

C-M-t：转置 S 表达式

C-M-t: Transpose S-expressions

您可以使用 and 转置 s 表达式（平衡表达式）C-M-t，就像使用 进行单词转置一样M-t，其机制是相同的；当转置函数找到左边缘和右边缘时，应用相同的前向和后向原理。

You can transpose s-expressions – balanced expressions – with C-M-t and, like word transposition with M-t, the mechanics are identical; the same forward & backward principles apply when the transposition function finds the left and right edges.

考虑以下 LISP 代码：

Consider the following piece of LISP code:

(/ (+ 2 n)-!- (* 4 n))
(/ (+ 2 n)-!- (* 4 n))

调用C-M-t它会交换两种形式的位置：

Calling C-M-t on it will swap the two forms’ positions:

(/ (* 4 n) (+ 2 n)-!-)
(/ (* 4 n) (+ 2 n)-!-)

与以前一样M-t，概念相同，但应用程序不同。但是C-M-t，与M-x forward-sexp( C-M-f) 非常相似，假设M-x transpose-word不存在平衡表达式：

Like M-t from before, the concept is identical but the application differs. But C-M-t, much like M-x forward-sexp (C-M-f), assumes the role of M-x transpose-word if there are no balanced expressions:

Hello,-!- World!
Hello,-!- World!

之后C-M-t就变成了：

And after C-M-t it becomes:

World, Hello-!-!
World, Hello-!-!

但考虑一下如果我们将平衡表达与单词混合会发生什么：

But consider what happens if we mix a balanced expression with a word:

Hello,-!- (insert name here)!
Hello,-!- (insert name here)!

后C-M-t：

After C-M-t:

(insert name here), Hello-!-!
(insert name here), Hello-!-!

所以，C-M-t仍然按您的预期工作。其用处在代码中也很明显：

So, C-M-t still works as you would expect. The usefulness is apparent in code as well:

ages = {
  'Seinfeld':-!- 34,
}
ages = {
  'Seinfeld':-!- 34,
}

正如您所期望的，Emacs 正确地转换了内容：

As you would expect, Emacs transposes things correctly:

ages = {
  34: 'Seinfeld'-!-,
}
ages = {
  34: 'Seinfeld'-!-,
}

与 相比，行为有所不同M-t。考虑与之前相同的场景，但使用M-t：

The behavior is different compared with M-t. Consider the same scenario as before but with M-t:

ages = {
  '34': Seinfeld-!-,
}
ages = {
  '34': Seinfeld-!-,
}

结果确实不同。我们没有调换整个平衡表达式，而是交换了单词，但留下了符号。

The result is different indeed. Instead of transposing the entire balanced expression we swapped the words instead but left the symbols behind.

其他转置命令

Other Transpose Commands

你还可以调换其他句法单元——行、段落和句子——我认为，除了调换行之外，其余的都更难证明立即学习的合理性。段落和句子命令是未绑定的，这使得它们更难使用——使用它们的唯一方法是通过 调用它们M-x。

You can also transpose other syntactic units – lines, paragraphs and sentences – and aside from transposing lines the rest are harder, I think, to justify learning right away. The paragraph and sentence commands are unbound, making them harder to use — the only way to use them is to invoke them through M-x.

然而，调换行C-x C-t是很有用的。我经常使用它来重新排序基于换行符的列表，它对于交换变量分配也很有用；更改函数调用的顺序，等等。

Transposing lines with C-x C-t is useful however. I use it frequently to re-order newline-based lists and it’s also useful for swapping around variable assignments; changing the order functions are called, and so on.

填写及评论

Filling and Commenting

填充

Filling

如果您编写大量文本，有时需要手动断开段落，以使行不会超过一定长度。您可以使用 Emacs 的填充功能来为您完成此操作，可以手动或在编写时自动完成。填充命令不仅仅适用于文本。例如，您也可以填写注释或文档字符串，使其不超过 80 个字符。

If you write a lot of text, you occasionally have to manually break paragraphs so the lines won’t exceed a certain length. You can use Emacs’s fill functionality to do this for you, either manually or automatically as you write. The fill command is useful for more than just text. For instance, you can fill comments or doc strings too so they fit in under 80 characters.

按键绑定 目的
M-q 补充段落
点在
C-x f 设置填充列宽度
C-x . 设置填充前缀
M-x auto-fill-mode 切换自动填充

当我在代码中编写注释时，我经常使用段落填充，使用M-q，并且主要模式通常使用C-x f用于该编程语言或文件类型的最佳实践来设置填充宽度 ( )。

I use paragraph filling, using M-q, often as I write comments in code and it is common for major modes to set a fill width (C-x f) with the best practices used for that programming language or file type.

看看夏洛克·福尔摩斯在《波西米亚丑闻》中引用的这句话，这句话已经超出了页面的内容：

Consider this quote by Sherlock Holmes in A Scandal in Bohemia that overruns the page:

'It is an old maxim of mine that when you excluded […]
'It is an old maxim of mine that when you excluded […]

将要点放在段落中并输入M-q：

After placing the point in the paragraph and typing M-q:

'It is an old maxim of mine that when you
have excluded the impossible, whatever
remains, however improbable, must be the
truth.'
'It is an old maxim of mine that when you
have excluded the impossible, whatever
remains, however improbable, must be the
truth.'

如果您输入M-q前缀C-u，Emacs 也会尝试调整文本：

If you type M-q with the prefix C-u, Emacs will attempt to justify the text also:

'It is an old maxim  of mine that when you
have  excluded  the  impossible,  whatever
remains, however  improbable, must  be the
truth.'
