如果您想插入文字换行符，请键入换行符C-q C-j– –符号，而不是您的返回键（它是.）LINE FEEDCARRIAGE RETURN

Line feed vs carriage return

If you want to insert a literal newline symbol, type C-q C-j as that is the newline – LINE FEED – symbol and not your return key (which is a CARRIAGE RETURN.)

引用的插入内容足够巧妙，可以使用第escape-glyph4面突出显示 ASCII 控制代码，以便您可以直观地发现它们。带引号的插入会对您输入的任何字符进行字面插入 - 例如，C-q ESC插入 ASCII 控制代码^[，也称为ESCAPE.

Quoted insert is clever enough to highlight ASCII control codes using the face escape-glyph4 so you can spot them visually. Quoted insert does a literal insert of any character you feed it — for example, C-q ESC inserts the ASCII control code ^[, also known as ESCAPE.

  1. DWIM 代表 Do What I Mean——Emacs 会尝试猜测你想要做什么的另一种说法。↩

  2. DWIM stands for Do What I Mean — another way of saying Emacs will try to guess what you want to do.↩

  3. PCRE 代表 Perl 兼容正则表达式——一种由 Perl 编程语言发明的正则表达式风格。↩

  4. PCRE stands for Perl-Compatible Regular Expressions — a style of regexp invented by the Perl programming language.↩

  5. ASpell 可以在这里找到https://aspell.net/win32/。↩

  6. ASpell can be found here https://aspell.net/win32/.↩

  7. 您可能还记得，您可以使用 进行自定义M-x customize-face。↩

  8. Which, as you may recall, you can customize with M-x customize-face.↩

Emacs 的实用

The Practicals of Emacs

“[...] Emacs 胜过所有其他编辑软件，就像正午的太阳胜过星星一样。它不仅更大、更亮；而且它只会让其他一切都消失。”

– Neal Stephenson，一开始……是命令行。

“[…] Emacs outshines all other editing software in approximately the same way that the noonday sun does the stars. It is not just bigger and brighter; it simply makes everything else vanish.”

– Neal Stephenson, In the Beginning… was the Command Line.

在前面的章节中，我几乎专门讨论了 Emacs 的理论方面。不过，激发你的大脑并寻找实际或新颖的应用是另一回事。对于大多数人来说，光有理论是不够的。在最后一章中，我将向您展示我所说的工作流程——在一定程度上涵盖特定领域或问题的演练。

In earlier chapters, I have almost exclusively talked about the theoretical aspects of Emacs. Galvanizing your brain and finding practical or novel applications is something else though; for most, theory is not enough. In this final chapter, I will show you what I call workflow — walkthroughs that cover a specific area or problem in some depth.

与前两章不同，我不会详细介绍本章中介绍的命令和功能。我把这个留给你自己去发现。如果您仍然不确定如何发现新功能，请继续阅读 — 本章的第一部分是探索 Emacs。

Unlike the last two chapters, I won’t cover the commands and features I introduce in this chapter in any great detail. I leave that to you to discover on your own time. If you are still unsure how to do discover new features, then read on — the first part of this chapter is Exploring Emacs.

探索 Emacs

Exploring Emacs

要真正掌握 Emacs，你必须学会​​如何查找东西。它是 Emacs 中的 alpha 和 omega。手册、书籍和博客文章对您的编辑环境（即 Emacs）做出了假设。一旦您更改变量、重新绑定键或更改 Emacs 以满足您自己的需求，您就创建了很少有人（如果有的话）拥有的独特的更改组合。因此，为了诊断问题，或者修复和改变你不喜欢的东西，你首先必须知道如何找到这些东西。

To truly master Emacs, you have to learn how to find things. It is alpha and omega in Emacs. Manuals, books and blog posts make assumptions about your editing environment — about Emacs. Once you change variables, rebind keys or alter Emacs to suit your own needs, you create a unique combination of changes that few other people, if any, have. Therefore, to diagnose issues, or fix and change things you dislike, you have to know how to find those things in the first place.

让我们探索一下 VC、Emacs 的版本控制界面。 VC 系统是 Emacs 中一个功能强大但未得到充分利用的工具，它公开了一个通用接口——用于版本历史记录、责备、提交、推送和拉取等操作——然后与您选择的版本控制系统进行对话。如果您经常使用多个版本控制系统，那么 VC 特别有用。

Let’s explore VC, Emacs’s Version Control interface. The VC system is a powerful and underutilized facility in Emacs that exposes a generic interface – for things like version history, blaming, committing, pushing and pulling – that then talks to your chosen version control system. VC is especially useful if you work regularly with more than one versioning system.

如果您以前不了解 VC，而您现在第一次接触它是通过阅读相关内容，那么您将如何了解它？

If you weren’t aware of VC before and your first introduction to it is reading about it now, how would you learn about it?

阅读手册

Reading the Manual

毫不奇怪，Emacs 的手册写得很好而且内容很丰富。让我们首先打开 Emacs 关于版本控制的手册。

Unsurprisingly, Emacs’s manual is well-written and extensive. Let’s begin by opening Emacs’s manual about Version Control.

  1. M-x info通过键入打开手册C-h i。
  2. Open the M-x info manual by typing C-h i.
  3. 导航到Emacs超链接并将其打开。
  4. Navigate to the Emacs hyperlink and open it.

  5. C-s使用version或进行搜索version control。

    你瞧，如果你点击C-s足够多的次数，最终你会看到版本控制手册。

  6. Search with C-s for version or version control.

    Lo and behold, if you tap C-s enough times eventually you’ll come across the Version Control manual that way.

因此，阅读手册效果很好，但并非每个功能都有手册。也许这些章节被埋在一个子子章中，不易触及。第三方软件包几乎从不附带手册info。

So, reading the manual works well — but not every feature has a manual. And perhaps the chapters are buried in a sub-sub-sub-chapter out of easy reach. And third-party packages almost never ship with info manuals.

关于信息手册
Apropos for info manuals

M-x info-apropos您可以使用带有搜索模式的命令，Emacs 将抓取所有已知的信息手册页以查找匹配的模式。如果您不确定某物在哪里，此命令是一个强大的工具。

You can use the command M-x info-apropos with a search pattern and Emacs will crawl all known info manual pages looking for matching patterns. If you are unsure of where something is, this command is a powerful tool.

使用 Apropos

Using Apropos

在Apropos中，我列出了使用 查询 Emacs 文档系统的所有多种方法apropos。其中 apropos 命令之一将搜索doc 字符串（Emacs 中大多数变量和函数附带的文档字符串）并列出匹配的函数或变量。搜索 Emacs 的文档字符串是最分散的查找方法：您实际上是在搜索纯文本文档。为此，请使用，这是搜索文档C-h d的 apropos 命令。

In Apropos, I listed all the many ways of querying Emacs’s documentation system using apropos. One of those apropos commands will search the doc string – the documentation string accompanying most variables and functions in Emacs – and list the matching function or variable. Searching Emacs’s documentation strings is the most scattered approach to finding things: you are literally searching plain text documentation. To do this, use C-h d, which is the apropos command that searches documentation.

Emacs Lisp 中的命名空间

Emacs Lisp 与其他 Lisp 不同，缺乏命名空间。在 Emacs 中使用模块或命名空间没有关注点分离。实际上，这并不是什么大问题（有更大的鱼要煎），但它确实意味着，非正式地，Emacs 中的包在其符号（函数、变量等）前面加上前缀，这样它们就不会发生冲突。

示例包括python-Python 主模式；apropos-与apropos相关的命令等等。

Namespacing in Emacs Lisp

Emacs Lisp, unlike other lisps, lacks namespacing. There is no separation of concerns using modules or namespaces in Emacs. In practice, it’s not a huge deal (there are bigger fish to fry) but it does mean that, informally, packages in Emacs prefix their symbols (functions, variables, etc.) so they don’t clash.

Examples include python- for the Python major mode; apropos- for apropos-related commands, and so on.

然而，如果您搜索version controlwith C-h d，第一个结果是这样的：

Nevertheless, if you search for version control with C-h d, the first result is this:

vc-mode

Function: Version Control minor mode. This
minor mode is automatically activated whenever
you visit a file under control of one of the
revision control systems in
`vc-handled-backends'.

VC commands are globally reachable under the
prefix `C-x v':
vc-mode

Function: Version Control minor mode. This
minor mode is automatically activated whenever
you visit a file under control of one of the
revision control systems in
`vc-handled-backends'.

VC commands are globally reachable under the
prefix `C-x v':

我们现在已经领先了。 VC模式是vc-mode。但是，我们想要它使用的前缀，它是vc-。

We now have a lead. The VC mode is vc-mode. However, we want the prefix it uses and it is vc-.

知道 VC 的前缀是vc-，我们可以使用M-x apropos-command, 绑定到C-h a, 来查找所有 VC 命令：

Knowing that VC’s prefix is vc-, we can use M-x apropos-command, bound to C-h a, to find all the VC commands:

M-x apropos-command RET
M-x apropos-command RET

然后根据提示输入：

Then at the prompt, enter:

Search for a command (word list or regexp): ^vc-
Search for a command (word list or regexp): ^vc-

Emacs 返回Apropos搜索的结果：

Emacs returns the results of the Apropos search:

vc-annotate  C-x v g
   Display the edit history of the current
   FILE using colors.
vc-check-headers      M-x ... RET
   Check if the current file has any headers in it.
vc-clear-context      M-x ... RET
   Clear all cached file properties.
[...]

   Display the edit history of the current
   FILE using colors.

   Check if the current file has any headers in it.
vc-clear-context      M-x ... RET
   Clear all cached file properties.
[...]

您将看到命令列表以及简要说明和键绑定（如果有）。

You’ll see a list of commands along with a brief description and the key binding, if any.

快速浏览一下就会发现一些有趣的命令。

A quick browse through reveals a handful of interesting commands.

按键和命令 描述
C-x v 前缀键为vc-
M-x vc-dir,C-x v d 显示当前目录的 VC 状态
M-x vc-diff,C-x v = 显示文件转速之间的差异
M-x vc-annotate,C-x v g 指责/注释当前文件
M-x vc-next-action,C-x v v 执行下一个逻辑动作
M-x vc-print-log,C-x v l 打印提交日志

有了这些，就很容易看出趋势。许多命令都绑定到前缀 key C-x v。下一步是通过附加 来查看哪些命令绑定到前缀键本身C-h。

With these, it’s easy to see a trend. A lot of the commands are bound to the prefix key C-x v. The next step would be to see what commands are bound to the prefix key itself by appending C-h.

C-h：探索前缀键

C-h: Exploring Prefix keys

在发现和记住键C-h中，我向您展示了在输入部分（前缀）键时追加会列出绑定到该前缀键的所有键。C-x v也不例外：输入C-x v C-h列出了绑定到该前缀键的所有键。

In Discovering and Remembering Keys, I showed you that appending C-h when you enter a partial (prefix) key lists all the keys bound to that prefix key. C-x v is no exception: typing C-x v C-h lists all the keys bound to this prefix key.

键入C-x v C-h会产生以下结果：

Typing C-x v C-h yields this:

Global Bindings Starting With C-x v:
key             binding

C-x v +         vc-update
C-x v =         vc-diff
C-x v D         vc-root-diff
C-x v G         vc-ignore
C-x v I         vc-log-incoming
C-x v L         vc-print-root-log
C-x v O         vc-log-outgoing
C-x v a         vc-update-change-log
C-x v b         vc-switch-backend
[...]
Global Bindings Starting With C-x v:
key             binding

C-x v +         vc-update
C-x v =         vc-diff
C-x v D         vc-root-diff
C-x v G         vc-ignore
C-x v I         vc-log-incoming
C-x v L         vc-print-root-log
C-x v O         vc-log-outgoing
C-x v a         vc-update-change-log
C-x v b         vc-switch-backend
[...]

这个命令的伟大之处在于它很容易输入。如果您忘记将C-x v =当前文件与最后一个文件修订版进行比较？没问题 –C-x v C-h表明绑定到C-x v =是M-x vc-diff。另一个明显的好处是它可以让您接触到您原本不会考虑使用甚至不知道存在的命令。也许您有一个新的需求，比如创建一个标签 ( C-x v s)，并且如果您不确定它的名称或绑定的内容 — 或者实际上，如果 Emacs 中存在这样的功能 — 那么C-h可能会对此有所帮助。

The great thing about this command is that it is so easy to type. If you forget that C-x v = diffs the current file with the last file revision? No problem – C-x v C-h shows that bound to C-x v = is M-x vc-diff. The other obvious benefit is it exposes you to commands you wouldn’t otherwise contemplate using, or even knew existed. Perhaps you have a new need to, say, create a tag (C-x v s) and if you’re unsure of what it’s called or what it is bound to – or indeed if such a feature even exists in Emacs – then C-h may shed some light on it.

C-h k：描述一个键的作用

C-h k: Describe what a key does

另一方面是拥有一把钥匙却不知道它的用途。该命令C-h k采用键绑定并显示活动缓冲区中与该命令绑定的内容。例如，C-h k后跟C-x v v不仅显示命令的名称，还显示该命令的文档字符串。通常，文本是描述性的并解释命令的作用：

On the other end of the spectrum is having a key and not knowing what it does. The command C-h k takes a key binding and shows you what is bound to that command in the active buffer. For instance, C-h k followed by C-x v v shows you not only the name of the command but the doc string for that command. Usually, the text is descriptive and explains what the command does:

C-x v v runs the command vc-next-action (found
in global-map), which is an interactive
autoloaded compiled Lisp function in `vc.el'.

It is bound to C-x v v, <menu-bar> <tools> <vc>
<vc-next-action>.

(vc-next-action VERBOSE)

Do the next logical version control operation on
the current fileset. This requires that all
files in the current VC fileset be in the same
state. If not, signal an error.

 ...
C-x v v runs the command vc-next-action (found
in global-map), which is an interactive
autoloaded compiled Lisp function in `vc.el'.

It is bound to C-x v v, <menu-bar> <tools> <vc>
<vc-next-action>.

(vc-next-action VERBOSE)

Do the next logical version control operation on
the current fileset. This requires that all
files in the current VC fileset be in the same
state. If not, signal an error.

 ...

上面显示的是按键绑定及其运行的命令。它还向您显示在何处找到该命令（在本例中是在全局映射中，因为它是全局键）以及包含该命令的库文件。接下来，列出它占用的所有键（可能有多个绑定），如果您要直接从 lisp 调用命令，则后面是函数参数。最后是描述该命令的文档字符串。

Shown above is the key binding and the command it runs. It also shows you where the command was found – in this case in the global map, because it is a global key – and the library file containing the command. Next, all the keys (it may have multiple bindings) it occupies are listed, followed by the function arguments if you were to call the command directly from lisp. And then, finally, is the documentation string describing the command.

所有这些信息都是在您调用时动态生成的C-h k。

All this information is dynamically generated when you call C-h k.

其轻微的缺点C-h k是它的目标受众是 elisp 黑客而不是最终用户；文档字符串从技术角度描述了命令如何工作，这通常意味着解释每个参数以及与最终用户无关的其他技术细节如何工作。但这对于有技术头脑的人来说通常不是问题，即使您不是 Lisp 开发人员。

The slight downside of C-h k is that its intended audience are elisp hackers and not end users; the doc string describes how the command works from a technical perspective and that usually means explaining how each argument, and other technical minutia of little relevance to end users, works. But that’s usually not a problem for a technically-minded person, even if you are not a lisp developer.

描述命令
Describing commands

如果您有命令的名称，例如vc-dir，您可以使用C-h f，Emacs 将描述该命令的作用。

If you have the name of a command, such as vc-dir, you can use C-h f and Emacs will describe what the command does.

C-h m：查找模式命令

C-h m: Finding mode commands

如果运行该命令C-x v d，则会出现一个新缓冲区，其中显示当前缓冲区存储库的版本状态；此处显示未跟踪和修改的文件等内容。但你如何与它互动呢？你如何发现如何使用VC的状态缓冲区？

If you run the command C-x v d, a new buffer appears showing you the version status of your current buffer’s repository; things like untracked and modified files are shown here. But how do you interact with it? How do you discover how to use VC’s status buffer?

答案是C-h m，一个描述模式的帮助命令。它显示您调用的缓冲区中所有活动的主要和次要模式的文档字符串，以及这些主要和次要模式特有的任何键。换句话说，使用此命令来找出每个主要和次要模式的作用（以及它们公开的键（如果有））。

The answer is C-h m, a help command that describes a mode. It displays the documentation strings for all major and minor modes active in the buffer you called it, alongside any keys unique to those major and minor modes. In other words, use this command to figure out what each major and minor mode does (and what keys, if any, they expose).

因此，C-h m在 VC 状态缓冲区内调用会产生大量密钥和文档：

So, calling C-h m inside a VC status buffer yields a plethora of keys and documentation:

key             binding

C-c             Prefix Command
TAB             vc-dir-next-directory
C-k             vc-dir-kill-line
RET             vc-dir-find-file

...
key             binding

C-c             Prefix Command
TAB             vc-dir-next-directory
C-k             vc-dir-kill-line
RET             vc-dir-find-file

...

从那时起，只需单击（用RET鼠标）您感兴趣的每个超链接即可。

From then on it’s a simple matter of clicking (with RET or the mouse) on each hyperlink you are interested in.

项目管理

Project Management

从历史上看，Emacs 总是孤立地查看文件，而不是作为相关文件的集合。尽管自 2002 年起就成为filesetsEmacs 的一部分，而且如此晦涩难懂，甚至连维护者都忘记了它，但 Emacs 大多将这个角色留给了目录局部变量1以及 Makefile 等外部工具。这使得 Emacs 维护者和社区很难建立一致的叙述来处理多个文件，例如搜索和替换、编译等。这种情况在 Emacs 23 中发生了变化，EDE 是 CEDET 的子集，它本身是一个非常复杂的工具套件，可以提供类似于 Emacs IDE 的功能。

Historically, Emacs always looked at files in isolation and never as a collection of related files. Despite the presence of filesets – a part of Emacs since 2002, and yet so obscure even the maintainers forgot about it – Emacs mostly left that role to directory-local variables1 and external tools like Makefile and friends. That made it hard for the Emacs maintainers and the community to build a consistent narrative to working with multiple files, such as searching & replacing, compiling, and so on. That changed in Emacs 23 with EDE, a subset of CEDET, itself a very complex suite of tools to give Emacs IDE-like functionality.

什么是 CEDET？

CEDET 是一个提供语言解析、语义分析和代码完成的工具集合；项目管理;代码生成；绘制图表；和更多。它与 C 和 C++ 配合良好，并在该社区拥有大量追随者，但从未在其他地方真正流行起来。 Emacs 23 中包含了一个删节版本。

What is CEDET?

CEDET is a collection of tools that offer language parsing with semantic analysis and code completion; project management; code generation; diagramming; and more. It works well with C & C++ and had a large following in that community, but never really caught on elsewhere. An abridged version was included in Emacs 23.

与 CEDET 一样，EDE 从未真正流行起来，与此同时，随着多语言项目变得更加普遍，大量第三方库（如Projectile ）蓬勃发展。他们还改变了项目管理的概念，将其基于源代码控制存储库的存在，而不是您有选择地添加或删除文件的静态项目文件。

Like CEDET, EDE never really caught on, and in the meantime a large number of third-party libraries (like Projectile) flourished as multi-language projects became more common. They also changed the notion of what project management should be by basing it around the existence of a source control repository instead of a static project file that you selectively add or remove files from.

尽管存在 EDE，Emacs 25 也包含了一个新的项目管理工具，但直到 Emacs 27 才达到成熟，其名称富有想象力project.el。它类似于Projectile，并且支持自定义后端，但默认使用基于 VC 的系统2来推断属于该项目的文件。

Despite the existence of EDE, Emacs 25 included – but it did not reach maturity until Emacs 27 – a new project management tool with the imaginative name project.el. It’s similar to Projectile, and supports custom backends, but defaults to a VC-based system2 to infer the files that belong to the project.

该项目套件广泛提供以下开箱即用的功能：

The project suite broadly offers these features out of the box:

从 VC 索引文件推断文件
Inferring files from VC-indexed files

Emacs 会自动猜测与项目相关的文件，并假设如果该文件由您正在使用的版本控制系统索引，那么它可能与项目用户相关。

Emacs will automatically guess the files relevant to the project with the assumption that if the file is indexed by the version control system you are using, then it is probably relevant to the project user.

从 VC 主目录推断出的根目录
Root directory inferred from the VC home directory

重要的是，文件搜索、linting 工具、编译命令等通常是相对于根目录执行的。

Important, as file searches, linting tools, compile commands, and so on are often executed relative to a root directory.

对枚举项目文件的内置支持
Built-in support for enumerating project files

用于搜索和替换项目中的多个文件或项目文件的子集。

For searching and replacing across multiple files in the project, or subsets of the project files.

选择适用于项目的命令
Selection of commands that work with projects

比如打开一个M-x shell或者M-x dired缓冲区；查找文件；杀死与项目相关的缓冲区；或按名称切换到另一个项目。

Such as opening a M-x shell or M-x dired buffer; finding a file; killing project-related buffers; or switching to another project by name.

虽然我在这里列出的细节可能看起来很底层，但它们很重要：这是 Emacs 中一个非常被错过的功能，并且奠定良好的基础（他们已经做到了）很重要，因为更广泛的社区的采用是至关重要的，因为它在这儿。

Though the details I listed here may seem low-level, they are important: this is a sorely-missed feature in Emacs, and laying a good foundation – which they have done – is important as uptake in the wider community is essential now that it is here.

对于大多数 Emacs 用户来说，这个项目包就是他们开始在 Emacs 中进行项目管理所需的全部。为此，您只需要一个 Git 或 Hg 存储库。我建议您尝试一下这个包；如果你发现它有所欠缺，那么Projectile是一个优秀的第三方包。

For most Emacs users this project package is all they need to get started with project management in Emacs. To do so, all you need is a Git or Hg repository. I recommend you give this package a shot; if you find it lacking, then Projectile is an excellent third-party package.

有一个前缀键盘映射专为绑定到的项目保留C-x p：

There’s a prefix keymap reserved just for projects bound to C-x p:

项目键 描述
C-x p p 切换到其他已知项目
C-x p b 切换到缓冲区
C-x p f 在项目中找到文件3
C-x p k 杀死项目缓冲区
C-x p g 通过正则表达式搜索
C-x p r 查询正则表达式搜索和替换
C-x p c 编译工程
C-x p v 打开 VC 对话框
C-x p s 打开外壳
C-x p d 打开 Dired 缓冲区

与更通用的对应项不同，键绑定的C-x p f工作C-x p b方式相同，但当然仅限于您的项目已知的文件。所有命令也是如此：它们将在后端定义的项目范围内运行 - 默认情况下，后端是 VC 根目录及其已知的任何文件。

Unlike their more general counterparts, key bindings like C-x p f and C-x p b work the same way but are of course restricted to files known to your project. The same goes for all the commands: they will act within the confines of the project as defined by its backend — which, by default, is the VC root directory and any files known to it.

Xref：Emacs 中的交叉引用

Xref: Cross-References in Emacs

外部参照是一个统一的平台，用于将符号（如下面的点）与其定义进行匹配，然后将它们呈现给用户，以便他们可以编辑或跳转到它们。它通过可配置的后端来实现这一点，这些后端可能会根据执行它的缓冲区的主要模式而改变。它设计用于与第三方包（尽管尚未广泛采用）以及生成自己的符号定义列表的工具一起使用。

Xref is a unified platform to match symbols (like the one under point) to their definitions, and then present them to the user so they can edit or jump to them. It does this with configurable backends that may change depending on the major mode of the buffer you execute it in. It’s designed to work with third-party packages, though it’s not widely adopted yet, and tools that generate their own lists of symbol definitions.

尽管 Xref 是在 Emacs 25 中引入的，但它仍然站稳脚跟。它正在慢慢取代许多在 Emacs 的各个角落尝试类似事情的临时实现。

Though introduced in Emacs 25, Xref is still finding its footing. It’s slowly replacing a number of ad hoc implementations that attempt a similar thing in various dusty corners of Emacs.

您应该了解的四个最常见的命令是：

The four most common commands you should know about are:

按键 描述
M-. 在点处查找定义
M-, 弹出标记4并返回
M-? 查找与模式匹配的参考
C-M-. 查找与模式匹配的符号

默认情况下，外部参照不附带有用的符号查找后端。如果您使用 调用外部参照的查找定义M-.，并且您的主要模式尚未配置外部参照，则很可能会要求您首先查找 TAGS 表文件。 TAGS 文件是一种生成标识符及其位置的老式方法，并将它们存储在文件系统上的大型静态查找表中以提高性能。如果您从事天文数字般的大型项目，它们仍然很有用；对于我们大多数人来说，动态搜索文件系统（或查询语言服务器）的工具通常就是您所需要的。

Xref does not come with useful symbol lookup backends by default. If you invoke xref’s find a definition with M-., you’re more likely asked to find a TAGS table file first if your major mode does not have xref configured already. TAGS files are an old-school way of generating identifiers and their locations and them storing them in large, static lookup tables on your file system to improve performance. They are still useful if you work on astronomically large projects; for most of us, tools that search your file system on the fly (or query a Language Server) is usually all you need.

为了帮助您入门，我建议您尝试第三方软件包，尽管它的名称如此，但它利用、 、或等dumb-jump文件搜索器的速度来查找与您的主要模式相关的匹配项。对于大多数事情来说，这已经足够好了。特别是在现代硬件上速度快得令人难以置信，并且与 Emacs 5配合得很好。grepackagripgrepripgrep

To get you started, I recommend you try the third-party package dumb-jump which, despite its name, leverages the speed of file searchers like grep, ack, ag or ripgrep to find matches relevant to your major mode. For most things it’s more than good enough. ripgrep in particular is unfathomably fast on modern hardware and pairs well with Emacs5.

配置完成后，您可以使用 跳转到标识符M-.并返回，您可以使用 弹出堆栈中的标记M-,。如果有多个定义，或者 Emacs 不确定哪一个是最好的，您将看到一个匹配定义的缓冲区。您还可以使用 与正则表达式进行匹配C-M-.。

Once configured, you can jump to an identifier with M-. and to return you can pop markers off the stack with M-,. If there are multiple definitions, or if Emacs is not sure which one is the best one, you’ll be shown a buffer of definitions that match. You can also match against a regexp with C-M-..

弹出堆栈

Emacs 中的一组常见术语是从堆栈中弹出某些内容，指的是从列表中删除最近添加的项目的计算机科学概念。您会在 Emacs 面向用户的命令中到处看到它，就像这个。

Popping the Stack

A common set of terms in Emacs is to pop something off the stack, referring to the Computer Science concept of removing the most recently added item to a list. You’ll see it here and there in Emacs’s user-facing commands, like this one.

如果没有其他可用的后端，键M-?绑定可能会回退到使用常见文件搜索工具搜索项目目录grep。通常，这是一个不错的起点。

The M-? key binding may fall back to searching your project directory with common file searching tools like grep if there is no other backend available. Usually, that is an OK starting point.

结果显示在外部参照定义缓冲区中。

The results are shown in an xref definitions buffer.

外部参照缓冲区键 描述
RET 跳转到定义
TAB 跳转到定义并隐藏外部参照
C-o 显示定义
.和, 向上或向下导航
r 查询搜索和替换正则表达式

.和都可,用于快速浏览匹配列表以找到您需要的匹配项。当您浏览列表时，Emacs 将跳转到匹配项。一旦您对选择感到满意，您可以按TAB跳转到该点的定义并关闭外部参照缓冲区。

Both . and , are useful for quickly browsing through lists of matches to find the one you need. Emacs will jump to the matches as you move through the list. Once you’re happy with the selection you can press TAB to jump to the definition at point and close the xref buffer.

键入r后，系统会提示您输入正则表达式以进行搜索和替换。它的工作原理与我在“搜索和替换”C-M-%中谈到的相同。

Type r and you’re prompted for a regexp to search and replace with. It works the same as C-M-% that I talked about in Search and Replace.

外部参照和定向

Dired 中也提供外部参照：您可以键入A搜索以及Q在标记的文件中搜索和替换。

Xref and Dired

Xref is also available in Dired: you can type A to search and Q to search & replace in marked files.

使用日志文件

Working with Log Files

仔细研究日志文件是一项常见的活动，Emacs 中有一些工具可以让您轻松掌握日志文件。

Poring over log files is a common activity and there are tools in Emacs that makes it a snap to stay on top of them.

按键 描述
C-x C-f 找到一个文件
C-x C-r 查找处于只读模式的文件
C-x C-q 切换只读模式

打开日志文件是第一步。您可能想以只读方式打开它；如果文件不可写，Emacs 将M-x read-only-mode自动打开它。您可以使用 来打开和关闭它C-x C-q。您可能想要禁用只读模式的原因是这样您可以对缓冲区应用破坏性更改，例如刷新或保留行：

Opening the log file is the first step. You may want to open it read only; if the file is not writable, Emacs will open it in M-x read-only-mode automatically. You can toggle it on and off with C-x C-q. The reason you may want to disable read only mode is so you can apply destructive changes to the buffer, such as flushing or keeping lines:

按键 描述
M-x flush-lines 刷新与模式匹配的行
M-x keep-lines 仅保留与模式匹配的行
M-s o 列出与模式匹配的行

M-s o创建与模式匹配的发生模式缓冲区。很多人从未考虑过的是，您可以M-s o在发生模式缓冲区上重新运行以进一步过滤它。

M-s o creates an Occur mode buffer matching a pattern. What a lot of people never consider is that you can re-run M-s o on an Occur mode buffer to filter it further.

如果您滚动浏览一行又一行几乎相同的日志条目，很容易遭受模式盲症并错过一些事情。 Emacs 的荧光笔在这里特别有用，因为它们以不同的颜色突出显示缓冲区中的模式，以便您可以区分它们：

It’s easy to suffer pattern blindness and miss things if you scroll through row after row of nearly-identical log entries. Emacs’s highlighters are especially useful here, as they highlight patterns in your buffer in different colors so you can tell them apart:

按键 描述
M-s h p 突出显示一个短语
M-s h r 突出显示正则表达式
M-s h . 突出显示该点的符号
M-s h u 删除点下的突出显示

荧光笔非常有用，即使您不将密钥存入内存，只需知道它们都已命名highlight-，因此在需要时很容易使用M-x.

Highlighters are incredibly useful and, even if you don’t commit the keys to memory, just know that they are all named highlight- and are thus easy to execute, when you need them, with M-x.

日志文件很少是静态文件：它们不断更改或附加。您可以启用次要模式，以便 Emacs 在文件系统上的文件发生更改时刷新该文件。在较新版本的 Emacs 上，它将使用文件更改事件（在 Windows 和 Linux 上）并在不支持通知的旧系统上进行轮询。

Log files are rarely static files: they are constantly changing or appended to. You can enable a minor mode so Emacs refreshes a file if it changes on your file system. On newer versions of Emacs, it’ll use file change events (on Windows and Linux) and polling on older systems that don’t support notifications.

按键 描述
M-x auto-revert-mode 恢复缓冲区时
文件更改
M-x auto-revert-tail-mode 追加更改的时间
文件更改

两种模式相似。M-x auto-revert-mode如果文件内容经常更改，则很有用。 Emacs 检测到更改并简单地重新加载整个文件。M-x auto-revert-tail-mode另一方面，其工作方式与 相同tail -f：当文件更改时，更改将附加到缓冲区的末尾，Emacs 将相应地滚动。

Both modes are similar. M-x auto-revert-mode is useful if the file content changes frequently. Emacs detects changes and simply reloads the entire file. M-x auto-revert-tail-mode, on the other hand, works the same way as tail -f: when the file changes, the changes are appended to the end of the buffer and Emacs will scroll accordingly.

浏览其他文件

Browsing Other Files

当然，没有什么可以阻止您将这些概念应用到其他文件类型。例如，Emacs 附带自动压缩模式（默认情况下启用的被动模式），当您打开和保存文件时，它会自动解压缩和重新压缩文件。结合它M-x dired，您可以浏览压缩档案，就像它们是目录一样。

There is, of course, nothing stopping you from applying these concepts to other file types. For instance, Emacs ships with auto compression mode – a passive mode enabled by default – that automatically de-compresses and re-compresses files when you open and save them. Combine it with M-x dired and you can browse compressed archives as though they were directories.

Dired：缩略图浏览器

Dired: Thumbnail Image Browser

您可以键入M-x image-dired并进入 Emacs 的图像缩略图浏览器。您将看到一个带有缩略图的窗口和一个带有文件的干燥窗口。

You can type M-x image-dired and enter Emacs’s image thumbnail browser. You’ll see a window with thumbnails and a dired window with the files.

缩略图缓冲区附带大量按键绑定。这里是其中的一些：

C-p,C-n 向上或向下移动一行缩略图
d, m,u 删除、标记或取消标记（如 Dired）
t t,t u 标记或取消标记图像

全尺寸图像缓冲区提供三个键绑定：

The full-sized image buffer offers three key bindings:

图像键 描述
q 辞职
s 调整图像大小以适应窗口

但请注意，从 dired 打开文件会使您进入图像模式（通用图像查看器（功能更强大）），而不是Dired 图像显示模式。

Note, though, that opening the file from dired puts you in Image Mode, a general-purpose image viewer (and far more powerful), and not Dired Image Display Mode.

DocView：查看丰富的文档

DocView: Viewing Rich Documents

如果您的系统相对较新，并且安装了正确的程序6，您可以利用 Emacs 渲染图像的功能，并在打开 PDF 和 Open / MS Office 文档时即时转换它们。

If your system is relatively modern, and if you have the right programs installed6, you can take advantage of Emacs’s ability to render images and have it convert PDF and Open / MS Office documents on-the-fly when you open them.

文档查看支持

有关 Emacs 将尝试转换的内容的完整列表，您可以键入C-h v auto-mode-alist并搜索doc-view.您可能还记得本书早期我们讨论的主要模式加载顺序中的变量。

DocView Support

For a full list of what Emacs will attempt to convert, you can type C-h v auto-mode-alist and search for doc-view. You may remember that variable from early on in the book where we talked about Major mode load order.

要使用 DocView，请打开 PDF 或其他支持的二进制文件，Emacs 将尝试为您呈现它。打开后，您可以使用的一些按键绑定是：

To use DocView, open a PDF or other supported binary file and Emacs will attempt to render it for you. When open, some of the key bindings available to you are:

按键 描述
n,p 向上翻页/向下翻页
<prior>,<next> 向上翻页/向下翻页
SPC 向下滚动
S-SPC 向上滑动
M-<,M-> 跳转到第一页/最后一页
+, -,0 放大、缩小或重置
W, H, P,F 适合宽度、高度、页面或窗口

这只是可用键绑定的一小部分。值得注意的是SPC，S-SPC它们在文档中缓慢推进，并且适用于您正在阅读的文档。+和两者-对于放大或缩小都很有用。您还可以让 Emacs 负责猜测W或H调整文档大小以适合窗口的宽度或高度。F另一方面，将调整窗口大小以适合文档。

This is but a small subset of available key bindings. Of note is SPC and S-SPC as they slowly advance through the document, and are intended for documents that you are reading. Both + and - are useful for zooming in or out. You can also let Emacs take care of the guesswork with W or H to resize the document to fit the width or height of the window. F, on the other hand, will resize your window to fit the document.

如果图像看起来像素化，您可以通过以下方法增加 DPI：

If the images look pixelated, you can increase the DPI with:

(setq doc-view-resolution 400)
(setq doc-view-resolution 400)

幻灯片查看器

M-x doc-view-presentationEmacs 27 获得了将 Doc View 缓冲区转换为全屏幻灯片放映的命令。您可以使用n和来在“幻灯片”之间导航p，然后q退出。

Slide Show Viewer

Emacs 27 gained the command M-x doc-view-presentation that turns a Doc View buffer into a full screen slide show. You can navigate between “slides” with n and p, and q to quit.

TRAMP：远程文件编辑

TRAMP: Remote File Editing

远程文件编辑通常很尴尬：您必须与远程环境进行交互，通常使用终端仿真器，并且几乎总是没有图形界面和常用设置的保真度。尽管随身携带.emacs.d很简单，但仍然很尴尬。对于技术的所有改进，远程文件编辑通常都需要权衡。

Remote file editing is usually awkward: you have to interact with a remote environment, usually using a terminal emulator, and almost always without the fidelity of a graphical interface and your usual settings. Even though it’s trivial to move your .emacs.d around with you, it is still awkward. For all the improvements in technology, remote file editing usually involves trade-offs.

Emacs 的 TRAMP 7系统是一个透明代理，旨在解决您可能遇到的大多数远程文件交互问题。毫无疑问，TRAMP 是Emacs 中最酷的功能。

Emacs’s TRAMP7 system is a transparent proxy that aims to solve most of the remote file interaction woes you are likely to encounter. TRAMP is, without a doubt, the coolest feature in Emacs.

TRAMP 通过监视C-x C-f（和其他命令）来工作，它会检测您何时尝试使用特殊语法访问远程文件，这与使用等命令行工具不同scp。 TRAMP 的伟大之处在于它的完全透明度。如果您不知道 Emacs 具有远程编辑功能，您永远不会知道。可以快速、无缝地访问和编辑远程文件。

TRAMP works by monitoring C-x C-f (and other commands) and it detects when you try to access remote files using a special syntax not unlike what command line tools such as scp use. What makes TRAMP great is its total transparency. If you didn’t know Emacs had remote editing capabilities, you’d never know. It is quick and seamless to reach out and edit remote files.

所有 TRAMP 连接都遵循以下语法：

All TRAMP connections follow this syntax:

/protocol:[user@]hostname[#port]:
/protocol:[user@]hostname[#port]:

TRAMP 支持许多协议 - 无论是旧的还是新的 - 但现在您最有可能使用的协议是ssh或可能scp。有关 TRAMP 协议及其工作原理的完整列表，请参阅变量tramp-methods或信息手册页(tramp) Internal methods。

TRAMP supports many protocols – both old and new – but nowadays the one you are most likely to use is ssh or maybe scp. For a full list of TRAMP protocols and how they work, consult the variable tramp-methods or the info manual page (tramp) Internal methods.

微软Windows

在 Windows 上，您的协议选择有所不同。如果您不使用 Cygwin 或 OpenSSH 的交叉编译版本，则需要安装 PuTTYplink.exe工具并用作plink协议。

Microsoft Windows

On Windows, your protocol choices differ. If you don’t use Cygwin or a cross-compiled version of OpenSSH, you will need to install PuTTY’s plink.exe tool and use plink as the protocol.

尽管如今的服务器环境比 25 年前更加同质，但 TRAMP 做了很多幕后工作，以确保远程 shell 提供一致（且可靠）的体验。我上面提到的变量tramp-methods控制 TRAMP 如何处理每种协议类型。如果您使用晦涩的系统，则可能需要自定义此变量。

Although the server landscape is a lot more homogeneous today than it was 25 years ago, TRAMP does a lot of behind-the-scenes work to ensure the remote shell delivers a consistent (and dependable) experience. The variable I mentioned above, tramp-methods, controls how TRAMP handles each protocol type. If you work with obscure systems, you may have to customize this variable.

TRAMP 的另一个很棒的功能是，当您输入协议时，它会解析您的~/.ssh/config文件并自动完成已知主机。ssh当然，您可以手动指定主机名、用户名和端口，后两者是可选的。

Another nifty feature of TRAMP is that it parses your ~/.ssh/config file and autocompletes known hosts when you have entered ssh as your protocol. You can, of course, specify both a hostname, username, and port manually, with the latter two being optional.

SSH 配置

如果您使用ssh，我强烈建议您使用配置文件，因为您可以将所有连接和凭据详细信息存储在一个易于记住的名称中。

有关详细信息，请键入M-x man RET ssh_config以阅读 Emacs 中的相关手册页。

SSH config

If you use ssh, I strongly suggest you use the configuration file as you can store all the connection and credential details in an easy to remember name.

For more information, type M-x man RET ssh_config to read the relevant manual page in Emacs.

最后，要实际调用 TRAMP，您必须从根调用它 -//在 FIDO 或 IDO 模式下键入将跳转到根 - 并遵循上述格式。

Finally, to actually invoke TRAMP you must call it from the root – typing // in FIDO or IDO mode will jump to the root – and follow the format as above.

舵

如果您还使用 Helm，则可以安装一个名为的第三方软件包，helm-tramp该软件包会自动生成您可能想要使用的所有合理的 TRAMP 配置。您还可以找到 TRAMP 扩展，添加对 Docker 等工具的支持。

Helm

If you also use Helm, you can install a third-party package called helm-tramp that auto generates all reasonable TRAMP configurations you may want to use. You can also find TRAMP extensions that add support for tools like Docker.

请注意，在您输入第二个之前，Emacs 不会启动远程连接:，如下所示：

Note that Emacs will not initiate a remote connection until you enter the second :, like so:

/ssh:homer@powerplant:/var/log/reactor.log
/ssh:homer@powerplant:/var/log/reactor.log

powerplant上面的命令使用ssh协议和homer用户连接到服务器。然后它打开该文件/var/log/reactor.log。

The command above connects to the server powerplant using ssh as the protocol and homer as the user. It then opens the file /var/log/reactor.log.

TRAMP 附带了 中描述的默认方法（协议），tramp-default-method无需指定 TRAMP 默认情况下应使用的协议。但是，从 Emacs 26 开始，您必须通过键入 向 Emacs 表明您想要默认方法/-:。我建议您对其进行自定义并将其从 更改为scp（ssh或者plink如果您使用的是 Windows。）

TRAMP comes with a default method (protocol) described in tramp-default-method that removes the need to specify the protocol TRAMP should use by default. However, as of Emacs 26, you must indicate to Emacs that you want the default method by typing /-:. I suggest you customize it and change it from scp to ssh (or plink if you’re on Windows.)

默认目录和远程编辑

The Default Directory and Remote Editing

每个缓冲区都有一个default-directory变量。用 elisp 术语来说，该变量是buffer local。每个缓冲区都有自己的default-directory变量，因为它只是该缓冲区的本地变量，而不是全局变量（就像 Emacs 中默认的变量一样）。

Every buffer has a default-directory variable. The variable, in elisp terms, is buffer local. Each buffer has its own default-directory variable as it is local to just that buffer and not global (like variables are by default in Emacs).

当您C-x C-f在缓冲区中键入内容时，Emacs 会查找default-directory并选择该目录作为打开新文件的默认目录。这是明智的，因为您可能想要打开与当前缓冲区共享目录的其他C-x C-f文件。在 中编辑文件时键入/etc意味着您可能想在 中打开另一个文件/etc，因此 Emacs 会选择该文件作为默认目录。

When you type C-x C-f in a buffer, Emacs looks to default-directory and picks that directory as the default one for opening new files. That is sensible as you may want to open other files that share a directory with the current buffer. Typing C-x C-f while editing a file in /etc means you may want to open another file in /etc, so Emacs picks that as your default directory.

此功能与 TRAMP 和远程文件的工作方式相同。C-x C-f在远程编辑的文件中调用时，Emacs 会自动查询远程系统而不是本地系统，让您轻松打开其他远程文件。

This feature works identically with TRAMP and remote files. Invoking C-x C-f in a remotely-edited file and Emacs automatically queries the remote system and not your local one, letting you easily open other remote files.

当您打开一个文件时，TRAMP 在幕后发挥其魔力，您最终会在 Emacs 中得到一个看起来非常像本地文件的文件。判断文件是远程的唯一可见方式是模型行：a@出现在文件名之前，default-directory反映 TRAMP 注释的文件路径；尝试一下，用 来检查变量C-h v。

When you have opened a file, TRAMP does its magic behind-the-scenes and you’ll end up with a file in Emacs that looks and seems much like a local one. The only visible way of telling that a file is remote is the modeline: a @ appears before the file name and default-directory reflects the TRAMP-annotated file path; try it, inspect the variable with C-h v.

因此，您可以远程编辑文件，但由于 TRAMP 和 Emacs 之间的紧密集成，您可以做更多的事情。调用命令可以与 Emacs 和 TRAMPM-x rgrep 无缝配合。该命令在远程计算机上运行，​​结果将反馈到 Emacs，就像您在本地调用该命令一样。

So, you can edit files remotely, but because of the tight integration between TRAMP and Emacs you can do so much more. Invoking commands like M-x rgrep works seamlessly with Emacs and TRAMP. The command is run on the remote machine and the results are fed back to Emacs as though you’d called the command locally.

您可以远程调用的事情无穷无尽。以下是我远程使用的一些命令：

There is no end to the things you can call remotely. Here are some of the commands that I use remotely:

C-x d： 迪雷德
C-x d: Dired

所有命令都通过远程会话进行隧道传输，因此您可以使用 dired 管理文件和目录，就像它们在本地一样。

您甚至可以在远程和本地定向会话之间复制文件，TRAMP 将透明地复制文件。

All commands are tunnelled through the remote session so you can manage your files and directories with dired as though they were local.

You can even copy files between remote and local dired sessions and TRAMP will transparently copy the files across.

M-x compile：编译
M-x compile: Compile

您可以输入编译命令，例如make或python manage.py runserver，或者实际上任何您喜欢的命令。 Emacs 远程运行该命令，输出显示在*compilation*缓冲区中。您甚至可以远程运行交互式服务器并提供实时反馈。

You can enter a compile command, such as make or python manage.py runserver, or indeed anything you like. Emacs runs the command remotely and the output is shown in the *compilation* buffer. You can even run interactive servers remotely with live feedback.

M-x rgrep：Grep命令
M-x rgrep: Grep Commands

find和都grep被远程调用，并且与其他命令一样，结果显示在 Emacs 中。 grep 输出中的超链接文件可以正确打开远程文件。

Both find and grep are called remotely and, as with the other commands, the results are displayed in Emacs. Hyperlinked files in the grep output correctly open the remote file.

M-x shell: Emacs 的 Shell 包装器
M-x shell: Emacs’s Shell Wrapper

启动远程登录 shell 并让您控制它。它的工作方式就像M-x shell在本地计算机上一样，但本例中的 shell 显然位于远程计算机上。TAB-completion（M-x shell由 Emacs 而不是实际的 shell 完成）也可以。

Starts a remote login shell and hands you control of it. It works just like M-x shell on a local machine but the shell in this case is, obviously, on the remote machine. TAB-completion – which in M-x shell is done by Emacs and not the actual shell – also works.

M-x eshell：EShell，Emacs 的 elisp shell
M-x eshell: EShell, Emacs’s elisp shell

Eshell 是用 Emacs lisp 编写的 shell。它还可以透明地与远程 TRAMP 连接一起使用。事实上，您可以cd直接从本地 shell 进入远程目录。

Eshell is a shell written in Emacs lisp. It also transparently works with remote TRAMP connections. In fact, you can cd into remote directories straight from a local shell.

多跳和用户切换

Multi-Hops and User Switching

TRAMP 的另一个有用功能是使用su或进行帐户提升sudo。如果您想以其他用户或根用户身份编辑文件，即使对于本地文件，这也非常有用。

Another useful ability of TRAMP is account elevation with su or sudo. This is extremely useful even for local files if you want to edit a file as another user or root.

执行此操作的能力也与多跳的概念紧密相关：通过中间主机连接到远程主机。例如，如果您必须访问内部服务器，但首先必须通过公共服务器进行连接以提高安全性；另一种情况是，如果您必须以一个用户身份登录，但随后必须以 root 身份调用 sudo 来编辑远程服务器上的文件。

The ability to do this also neatly ties in with the concept of multi-hops: connecting to a remote host through intermediate hosts. An example is if you have to access an internal server but first have to connect through a public server for added security; another is if you have to log in as one user but then have to call out to sudo to edit a file as root on a remote server.

sudo让我们从请求访问的更简单的情况开始/etc/fstab：

Let’s start out with the simpler case of requesting sudo access to /etc/fstab:

/sudo:root@localhost:/etc/fstab
/sudo:root@localhost:/etc/fstab

正如您所看到的，语法与普通的远程 TRAMP 连接相同 - 只是我们正在使用sudo并且我们正在本地连接。您通常可以省略root@，因为 TRAMP 足够聪明，可以猜到它是root。请记住，该文件在技术上是远程的（在 TRAMP 意义上），因此适用通常的规则default-directory。C-x C-f在远程缓冲区中打开文件将会以sudo.

As you can see, the syntax is identical to a normal remote TRAMP connection — only we’re using sudo and we are connecting locally. You can usually omit root@ as TRAMP is clever enough to guess it’s root. Keep in mind that this file is technically remote (in the TRAMP sense) so the usual rules about default-directory apply. Opening files with C-x C-f in a remote buffer will open other files as sudo.

TRAMP 中的多跳通常是通过自定义来完成的，tramp-default-proxies-alist但我发现它有点繁琐； ad hoc语法要简单得多：

Multi-hopping in TRAMP is usually done by customizing tramp-default-proxies-alist but I find it a bit fiddly; the ad hoc syntax is much easier:

/ssh:homer@powerplant|sudo:powerplant:/root/salary.txt
/ssh:homer@powerplant|sudo:powerplant:/root/salary.txt

上面的示例连接到powerplantas homer。然后，另一个“连接”以 sudo 用户身份调用sudo并打开。在字符串中重复主机名非常重要/root/salary.txt，否则sudo它将不起作用。和以前一样，远程文件遵循与之前相同的规则。如果从工资文件调用，类似的命令M-x shell将为您提供 root shell 。powerplant

The example above connects to powerplant as homer. Then, another ‘connection’ invokes sudo and opens /root/salary.txt as a sudo’d user. It is very important that you repeat the hostname in the sudo string or it will not work. As before, remote files obey the same rules as earlier. Commands like M-x shell will give you a root shell on powerplant if invoked from the salary file.

书签

您可以使用书签（请参阅书签和寄存器）远程文件，并且如果您稍后使用或C-x r m重新打开书签，TRAMP 将自动重新连接。书签非常有用，可以节省大量时间，特别是对于复杂的多跳。C-x r bC-x r l

Bookmarks

You can bookmark (see Bookmarks and Registers) remote files with C-x r m and TRAMP will automatically reconnect if you re-open a bookmark later with C-x r b or C-x r l. Bookmarks are extremely useful and a great time saver, especially for complex multi-hops.

最后，我建议您将此代码片段添加到您的init 文件中。这是一个自定义命令，当作为 调用时M-x sudo，使用 TRAMP 以 root 身份编辑当前文件：

Finally, I recommend you add this snippet to your init file. It is a custom command that, when invoked as M-x sudo, uses TRAMP to edit the current file as root:

(defun sudo ()
  "Use TRAMP to `sudo' the current buffer"
  (interactive)
  (when buffer-file-name
    (find-alternate-file
     (concat "/sudo:root@localhost:"
             buffer-file-name))))
(defun sudo ()
  "Use TRAMP to `sudo' the current buffer"
  (interactive)
  (when buffer-file-name
    (find-alternate-file
     (concat "/sudo:root@localhost:"
             buffer-file-name))))

从上面的内容来看，调整字符串并构建多跳命令很容易——如果您是 elisp 的新手并且需要多跳，请将其视为开始学习的有趣的第一个地方。

From the above, it’s easy to tweak the string and build multi-hopped commands — if you are new to elisp and you need multi-hops, consider it a fun first place to start learning.

结论
Conclusion

TRAMP 与 Emacs 的内置 shell 支持及其窗口和缓冲区相结合，使其成为 tmux 和基于 GNU 屏幕的工作流程的良好替代品。通过在 Emacs 中进行远程文件编辑，您可以统一环境，并大大减少不同 Emacs 会话带来的心理环境切换。 TRAMP 是 Emacs 中一项非常强大的功能，并且比其他替代方案更值得使用 - 它永远不会完全取代现有的远程编辑方法，但它是一个很好的起点。

TRAMP, in conjunction with Emacs’s built-in shell support, and its windows and buffers, make it a fine replacement for tmux & GNU screen-based work flows. By keeping the remote file editing inside Emacs, you unify your environment and you greatly lessen the mental context switching of having disparate Emacs sessions. TRAMP is a really powerful feature in Emacs and one that is worth using over other alternatives — it’ll never completely replace the incumbent methods of remote editing but it’s a good place to start.

EWW：Emacs Web Wowser

EWW: Emacs Web Wowser

很久以前，Emacs 屈服于Zawinski 的软件封装定律，该定律指出：“每个程序都会尝试扩展，直到它可以读取邮件。那些不能如此扩展的程序将被那些可以扩展的程序所取代，即内置的不是一个而是多个邮件客户端。

Long ago Emacs succumbed to Zawinski’s Law of Software Envelopment that states, “Every program attempts to expand until it can read mail. Those programs which cannot so expand are replaced by ones which can”, by having not one, but many, mail clients built in.

显然，对于二十一世纪，我们需要提高标准。因此，Emacs 有一个内置的 Web 浏览器 EWW（Emacs Web Wowser）也就不足为奇了。

Clearly, for the twenty-first century, we need to raise the bar. So it should come as no great surprise that Emacs has a built-in web browser, EWW — the Emacs Web Wowser.

EWW正在积极开发中，实际上非常有用。它的渲染器仅限于基本的 HTML 和图像支持，因此它与现有的基于文本的浏览器没有太大区别。然而，尽管其渲染器有限，但它非常适合阅读技术文档、快速网络搜索以及浏览您不希望老板看到的网站。

EWW, under active development, is actually very useful. Its renderer is limited to basic HTML and image support so it is not terribly different from existing text-based browsers. However, despite its limited renderer, it is excellent for perusing technical documentation, quick web searches, and browsing web sites you don’t want your boss to see.

版本兼容性

EWW 首次在 Emacs 24.4 中引入，但在 Emacs 25 中真正取得了长足进步，提供了更多功能和错误修复。在 Emacs 26 和 27 中添加了额外的可用性功能。

Version compatibility

EWW was first introduced in Emacs 24.4, but really hits its stride in Emacs 25 with many more features and bug fixes. In Emacs 26 & 27 additional usability features were added.

要使用 EWW，只需键入M-x eww，系统就会提示您输入 URL 或搜索词。默认情况下，搜索引擎是DuckDuckGo，但您可以自定义eww-search-prefix并将其更改为其他引擎。从 Emacs 27 开始，键入C-u M-x eww将创建一个新的 EWW 缓冲区，即使该缓冲区已经存在。

To use EWW, simply type M-x eww and you are prompted for an URL or a search term. By default, the search engine is DuckDuckGo, but you can Customize eww-search-prefix and change it to something else. Starting with Emacs 27, typing C-u M-x eww will create a new EWW buffer even if one already exists.

外部和内部浏览

您可以使用以下命令指示 Emacs 在 Web 浏览器中打开内容M-x browse-url。 Emacs 将使用变量browse-url-default-browser，该函数将尝试根据您的操作系统和安装的浏览器猜测要使用的正确浏览器。

您可以通过键入 来自定义默认浏览器M-x customize-option browse-url-default-browser。

External and internal browsing

You can instruct Emacs to open things in a web browser with the command M-x browse-url. Emacs will use the variable browse-url-default-browser, a function that will attempt to guess the right browser to use depending on your operating system and installed browser.

You can customize the default browser by typing M-x customize-option browse-url-default-browser.

EWW 中的导航主要通过键盘进行（正如您对 Emacs 所期望的那样），但可以使用鼠标单击超链接。

Navigation in EWW is mostly through the keyboard (as you would expect from Emacs) but hyperlinks are clickable with a mouse.

按键 描述
TAB,S-TAB 循环到下一个/上一个超链接
q 退出EWW
& 打开页面为M-x browse-url
B 显示书签
b 添加书签
H 显示浏览器历史记录
l,r 向后/向前浏览历史记录
p, n, u,t 语义网络导航辅助工具
R 启用阅读器模式
RET 浏览链接
C-u RET 在外部浏览器中打开链接
M-s M-w 在 EWW 中搜索点
M-RET 在新缓冲区中打开链接 (Emacs 26)
s 切换到另一个 EWW 缓冲区 (Emacs 26)
w 复制此处的链接 (Emacs 26)

不幸的是，在所有版本的 Emacs 中，书签功能与 Emacs 自己的书签实用程序是分开的，后者可以在所有 Emacs 中使用——这确实是一种耻辱，因为组合起来会更有用。

In all versions of Emacs the bookmark functionality is unfortunately separate from Emacs’s own bookmark utility that work across all of Emacs — a shame, really, as a combined one would be far more useful.

最常用的命令是TAB和S-TAB打开超链接；因为它们l是r您将用来在浏览器历史记录中后退和前进的工具。仅当网页从语义上说明哪些超链接是下一个和上一个超链接时，命令p、n和才起作用。ut

The most common commands to use is TAB and S-TAB to open hyperlinks; and l and r as they are the ones you will use to go backward and forward through the browser history. The commands p, n, u and t only work if the web page semantically says which hyperlinks are the next and previous ones.

您可以使用切换到阅读器模式R。这非常有用。它删除了——或者试图删除，但 EWW 在大多数情况下都是正确的——所有干扰因素，只留下文本的主体。非常适合阅读。

You can switch to a reader mode with R. It’s very useful. It strips out – or attempts to, but EWW gets it right most of the time – all the distractions and leaves just the main body of text. Great for reading.

命令M-s M-w也很方便。它将获取活动区域并将其发送到默认搜索引擎（通常是DuckDuckGo）并在 EWW 中显示结果。

The command M-s M-w is also handy. It will take the active region and send it to the default search engine (usually DuckDuckGo) and display the results in EWW.

Dired：文件和目录

Dired: Files and Directories

浏览文件系统上的文件和目录并与之交互是 Emacs 非常适合的另一项任务。除了以通常的方式编辑本地文件和使用 TRAMP 编辑远程文件之外，您还可以使用 Emacs 的目录编辑器dired来操作目录和文件。

Both browsing and interacting with files and directories on your file system are another task for which Emacs is eminently well-suited. Aside from editing local files the usual way, and remote files using TRAMP, you can manipulate directories and files using Emacs’s directory editor, dired.

要访问 dired，您可以通过多种方式执行此操作：

To access dired, you can do so in multiple ways:

从 IDO 模式
From IDO mode

您可以C-d在查找文件时键入以C-x C-f在该文件的当前目录中打开一个dired缓冲区。

You can type C-d when finding files with C-x C-f to open a dired buffer in that file’s current directory.

作为命令
As a command

该命令M-x dired将打开一个提示，询问您要打开的目标位置。它默认为default-directory，当前缓冲区所在的目录。与 TRAMP 一样，如果文件是远程的，Emacs 会询问您是否想要远程定向会话。

The command M-x dired opens a prompt that asks you for the dired location to open. It defaults to default-directory, the directory the current buffer is in. As with TRAMP, if the file is remote Emacs will ask you if you want a remote dired session.

作为键绑定
As a key bind

键绑定的C-x d工作方式与上面的命令相同。命令C-x 4 d, 执行相同的操作，但在另一个窗口中。

The key binding C-x d works identically to the command above. The command, C-x 4 d, does the same but in the other window.

当您在 Emacs 中打开一个 Dired 缓冲区时，您会看到类似于以下内容的视图：

When you open a dired buffer in Emacs, you’re greeted with a view that looks similar to this:

/usr/share/dict:
total used in directory 2328 available 187646744
drwxr-xr-x   2 root root   4096 Feb 16 09:57 .
drwxr-xr-x 326 root root  12288 Mar 27 11:43 ..
-rw-r--r--   1 root root 938848 Oct 23  2011 american-english
-rw-r--r--   1 root root 938969 Oct 23  2011 british-english
-rw-r--r--   1 root root    199 Jan 14  2014 select-wordlist
/usr/share/dict:
total used in directory 2328 available 187646744
drwxr-xr-x   2 root root   4096 Feb 16 09:57 .
drwxr-xr-x 326 root root  12288 Mar 27 11:43 ..
-rw-r--r--   1 root root 938848 Oct 23  2011 american-english
-rw-r--r--   1 root root 938969 Oct 23  2011 british-english
-rw-r--r--   1 root root    199 Jan 14  2014 select-wordlist

如果您使用 Linux 命令行，其输出应该看起来很熟悉。这是因为 Emacs 与其他命令（如 ）的精神保持一致M-x grep，只是增加了现有命令行实用程序的输出。在这种情况下，通常是ls -al，但您可以通过自定义更改使用的开关dired-listing-switches。

If you use the Linux command line, its output should look familiar. That is because Emacs, in keeping with the spirit of other commands like M-x grep, simply augment the output from existing command line utilities. In this case, it is usually ls -al, but you can change the switches used by customizing dired-listing-switches.

微软Windows

如果您使用 Microsoft Windows，则不用担心。 Emacs 包含一个ls用 elisp 编写的模拟层。 Emacs 不会调用ls，而是直接查询操作系统。最终结果是一个跨平台工作的无缝界面。

Microsoft Windows

If you use Microsoft Windows, then don’t worry. Emacs includes a ls emulation layer written in elisp. Instead of calling out to ls, Emacs will instead query the operating system directly. The end result is a seamless interface that works across platforms.

正如我之前谈到的，缓冲区的概念和 Emacs 的“增强”系统是与外部程序对话的一种强大而实用的方式。当 Emacs 调用 时ls，输出将被插入到缓冲区中，被dired-mode激活，并且文本会通过突出显示、超链接和其他隐藏属性进行增强，以帮助 Emacs 机械地导航文本。主模式本身提供按键绑定，以便按下RET文件即可打开它。事实上，与任何缓冲区一样，您可以复制 dired 的输出，因为它基本上是纯文本。

As I talked about earlier, the concept of The Buffer and Emacs’s “augmentation” system is a powerful and pragmatic way of talking to external programs. When Emacs calls out to ls, the output is inserted into the buffer, the dired-mode activated, and the text augmented with highlighting and hyperlinks and other hidden properties to help Emacs navigate the text mechanically. The major mode itself supplies the key bindings so that pressing RET on a file opens it. Indeed, as with any buffer, you can copy the output of dired as it is basically plain text.

大多数 Emacs 初学者——甚至中级用户——从来没有真正掌握 dired。大多数人从未超越过用它来导航目录，这是一种耻辱，因为在其简单的外观背后是一个非常复杂且高效的文件和目录操作系统。事实上，有数百个 dired 命令以及数十个与其他命令的交互，可以与 dired 的界面无缝协作。

Most Emacs beginners – and even intermediate users – never really get to grips with dired. Most never get beyond navigating directories with it, which is a shame because behind its simple exterior is a very complex and efficient system for file and directory operations. Indeed, there are hundreds of dired commands and dozens of interactions with other commands that work seamlessly with dired’s interface.

导航

Navigation

导航 dired 相当简单，而且由于它是一个缓冲区，所有常用的导航辅助工具都可以使用：Isearch、箭头键。

Navigating dired is fairly straightforward and since it’s a buffer, all your usual navigational aids work: Isearch, arrow keys.

按键 描述
RET 访问文件或目录
^ 上一级目录
q 退出干涸
n, p, C-n,C-p 在列表中向上/向下移动点

但是，^如果您想要上一个目录到当前目录的父目录，则需要键。命令C-n和n&C-p以及p向下或向上一行，但也会重新调整您的点，使其位于文件名之前。

However, ^ is the key you need if you want to go up one directory to the parent of your current directory. The commands C-n and n & C-p and p go down or up a line but also reorient your point so it is positioned right before the filename.

当您按下 时RET，Emacs 将访问该文件或目录；如果它是一个目录，则打开一个新的dired缓冲区。因此，q在访问子目录后按下应该会带您返回到最后一次访问的缓冲区。

When you press RET, Emacs will visit the file or directory; if it is a directory, a new dired buffer is opened. So pressing q after visiting a sub-directory should take you back to your last dired buffer.

标记和取消标记

Marking and Unmarking

如果您想对多个文件或目录执行操作，标记和取消标记是您经常要做的事情。

Marking and unmarking things is something you’ll do frequently if you want to carry out operations on multiple files or directories.

按键 描述
m 标记为活跃
u 取消标记为活动
U 取消标记所有内容
d 删除标志

标记和删除标记之间必须有一个重要的区别：删除d 标记D（并且 a放置在标记项目旁边）和m 标记。标记永远不会受到删除命令的影响，反之亦然，但删除标记文件的命令除外。标记的文件以 突出显示*。

An important distinction must be made between marking and flagging for deletion: d flags for deletion (and a D is placed next to the flagged item) and m marks. Marks are never affected by the delete command, and vice versa, except for one command that deletes marked files. Marked files are highlighted with *.

标记和标记都会将点前进到下一个项目（就像您键入了C-n），但您可以使用负参数反转方向。

Marking and flagging both advance the point to the next item (as though you’d typed C-n) but you can reverse direction with a negative argument.

发现更多

dired 中有如此多的命令，不可能列出所有命令。我建议您应用通常的探索性方法（正确的，描述模式，列出绑定到前缀的键）来发现其余的内容。

或者，您可以尝试我的包 Discover，它向 Emacs 添加了描述性弹出菜单。您还可以浏览我的网站，获取详细的文章，其中详细介绍了各种令人讨厌的功能。

Discover more

There are so many commands in dired that listing all of them is not possible. I recommend you apply the usual exploratory approaches (Apropos, describing the mode, listing keys bound to prefixes) to discover the rest.

Alternatively, you can try out my package, Discover, that adds descriptive popup menus to Emacs. You can also browse my website for detailed articles that cover various dired features in great detail.

还有标记特定事物的标记命令：

There are also mark commands that mark specific things:

按键 描述
* m 标记区域
* u 取消区域标记
* % 通过正则表达式标记文件
* . 按扩展名标记文件
t,* t 切换标记
* c 更改标记

前缀键*充满了标记命令。上面显示的是日常使用中最实用的四种。区域键标记或取消标记活动区域触摸的每个重复项目。 regexp 和扩展标记命令同样有用，您可以使用它* t来切换（反转）标记。

The prefix key * is full of mark commands. Shown above are the four most practical ones for day-to-day use. The region keys mark or unmark every dired item touched by an active region. The regexp and extension mark commands are similarly useful, and you can use * t to toggle (invert) the marks.

* c很特别。它将标记符号从旧的更改为新的。因此，您可以将*（默认标记符号）更改为D并将标记的文件转换为标记为删除的文件。但是，由于删除实际上是您想要对标记文件执行的唯一操作，因此有一个特殊命令可以删除标记文件，另一个命令也可以删除标记文件。

* c is special. It changes the mark symbol from old to new. So, you can change * (the default mark symbol) to D and turn the marked files into files flagged for deletion. However, as deleting is practically the only thing you’d want to do with flagged files, there is a special command that deletes flagged files and another that deletes marked ones too.

运营

Operations

您可以对活动项目（如果 dired 中没有标记的文件）或标记的项目（如果有）执行操作。

You can carry out actions – or operations – on either the active item (if there are no marked files in dired) or the marked ones, if there are.

当您对标记的文件进行操作时，Emacs 通常会要求您确认操作，并列出受影响的文件。与标记命令一样，您可以执行许多操作。我们先来看看基本的：

When you operate on marked files, Emacs will usually ask you to confirm the action, and lists the affected files. Like the mark commands, there are many operations you can do. Let’s take a look at the basic ones first:

密钥（标记文件） 描述
C 复制文件
R 重命名或移动文件
O 改变所有者
G 更改组别
M 更改权限
D 删除标记（显示为*）
x 删除标记（显示为D）
F 访问文件（需要 dired-x）
c 压缩标记为文件
（Emacs 25 或更高版本）

上面的大多数键都是不言自明的。只要记住x和D如果要删除文件之间的区别即可。

Most of the keys above are self-explanatory. Just remember the difference between x and D if you want to delete files.

在直接缓冲区之间复制或重命名

如果您自定义该选项，您可以在具有直接缓冲区的两个窗口之间复制或重命名（移动）文件dired-dwim-target。请小心，不要意外地将文件移动到您忘记已打开的错误的 Dired 缓冲区 — 我自己就犯过好几次这样的错误！

Copying or renaming between dired buffers

You can copy or rename (move) files between two windows with dired buffers if you customize the option dired-dwim-target. Be careful you don’t accidentally move files to an errant dired buffer you forgot you had open — I’ve made that mistake myself quite a few times!

还有一些键不会专门作用于标记的文件：

There are also keys that don’t act on marked files specifically:

按键 描述
g 刷新指定缓冲区
+ 创建一个子目录
s 按名称/日期切换排序
<,> 跳转到上一个/下一个目录
j 跳转到文件

默认情况下，Emacs（在 Emacs 25.1 之前的版本中）不会跟踪对文件系统所做的更改。因此，您必须通过键入 显式刷新 dired g。顺便说一下，这个命令是通用刷新、恢复或重新运行某些键。在 Emacs 25.1 或更高版本中，如果您的 Emacs 版本是使用通知跟踪进行编译的，它将使用您的操作系统自动跟踪具有 Dired 缓冲区的目录更改。

Emacs (in versions prior to Emacs 25.1) will not track changes made to the file system by default. Therefore, you must explicitly refresh dired by typing g. This command, incidentally, is the universal refresh, revert or rerun something key. In Emacs 25.1 or newer, if your version of Emacs is compiled with notification tracking, it will use your operating system to track changes to directories with a dired buffer automatically.

迪雷德-X

有些命令需要dired-x.这是一个默认情况下没有充分理由启用的软件包，不幸的是，您必须手动启用。将其添加到您的初始化文件中以使其生效：

(require 'dired-x)

Dired-X

Some commands require dired-x. It’s a package that for no good reason is not enabled by default that, unfortunately, you have to manually enable. Add this to your init file for it to take effect:

(require 'dired-x)

安装后dired-x，您可以使用F，它可以访问所有标记的文件。重要的是，它将尝试打开文件并为每个文件提供自己的窗口 - 这可能是您不想要的。为了避免这种情况，请在后台打开它们，输入C-u F.

With dired-x installed you can use F, which visits all marked files. Importantly, it will attempt to open files and give each file its own window — which you may not want. To avoid this, and open them in the background, type C-u F.

密钥（标记文件） 描述
M-s a C-s 开始isearch
Q 外部参照查询替换正则表达式
A 通过正则表达式进行外部参照搜索
! 同步 shell 命令
& 异步 shell 命令

有时，您必须搜索或替换文件中的文本，并且您可以使用相当尴尬的键绑定来进行多文件 Isearch M-s a C-s。该命令Q确实C-M-%在每个标记的文件上调用 – 查询替换正则表达式 – 但不要忘记保存更改（C-x s查询以保存每个未保存的缓冲区）。

Occasionally, you have to either search through or replace text in files and you can multi-file Isearch with the rather awkward key binding M-s a C-s. The command, Q, does calls C-M-% – query replace regexp – on every marked file — but don’t forget to save the changes (C-x s to query to save every unsaved buffer).

如果启用了dired-x，不带标记的调用!和 dired 将尝试猜测该文件的下一个操作：如果它是一个文件，它会询问您是否要解压缩它。如果它是一个文件，Emacs 将调用它。变量中指定了多种模式。这是一个非常有用的功能。.zip.patchpatchdired-guess-shell-alist-default

Call ! with no marks and dired will attempt to guess the next operation on that file if dired-x is enabled: If it’s a .zip file, it will ask if you want to unzip it. If it’s a .patch file, Emacs will call patch on it. There are many patterns specified in the variable dired-guess-shell-alist-default. It is a very useful feature.

通过 标记、shell 键!和&，可以调用 shell 命令。它们将每个标记的文件作为参数：每个 shell 命令一个，或者将所有文件传递给一个命令，并用空格分隔。然后，这些命令将同步（使用!）或异步运行&。

With marks, the shell keys, ! and &, call out to a shell command. They take every marked file as arguments: either one-per-shell command, or all of them passed to one command, separated by spaces. The commands are then run either synchronously (with !) or asynchronously with &.

考虑这种情况：我们有两个文件american-english，british-english并且根据您如何表达 shell 命令，行为会发生变化。您可以选择指定*或?。*其工作方式类似于 shell 的文件 glob 模式，Emacs 将所有标记的文件作为一个长参数插入到单个命令中：

Consider this scenario: we have two files american-english and british-english and depending on how you phrase the shell command, the behavior changes. You can optionally specify either * or ?. * works like a shell’s file glob pattern and Emacs inserts all marked files as one long argument to a single command:

echo *
echo *

印刷：

Prints:

american-english british-english
american-english british-english

然而：

Whereas:

echo ?
echo ?

印刷：

Prints:

american-english
british-english
american-english
british-english

如果有输出，并且只有几行，则输出将打印在回显区域中。否则，它会被重定向到一个名为 的专用缓冲区*Shell Command Output*。

The output, if there is any, is printed in the echo area if it is only a few lines. Otherwise, it is redirected to a dedicated buffer called *Shell Command Output*.

跨目录工作

Working Across Directories

确实是一个常见的事情：如何标记文件/foo/但也/foo/bar/？答案就是i命令。在 dired 中输入i目录会将其作为子目录插入到同一 dired 缓冲区中。这意味着您可以在 dired 目录中使用相同的标记和标志命令，前提是它们位于相同的 dired 缓冲区中。您可以折叠子目录 - 这意味着命令在折叠时不会应用于它 - 使用$.

A common thing indeed: how do you mark files in /foo/ but also /foo/bar/? The answer is the i command. Typing i on a directory in dired inserts it in the same dired buffer as a sub-directory. That means you can use the same mark and flag commands across dired directories provided they are in the same dired buffer. You can collapse a sub-directory – meaning commands won’t apply to it while it is collapsed – with $.

通过将多个目录插入共享的目录缓冲区，您不仅可以同时查看多个目录，还可以像处理一个大目录一样处理它们。这是 Emacs 中另一个强大但未被充分利用的功能。

By inserting multiple directories into a shared dired buffer, you can not only glance at multiple directories at the same time but you can also work on them as though they were one large directory. This is another powerful but underutilized feature in Emacs.

然而，还有另一种方法，因为输入i很乏味，并且如果您想递归地应用 dired 或 shell 命令，则效果不佳。

There is another approach, however, as typing i is tedious and won’t work well if you recursively want to apply a dired or shell command.

要解决这个问题，您可以使用 Emacs 的find包装器命令。我认为这些命令与 dired 的强大功能相结合，几乎完全取代了find和的所有直接使用xargs。借助 dired 的 shell 命令支持和广泛的文件操作，我可以在 Emacs 中完成大多数人难以完成的工作find。

To get around that problem, you can use Emacs’s find wrapper commands. I consider these commands, combined with the power of dired, to almost completely replace all direct use of find and xargs. With dired’s shell command support and extensive file operations, I can do in Emacs what most people struggle to do well with find.

所有命令都会获取输出find并构建相对于起始目录的 Dired 缓冲区。 Emacs 足够聪明，可以注意到缓冲区文件名部分的相对路径。所有命令都照常工作。

All commands take the output of find and build a dired buffer relative to a starting directory. Emacs is clever enough to notice the relative paths in what was the filename portion of the buffer. All commands in dired work as usual.

命令 描述
find-dired find使用模式进行调用
find-name-dired 拨打find电话-name
find-grep-dired 来电find和grep
find-lisp-find-dired 使用 Emacs 和 regexp 查找文件

前三个命令调用find命令行实用程序。find-dired与 grep 命令一样，是最基本的命令：您必须为其提供一个find模式和一个起始目录。find-name-dired仅根据文件名通过 shell glob 模式进行查找，从您选择的特定目录开始。find-grep-dired匹配所有文件，但仅显示与传递给 的模式匹配的文件grep。

The first three commands call out to find, the command line utility. find-dired, like with the grep commands, is the most basic one: you have to give it a find pattern and a starting directory. find-name-dired finds by shell glob patterns against the filename only, starting in a particular directory of your choosing. find-grep-dired matches all files but only displays the ones that match a pattern passed to grep.

微软Windows

Microsoft Windows 可以选择安装交叉编译的二进制文件（例如 GNUWin32 或 Cygwin）或使用find-lisp-find-dired.

Microsoft Windows

Microsoft Windows has a choice of installing cross-compiled binaries like GNUWin32 or Cygwin or using find-lisp-find-dired.

该命令find-lisp-find-dired是 Emacs 的 elisp 实现find-dired。它适用于任何平台，不需要外部工具。作为回报，它没有那么强大。此外，它使用 Emacs 的正则表达式引擎，而不是shell 通配符。

The command find-lisp-find-dired is Emacs’s elisp implementation of find-dired. It works on any platform and require no external tools. In return, it is not as powerful. Also, it uses Emacs’s regular expression engine, and not shell globbing.

外壳命令

Shell Commands

正如有关 dired 的章节所演示的，Emacs 中有一些与 shell 交互的强大命令。对于所有其他缓冲区，有更通用但同样强大的 shell 命令可用于通用缓冲区。

As the chapter on dired demonstrated, there are powerful commands in Emacs that interact with the shell. For all other buffers, there are the far more general, but equally powerful, shell commands that work on generic buffers.

按键 描述
M-! 调用 shell 命令并打印输出
C-u M-! 如上所述，但插入到缓冲区中
M-& 类似M-!但异步
C-u M-& 类似C-u M-!但异步
M-| 通过管道将区域传输到 shell 命令
C-u M-| 喜欢M-|但替换区域

您可以使用 调用任何 shell 命令，M-!如果文本只有几行长，Emacs 将在回显区域中打印其输出；或者如果您*Shell Command Output*使用过M-!，则调用一个专用缓冲区。使用通用参数调用任一命令都会将输出插入到当前缓冲区中。*Async Shell Command*M-&

You can invoke any shell command with M-! and Emacs will print its output in the echo area, if the text is only a few lines long; or a dedicated buffer called *Shell Command Output* if you used M-!, and *Async Shell Command* if you used M-&. Calling either command with a universal argument will instead insert the output into your current buffer at the point.

该M-|命令更加实用。它将区域作为输入，并将其发送到您选择的 shell 命令的标准输入，并以与以下大致相同的方式返回输出M-!：在回显区域或专用缓冲区中。使用通用参数调用命令，活动区域将被替换；这C-u M-|对于临时调用命令（例如uniq修改其输入的其他命令行工具）非常有用。

The M-| command is far more practical. It takes the region as input and sends it to the standard input of a shell command of your choosing and returns the output in much the same way as M-!: either in the echo area or a dedicated buffer. Calling the command with a universal argument, the active region is replaced instead; that makes C-u M-| extremely useful for offhand calls to commands like uniq or other command line tools that modify their input.

虽然M-&它是异步的——也就是说，它不会阻塞 Emacs，直到它终止——但对于长时间运行的任务来说，这是一个相当糟糕的选择。使用它要好得多M-x compile。

Although M-& is asynchronous – that is, it won’t block Emacs until it terminates – it is a rather poor choice for long-running tasks. It’s far better to use M-x compile.

在 Emacs 中编译

Compiling in Emacs

调用 shell 命令意味着快速、一次性的命令，通常不是您经常重复执行的操作。为此，您应该考虑 Emacs 的M-x compile命令，尽管它的名字如此，但它不仅仅擅长编译。

Calling out to shell commands is meant for quick, one-off commands and usually not something you regularly do, over and over. For that purpose, you should consider Emacs’s M-x compile command that, despite its name, excels at more than just compilation.

命令 描述
M-x compile 运行命令并跟踪错误
M-x recompile 重新运行最后一个命令
M-g M-n,M-g M-p 跳转到下一个/上一个错误（全局）
g 重新运行最后一个命令
C-x p c 在当前项目中编译

当您调用 时M-x compile，系统会要求您输入命令，并且 Emacs 会假定您正在使用make.但是，您可以随意将其替换为您想要跟踪输出的任何命令：单元测试、编译、运行脚本——您能想到的都可以。

When you invoke M-x compile, you are asked for a command and Emacs kindly assumes you’re using make. However, you are free to replace it with any command of which you want to track the output: unit tests, compiling, running a script — you name it.

它的主要优点M-x compile是它的辅助命令M-x recompile，因为它会重新运行您的上一个命令。由于其模式匹配引擎，Compile 还可以跟踪错误。与M-x grep和一样M-x occur，M-g M-n和M-g M-p命令将跳过调用堆栈或编译器错误日志，前提是它们的格式与 Emacs 所知道的相匹配。从 Python 到大多数编译器的所有内容都是 Emacs 已知的，因此它可能也适合您的。

The main advantage of M-x compile is its helper command M-x recompile, as it re-runs your last command. Compile also tracks errors thanks to its pattern matching engine. Like M-x grep and M-x occur, the M-g M-n and M-g M-p commands will jump through a call stack or compiler error log provided their formatting matches one Emacs knows. Everything from Python to most compilers are known to Emacs, so it will probably work for yours too.

Emacs 中的 shell

Shells in Emacs

为什么不使用 Emacs 作为“多路复用器”并使用 Emacs 来运行 shell，而不是使用外部终端仿真器 – 或者在终端中运行 Emacs，以便您可以将其与tmux或一起使用？screen结合 TRAMP 和 Emacs 的平铺窗口管理和缓冲区支持，您可以替换专用终端模拟器的几乎所有常见用例。

Instead of using an external terminal emulator – or running Emacs in a terminal just so you can use it with tmux or screen – why not use Emacs as the “multiplexer” and use Emacs to run your shell instead? Combined with TRAMP and Emacs’s tiling window management and buffer support, you can replace almost all common use cases of dedicated terminal emulators.

bash与 Emacs一样，可以通过三种方式与 shell 交互。一种是围绕外部现有外壳（如 ）的简单包装，bash称为M-x shell;另一个是用 elisp 编写的完整 shell 实现，称为M-x eshell;第三个是名为 的终端仿真器M-x ansi-term。

There are three ways of interacting with shells – like bash – in Emacs. One is a simple wrapper around an external, existing shell (like bash) called M-x shell; another is a complete shell implementation written in elisp called M-x eshell; and the third is a terminal emulator called M-x ansi-term.

这三个人都非常强大，并且每个人都试图以自己特殊的方式解决问题。无论您使用哪一种（并且您最终可能会使用不止一种）都需要进行一些权衡。

All three are very powerful and each attempts to solve the problem in their own special way. Whichever one you use (and you may well end up using more than one) comes with a number of trade-offs.

然而，这三者都使用 elisp 与外部程序通信，或者在 Emacs 中实现 shell，或者解释呈现复杂的交互式程序（如top.所有这三个都还使用 Emacs 强大的缓冲区范例（现在您已经非常熟悉）来为所有三个实现提供统一的接口。

All three, however, use elisp to either communicate with an external program, or to implement a shell in Emacs, or to interpret the terminal control codes needed to render complex, interactive programs like top. All three also use Emacs’s powerful buffer paradigm – that by now you are quite familiar with – to provide a unified interface for all three implementations.

缓冲区范式在这里特别强大，因为与外部程序或直接与操作系统通信的能力是 Emacs 如此强大的编辑器的一部分。您可以在缓冲区中获得所有编辑和移动命令以及 elisp 的强大功能，该缓冲区同时用于更传统的操作（例如文本编辑），但现在也用于更高级和专业的操作（例如与bash.而且因为两个极端都有一个共同点——缓冲区——你不必重新学习一个全新的系统；不再需要用鼠标在终端仿真器中手动选择文本并将其复制到文本编辑器或 Web 浏览器中。在 Emacs 中，都是文本，您熟悉的所有移动和编辑命令在这里都完全相同。

The buffer paradigm is especially powerful here as the ability to communicate with external programs or directly with the operating system is part of what makes Emacs such a powerful editor. You gain all the editing and movement commands, and the power of elisp, in a buffer that is simultaneously used for more traditional things like text editing but now also for far more advanced and specialized things like interacting with bash. And because both extremes share a common ground – the buffer – you don’t have to re-learn an entirely new system; no more fretting with hand-selecting text in a terminal emulator with a mouse just to copy it into your text editor or web browser. In Emacs, it is all text and all the movement and editing commands you are familiar with work exactly the same here.

M-x shell：外壳模式

M-x shell: Shell Mode

Emacs 中的 Shell 模式调用外部程序（例如bash在 Linux 或cmd.exeWindows 上），并在 Windows 上重定向stdin、stdout和stderr，或通过伪终端（在 Linux 上），以便您可以通过 Emacs 与底层 shell 交互。

Shell mode in Emacs calls out to an external program – such as bash on Linux or cmd.exe on Windows – and either redirects stdin, stdout and stderr on Windows, or through a pseudo-terminal (on Linux) so you can interact with the underlying shell through Emacs.

然而，由于 Emacs 重定向 I/O，因此您可以获得随之而来的所有优点和缺点。例如，您不能使用 shell 的本机TAB完成机制。相反，您必须使用 Emacs 自己的（在某些方面更强大）。硬币的另一面是 shell 模式缓冲区完全是文本：您可以编辑和删除命令的输出，并且可以轻松地在缓冲区中删除和拉出文本。这使得 shell 模式变得灵活但两极分化。像这样的程序top根本man不起作用，或者即使起作用，它们也不能很好地工作。8

Because Emacs redirects I/O, you gain all the benefits and downsides that go with that, however. For instance, you cannot use your shell’s native TAB-completion mechanism. Instead, you have to use Emacs’s own (which is more powerful in some respects). The flip side to the coin is that a shell mode buffer is entirely text: you can edit and delete output from commands and you can kill and yank text to and from the buffer with ease. That makes shell mode flexible but polarizing. Programs like top and man don’t work at all, or if they do, they don’t work well.8

我个人使用 shell 模式来满足几乎所有的命令行需求。我很少使用交互式终端程序，当需要时，我可以使用 EmacsM-x ansi-term进行正确的终端模拟。

I personally use shell mode for almost all my command line needs. I use very few interactive terminal programs and when I need to I can use Emacs’s M-x ansi-term for proper terminal emulation.

优点：自由格式的文本编辑和移动，因为 shell 模式只是一个简单的缓冲区，超过了缺点。

The upsides: free-form text editing and movement because shell mode is just a simple buffer outweighing the downsides.

GNUreadline和默认值

大多数 Linux 发行版使用 GNU readline（一个库）来提供基本的命令提示符功能，例如：命令历史记录、搜索和替换命令以及其他有用的功能。默认情况下，它们是 Emacs 键绑定。如果您知道其中一个，则可以在此处大部分应用相同的，反之亦然。这也适用于一般编辑和移动命令。

GNU readline and defaults

Most Linux distributions use GNU readline – a library – to provide basic command prompt functionality, like: command history, search and replace commands and other useful features. They are, by default, Emacs key bindings. If you know one, you can mostly apply the same ones here and vice versa. And that goes for general editing and movement commands too.

以下是一些最有用的命令。不幸的是，它们在绑定方面到处都是。

Here are some of the most useful commands. Unfortunately, they are all over the place in terms of bindings.

按键 描述
M-p,M-n 循环查看命令历史记录
C-<up>,C-<down> 循环查看命令历史记录
M-r I向后搜索历史记录
C-c C-p,C-c C-n 跳转到上一个/下一个提示
C-c C-s 将命令输出保存到文件
C-c C-o Kills 命令输出到杀死环
C-c C-l 列出命令历史记录
C-d 删除转发字符或发送^D
C-c C-z 发送停止子作业
TAB 到点就完成了

M-p、M-n、C-<up>和都C-<down>循环浏览命令历史记录，其方式与在普通终端仿真器中使用向上和向下箭头键的方式大致相同。在 Emacs 中，它们实际上是在缓冲区中移动点，尽管这总是让不习惯 shell 模式的人感到困惑。

Both M-p, M-n, C-<up> and C-<down> cycle through the command history in much the same way that using the up and down arrow keys would in normal terminal emulators. In Emacs, they literally move the point around in the buffer though this always confuses people not used to shell mode.

M-r是触发历史反向Isearch。这是一个非常强大的命令，值得学习。C-d删除该点之前的一个字符，就像在其他地方一样。但是，如果没有输入（意味着您没有在提示符下输入任何内容），Emacs 将发送控制代码EOF来终止正在运行的程序。类似地，与作业控制中的操作C-c C-z相同。C-zbash

M-r is triggers the history reverse Isearch. It’s a very powerful command that is worth learning. C-d deletes a character ahead of the point, as it would anywhere else. However, if there is no input (meaning you haven’t typed anything at a prompt), Emacs will send the control code EOF to terminate the running program. Similarly, C-c C-z does the same as C-z in bash does for job control.

shell 模式的一个很棒的功能是能够使用 保存最后一个命令的输出到文件C-c C-s，并使用 直接将其发送到您的杀戮环C-c C-o。

One nifty feature of shell mode is the ability to save the output of the last command to a file with C-c C-s, and to send it straight to your kill ring with C-c C-o.

TAB值得特别一提。 Shellbash具有自己复杂的完成机制，而不仅仅是文件和路径。 Emacs 也是如此。您可以完成诸如主机名之类的命令ssh或组和所有者之类的事情chown。

TAB deserves its own special mention. Shells like bash feature their own complex completion mechanisms, and not just for files and paths. Emacs does too. You can complete things like hostnames for commands like ssh or groups and owners for chown.

M-x ansi-term：终端仿真器

M-x ansi-term: Terminal Emulator

Emacs 有自己的支持 ANSI 的终端仿真器。调用M-x ansi-term并选择 shell，您可以运行交互式程序，例如top或 甚至vim和emacs。

Emacs has its own ANSI-capable terminal emulator. Invoking M-x ansi-term and selecting a shell, you can run interactive programs like top or even vim and emacs.

它的主要缺点是速度慢并且不支持一些模糊的终端仿真功能。

Its main downside is its slowness and some obscure terminal emulation features are not supported.

按键 描述
C-c C-j 切换到线路模式
C-c C-k 切换到字符模式

默认情况下，ansi-term其行为类似于常规终端仿真器，而不是 shell 模式或典型的 Emacs 缓冲区。但是，您可以在两种不同的模式之间切换：行模式，就像典型的 Emacs 缓冲区；和字符模式，就像普通的终端模拟器。

By default, ansi-term acts like a regular terminal emulator and not like shell mode or a typical Emacs buffer. However, you can switch between two different modes: line mode, which is like a typical Emacs buffer; and character mode, which is like a normal terminal emulator.

默认模式是字符模式，这意味着大多数键（包括键盘字符，而不仅仅是 Emacs 键绑定）都会直接发送到底层 shell 程序，完全绕过 Emacs。有一个转义字符, C-c，Emacs 会拦截该字符，因此像C-c C-j和 之类的命令C-c C-k不会发送到子程序。所以如果你想发送C-c到子程序，你必须输入C-c C-c。

The default mode is character mode and that means most keys – including keyboard characters, and not just Emacs key bindings – are sent directly to the underlying shell program, bypassing Emacs entirely. There is an escape character, C-c, that Emacs intercepts so commands like C-c C-j and C-c C-k are not sent to the sub-program. So if you want to send C-c to the sub-program, you must type C-c C-c.

如果您想在 Emacs 中获得最忠实的终端体验，ANSI 术语是您最好的选择。我发现在行模式和字符模式之间切换相当麻烦，所以我更喜欢使用 shell 模式。

If you want the most faithful terminal experience in Emacs, ANSI term is your best bet. I find the hassle of switching between line and character mode rather cumbersome so I prefer to use shell mode instead.

M-x eshell: Emacs 的 Shell

M-x eshell: Emacs’s Shell

有人用 elisp编写了整个 shell，这不足为奇。当您运行时M-x eshell，您使用的是用 elisp 编写的 shell，它通过 Emacs 与底层主机操作系统进行通信，并为典型的 Linux 风格的bashshell 提供了一个出色的传真，并配有 elisp 模拟的 GNU coreutils 命令，例如ls，cp，cd， 还有很多。

It shouldn’t come as much of a surprise that someone has written an entire shell in elisp. When you run M-x eshell, you are using a shell that is written in elisp, that communicates, through Emacs, with the underlying host operating system and provides an excellent facsimile to a typical Linux-style bash shell, complete with elisp-emulated GNU coreutils commands like ls, cp, cd, and many more.

实际上，这意味着您可以在运行 Emacs 的所有平台上获得一致的 shell。结合本机 TRAMP 支持以及将命令输出直接重定向到 Emacs 缓冲区的能力，您将拥有一个多功能、强大且非常符合 Emacs 精神的工具。

In practice, that means you get a consistent shell across all platforms on which Emacs runs. Combined with native TRAMP support and the ability to redirect the output of commands straight into an Emacs buffer, you have a tool that is versatile, powerful and very much in the spirit of Emacs.

Eshell 比 ANSI 术语更类似于 shell 模式。它不支持诸如 之类的交互式程序top，而是在您从 Eshell 调用这些程序时打开一个专用M-x ansi-term实例来运行这些程序——这是解决该问题的聪明而务实的解决方案。

Eshell is more akin to shell mode than ANSI term. It does not support interactive programs like top, preferring instead to open a dedicated M-x ansi-term instance to run those programs when you call them from Eshell — a clever and pragmatic solution to the problem.

另一个重要的区别是，尽管 Eshell 的灵感来自于诸如 之类的 shell bash，但事实上，它是它自己的 shell 实现，具有随之而来的所有怪癖、功能和限制。必须说，Eshell 首先是一个 elisp shell，因为你在 Eshell 中输入的每个命令都会首先通过 Eshell 自己的模拟层过滤，然后通过 Emacs 自己的交互式命令，最后通过你$PATH或当前目录中的程序。例如，您可以键入在当前目录中dired .打开会话，或在当前运行的 Emacs 中打开。M-x diredfind-file todo.orgtodo.org

Another important difference is that although Eshell is inspired by shells like bash, it is, in fact, its own shell implementation with all the quirks, features and limitations that go with it. It must be said that Eshell is an elisp shell first and foremost, as every command you type into Eshell is first filtered through Eshell’s own emulation layer, then through Emacs’s own interactive commands, and then finally through programs in your $PATH or in the current directory. For instance, you can type dired . to open a M-x dired session in the current directory, or find-file todo.org to open todo.org in your currently-running Emacs.

  1. 如果 Emacs 找到文件，它将读取并评估 elisp 的（可配置）子集.dir-locals.el。这是一个强大的概念，但无法替代项目管理。↩

  2. Emacs would read and evaluate a (configurable) subset of elisp if it found a .dir-locals.el file. It’s a powerful concept, but a poor substitute for project management.↩

  3. VC 是我之前写过的 Emacs 中的版本控制工具。↩

  4. VC is the Version Control tool in Emacs I wrote about earlier.↩

  5. 如果您使用IDO，则默认情况下此处不会完成。但 FIDO 会的。↩

  6. IDO will not complete here by default if you use it. But FIDO will.↩

  7. M-.当像带你离开原来的位置这样的命令时，它们会留下标记，你可以稍后返回。↩

  8. When commands like M-. whisk you away from where you were, they leave behind markers that you can return to later.↩

  9. 查看包管理器；输入M-s o ripgrep包列表以查找提及它的包。↩

  10. Have a look in the package manager; type M-s o ripgrep in the package list to find packages mentioning it.↩

  11. 您需要哪些是特定于平台的，但M-x customize-group doc-view RET会告诉您您需要什么。对于大多数 Linux 发行版来说，它应该可以开箱即用。↩

  12. Which ones you need is platform specific, but M-x customize-group doc-view RET will show you what you need. For most Linux distros, it should work out of the box.↩
